column13: Best Face Peel I've Ever Used!
column14:
After receiving this product as a sample, I immediately tried it. I love trying face peels and masks as I have problem skin. So I'm always looking for a quick fix. This by far was the most effective, and fascinating, face product I've ever used. My skin had lots of rosacea, acne scars, and acne. So I try to use very gentle products. This peel showed instant results.

I recommend leaving your face slightly wet after cleansing. Not dropping wet, but just a little moisture. Then when you put it on, just lightly spread it. After 15 seconds or so, that's when you start rubbing it. Your dead skin actually peels off! The first time I used it there was SO much dead skin. I couldn't believe it. After the sample ran out I instantly purchased the full size product. I also recommend wiping it off with warm water and a soft cloth to get the dead skin off. I use this product once a week because I don't want to overwork my sensitive skin.

column6: Dermal Korea Collagen Essence Full Face Facial Mask Sheet
column13: Great For an Addition of Moisture to Your Skin
column14:
This is my second time purchasing these. This purchase is really about the perfect quantity, quality and price. I've used several brands of face masks, including the Body Shop, Nivea, Garnier, My Beauty Diary etc. This ranks near Body Shop at a slightly lower price. Each mask peels off from plastic and is easy to use, soothing and refreshing.

Many of the masks have a nice scent, but they do lay on a little wet at the start, they seem saturated with the solution and do feel like you have condensed milk on you face. As it dries, it starts to feel more rejuvenating, but if the initial wetness grosses you out, then these probably aren't for you. I don't mind the excess moisture as much because I have a shower right after and I like to sit in front of a fan and have it dry faster. A fan really helps make this mask refreshing and soothing (I think there is a little methanol in this, it reminds me of a milder version of when you drink water while chewing gum).

I use a dead sea mud mask as part of my weekly routine and need a decent moisturizing mask for after or my skin dries out too much, this suits that purpose very well. This is like a nice spa day, fun and refreshing, but don't expect it to do much for you skin except hydrate and perhaps smooth if the rest of your skin care regiment is good.

I have found that excess use, more than twice a week can result in oily skin with combination skin types (like mine) and can even lead to a mild acne break out. Also, if you wear glasses, you might have to lay the nose hole several times to get it right and squeeze down the the edges above your nose, or your glasses will be fogging up the hole time (in case you are doing other stuff at the same time). If you are looking for an affordable addition of moisture or soothing for you skin, this will work well.

column6: CRYSTAL BODY DEODORANT Stick Unscented (4.25 fl oz)
column13: Finally a natural deodorant that actually works
column14:
Ever since I switched to more natural products a few years ago, I was in search of an efficient natural deodorant. I tried several brands, but wasn't very satisfied with the results. I was very tempted to try to make my own deodorant, but most recipes use coconut oil and I thought it would be greasy and stain my clothes, so I abandoned the idea.

I read about Crystal a long time ago, but for some reason never purchased one until recently. I decided to go with the travel-size one (1.5 oz) to make sure I like it. Besides, the small size makes it easy to carry around in your purse or travel bag.

I paid pretty much the same price in store for this product, so don't hesitate to order it from Amazon. It is a really good price for this product.

After using it for three months, I can say that the product really works. I don't sweat a lot (as in not a lot of moisture), but there is a certain smell that of course, bothers me. After applying this product, not only there is no moisture, but there is also no smell whatsoever. I have been exercising every morning, including walking up a big hill in my neighborhood, which is exhausting. I decided to exercise without putting on any deodorant and I did sweat a bit and there was quite a bit of armpit moisture. But whenever I apply the deodorant, I stay dry and there is no smell. I keep checking myself and cannot believe how efficient it is. I purchased a second one for my husband and it works just as good on him, with the exception that there is more moisture in his situation (he is a big guy though), but still, no smell.

The travel-size product is not a roll-on. It is basically a big stick of salt, stuck in the plastic container. I was a bit concerned at the beginning, that the stick might fall after a while, but it seems to stay in place very well. The product has no smell and it has a very smooth texture.

The Crystal stone comes from Thailand and is made from natural mineral salts. The salt keeps the bacteria in your armpits from releasing the unpleasant smell. It is hypoallergenic, vegan and contains no other ingredients than Ammonium Alum. There is a huge difference between Ammonium Alum and Aluminum Chloride/Chlorohydrate/Zirconium (toxic aluminums found in most deodorants). The toxic aluminum blocks your sweat ducts and glands and this is why it keeps you dry. But by doing so, they also prevent the body from naturally expelling toxins through sweat. They also absorb very easily into your skin and blood, which is obviously not good. Ammonium Alum, on the other hand, is not absorbed through the skin. Instead, it stays on the surface of the skin where it prevents the bacteria (responsible for causing B.O.) from multiplying.

I will not write about how to apply the product, since I noticed most reviews have already mentioned it. I do find that it dries very fast, which is another plus, since I don't have to wait around waving my arms for minutes.

Make sure not to leave the deodorant on granite or marble countertops, since it might cause discoloration.

The product might be small, but you only use very little each time and it will last for months.lts. The salt keeps the bacteria in your armpits from releasing the unpleasant smell. column6: Wrinkle Filler and Remover with Vitamin E - Best Quality - Smoothes Forehead, Chest & Frown Lines – Moisturizes & Reduces Existing Wrinkles, Helps Prevent New Creases - for Women and Men
column13: I am ordering more! This definitely has potential.
column14: I am always skeptical of products that claim to banish wrinkles because there are very few things that can actually do that and usually require a trip to a plastic surgeon. In spite of that, I am always looking for something that can soften my wrinkles, especially on my forehead and that dread "11" that I have from stress and thinking. I put this on last night and left it on overnight. The first thing I noted was the cooling sensation that it gives, which is actually rather pleasant. It is very easy to apply, just peel and stick.   When I removed it this morning, I was very surprised to see that my forehead was nearly smooth (think Botox smooth) except for my deepest line in my 11, which I think nothing short of Botox or a filler could really eradicate. It was fantastic! Once I washed my face, the effects lessened, but they did not entirely go away, and my forehead lines still look softer hours later. I am actually quite impressed. I don't know if it using this treatment repeatedly will provide long-term results, or if this is just a temporary fix that draws the moisture to the surface and plumps up the lines to make them temporarily disappear.   I think I will be reordering this product in a larger quantity to use it and find out and if it does produce lasting results, I will definitely return and give it 5 stars. This is actually a bit large on my forehead as well, so I think I will trim the "wings" off it and use those as extra treatments on my "11" area, which needs it the most, or perhaps try it on my marionette lines.   I am definitely intrigued by this product and very interested to find out what effects it could have with repeated use. I told my sister about it and she is ordering it today to try it herself. It's not a miracle in a facial strip, but it definitely has potential. I received this wrinkle remover treatment at a promotional price for the purpose of product testing and feedback in the form of an honest and unbiased review.All opinions expressed are entirely my own based on my personal experience with the product.

column6: Yardley of London English Lavender Brilliantine for Women, 2.8 Ounce
column14: One of my favorite short essays is about Yardley's Brilliantine and I wanted to share it. Enjoy!  Yardley's Brilliantine by Stephen Johnson      In the box marked "SF 1989-91," I found a small, clear jar labeled Yardley's Brilliantine. The neon-green hair goop inside the glass rim still smelled like lavender.     I moved to San Francisco after college and was ready to try new things. I bought the jar in a drugstore and promptly slicked back my hair. I purchased a nice tweed coat at a Goodwill thrift store. I went to gay clubs, and I also picked up women in small hipster bars in the Mission District. Everyone liked the scent of my hair. Each morning in the new city before going to work at various temp jobs, I rubbed the pomade on my hair and it smelled like the 1950's. I figured that Montgomery Clift had probably used this brand.      As a kid, I remember every morning my father, a code breaker for the Navy in WWII, before work would squeeze out a dab of white Brylcreem and fashion it into his dark hair with a sturdy comb with "Yellow Pages" on the handle. When he wasn't looking, I would glom too much Brylcreem into my hair, put some shaving cream on my fresh young face, and razor it with the Yellow Pages comb. I wonder if he still uses Brylcreem.      When I left San Francisco, I stopped the 1950's sensitive-guy business and grew my hair long. Years later, as a man, I decided to cut my hair short again, but by then I couldn't find the Yardley's Lavender Brilliantine any more, only a cloudy replacement that smelled like perfume.      You can only be a young man fresh to the big city once. You can only pretend to be Montgomery Clift or your father once. When you try to go back again, they won't have the right hair stuff or anything.

column6: Jojoba Oil, USDA Certified Organic, 100% Pure, Cold Pressed, Unrefined. Revitalizes Hair & Gives Skin a Radiant Youthful Look. Great treatment for Face, Lips, Cuticles, Stretch Marks
column14:
Jojoba oil is an ingredient commonly mentioned in many beauty magazines, and it’s with good reason–it’s found in many beauty products from shampoos to moisturizers. This bottle is filled with the pure oil itself, and can be used as a moisturizer for both the face and the hair. Having used this for a month now, I must say it’s a fantastic natural moisturizer.

There are a variety of oils out there that also have moisturizing properties, including argan oil and rosehip oil, but Jojoba oil tends to be a bit cheaper than those two. Another thing I really like about this is the fact that it has a very light nutty odor–you can barely detect it. I put this on after a warm shower and applying a toner and wake up the next day with extremely soft skin–I love it! This bottle specifically may not look like much, but since you don’t use much per application, one of these should be able to easily last 2+ months.

Overall, I think this is a great starting choice for anyone looking for a natural alternative moisturizer and want to give the oils a try. It’s one of the most budget friendly choices, and it really does work. For those who feel weird about putting oils on their face/body, they actually get absorbed by your body rather quickly and I haven’t experienced any breakouts whatsoever. If anything, they’ve helped my acne due to how nourishing it is for the skin. Just make sure to apply the oil sparingly–you really don’t need that much.

Please note that I was sent this product for review, and I hope that it’s been helpful for you! Feel free to leave any questions/comments below and I’ll do my best to respond.

==The Good==
+ Works fantastically as a moisturizer
+ Very light scent
+ Great value

==The Bad==
- None!

5/5

column6: Profesional Makeup Brush Set -13 pcs – Quality Cosmetic Applicators for BB Cream, Concealer, Eyeshadow, Foundation and Blush
column14:
This was the first brush set that I've ever purchased, and it's great for beginners because it has everything that you would ever need! When it first came, each brush was individually wrapped in plastic, and there was a strong odor. However, after washing them, the smell faded and the brushes didn't shed. The ferrules weren't loose and the brushes were sturdy. I think that the pink and white is quite stylish, and the little case that they come in is nice for storage. I love that these brushes are synthetic and cruelty-free.

I wish that the set swapped out the "smudging eye brush" with an actual eye brush (maybe a smaller eye shadow brush?) because it's basically those sponge-tipped applicators that come with every eye shadow that you buy at the drugstore, and most people (including me) would throw them out. I've never used this "brush", and I'm not sure how you would even wash it.

After delving into the world of makeup and discovering other companies with affordable makeup brush sets like BH Cosmetics and Coastal Scents, I also think that the price point for this set is a bit too high. On Amazon, though, this is a great set, and definitely does not feel cheap.

EDIT (9/29/2015): After storing them for a while in the included purple case, I found that the handles were somehow stuck to the case material. I had them stored in a sealed box, so moisture or pressure should not have been problems. After pulling each brush out (it felt like they were glued in!), bits of the purple case material were stuck to the handles, and the white paint was ruined. I'm not sure how that happened, but I've thrown out the case.

column6: The Honest Company - Sunscreen Lotion SPF 30, 3 Fl Oz
column14:
If by "broad spectrum protection" you mean "blistering, scorching sunburn, the likes of which you've never seen before..." then yes, this is an HONEST and accurate description of the product. I'm usually quite vigilant about my sun protection and I have that lucky olive skin tone that rarely burns even with prolonged and direct exposure to the strongest of rays on a warm August day, but this s*** right here... let's just say it's three days later and I'm still the color of an over-boiled lobster with added red dye.

When I have to chose between being exposed to carcinogenic chemicals in sunscreen or using "chemical" free alternatives from now on, I think I'll take my chances with chemically induced cancer over spontaneous human combustion. At least skin cancer has the possibility of a decent survival rate if caught early. You can't do much once you've been set ablaze by your own desire to be environmentally conscious and free of parabens.

column6: OGX Body Crème, Healing Cherry Blossom Rice Milk, 13oz
column14:
This smells really good, although the scent doesn't last a super long time for me. I feel like I am smelling a little bit of cherry in addition to the cherry blossom (it does contain cherry extract, so that makes sense). I mostly use it on my lower legs to keep them smooth and hydrated after shaving. It absorbs into the skin well and doesn't leave me feeling oily. Plus, I like layering this with the shower gel from the same product line.

You can see the ingredients list if you scroll down the product page. Please note that this contains Red #40, to which some people are allergic. Please also note that the company that makes this is now called "OGX" instead of "Organix," due to labeling issues (i.e., they don't claim that all their ingredients are organic). So don't go into this expecting an organic product. It also contains petrolatum and dimethicone, so if you are avoiding petroleum byproducts or silicones, you will want to stay away.

I have been using this once daily for a few weeks and it has not irritated my skin. I have some cuts where one of my cats attacked my lower leg (he's on medication that makes him rather aggressive as a side effect) and this did not even bother my cuts (if I am going to have issues with a lotion, it is usually around where I have broken skin -- but that was not a problem here).

In the end, I'm not in love with all the ingredients but this has been gentle enough for me to use daily and it has made a difference -- my skin is softer. So I will definitely continue to use it.

column14:
I received 3 Retseliney Acne Treatment products for review about 4 weeks ago. Since 3 all items that I received works together, I am posting same review on all 3 product page.

My grandson now has acne, only on his forehead. But, his acne is not bad enough, so doctor will not prescribe acne medicine. He tried couple of “over the counter” acne treatment, but some of the treatment is too strong, it actually made his acne flare up even more and some doesn’t work at all. I noticed he now doesn’t like to take pictures and tried to hide his forehead with hair, which makes acne even worst.

When Retseliney sent me their Acne Treatment products, my grandson visited me from NY for few weeks for the summer. So, I have him try all 3 of Retseliney’s acne product. To my amazement, even though I am not surprised since I am already a big fan of Retseliney’s skin care products, in about a month using the Retseliney’s Acne Treatment Skin care, acnes on my grandson’s forehead is completely gone! Not even trace of he ever had acnes. If I look really closely, I can see just a few spots, used to have acne, show discoloration. But from few feet away, no one will ever guessed he had acne ever. My grandson is so happy now and I can see his personality changed almost overnight. This is really AMAZING product. It’s been about 4 weeks now, but just a few days of using Retseliney, he started to see changes.

This is how he uses Retseliney products. I am not sure if this is the correct way to do it or not, but Retseliney’s customer service is superb and they will not have any problem answering if anyone have questions.

Everyday (7 days/week – at least 2 times daily ) AM and PM Skin Care. But if he sweats and have to shower, he apply same skin care again.
* He wash his face with Retseliney Acne Face Wash & Oil Control and apply Retseliney Acne Treatment Moisturizer Cream & Oil Control. (Only these 2 on his face)
* Every Wed and Saturday, he also apply Retseliney Acne Face Mask & Oil Control. He said he can actually feel his pores getting tighter. LOL. He only apply this on his forehead.

All 3 products are very gentle on his skin and cream goes on very smooth and he only have to use just little bit covers all affected area. He stayed with treatment without skipping a day. He really religiously stick to acne skin care regiment and he is so glad he did. He still have good portion of the product left. The process is pretty easy - you brush with one, then the second step, but it left my gums and teeth very sensitive after 2 weeks of use. I (surprisingly) had a cleaning scheduled during the period where I was testing this product and had no cavities, but have hot/cold sensitivity around two of my existing fillings.

I really had high hopes for this as it wasn't a tray or a leave on treatment too!

column6: Lipogaine Big 3 Premium Hair Loss Prevention shampoo for Men and Women (2 in 1 formula)- 8 oz
column14:
It's helped me tremendously with my hair thinning. I am 22 years old, and when I turned 19, my long-time childhood sweetheart and I broke up; in the aftermath, I underwent extreme stress and emotional upheaval. Stress and emotional distress, of course, can trigger hair loss. Well, it happened in a big way: I went from being a big-curly haired, happy fellow to nearly bald in a little less than a year. It was quite tragic.

Anyway, I lived with being bald for about two years, and then this past January I found this Lipogaine shampoo. This stuff does wonders, but it grows VERY slowly unless you combine it with other products. I have used their other product, the Minoxidil dropper, along with UltraX labs Hair Rush pills, and this shampoo, and the results are incredible. My hair looks almost as good as it did a few years ago in less than 8 months time. The shampoo I will use for as long as it provides thickness and growth; however, the pills and the Minoxidil cause a lot of blood pressure issues, so be aware of that. After 6 months of continuous use with the pills (the pills are the worst thing, btw), my blood pressure was regularly in pre-hypertension ranges; now, using only the shampoo, my hair still looks fine and I'm back at very healthy, regular pressures.

Overall: be careful using it because you might give yourself heart disease during prolonged use, but in the short-term, the combination of those three aforementioned products will grow you a lot of hair, and continuous use of the shampoo will help you keep said hair.

column6: Pantene Pro-V Truly Natural Hair
column13: My curls are pretty defined in low humidity but I've had great difficulties ...
column14: Makes my curls pop and STAY popped in the humidity!  My curls are pretty defined in low humidity but I've had great difficulties keeping curls in my hair for weeks since the summer humidity came upon us.  I'll have curls out of the shower but in no time at all because of the humidity I'll just have a poof ball on my head!  I used to use a ton of hairspray to hold the curls.  That worked well when my hair was very short but that hasn't really worked too well as I've let my TWA grow out some (approx 4-6 inches).  This does a much better job of holding the curls with my additional length.  I guess because this can be applied from the roots to the ends.  I applied it to my hair soaking wet right out of the shower.  I immediately noticed a positive difference.  I imagine like any gel type product, the more you use the crunchier your hair will be.  There is a feel of a product that is made to hold or set your hair but my hair was not too crunchy for me.  I'm not sure if I'll even need it during the winter months but I'm definitely using it daily during the summer!  I co-wash and go each morning so I have no idea how long it would last or no idea about buildup issues.  I start fresh with my hair each morning and consequently use a lot of product, so the price is definitely right!

column14:
This was such a wonderful product, I’ll have to admit that I was a bit skeptical about putting this mask on my face. I’ve been swimming a lot in the pool, and also tanning outside lately. My skin has felt very dry lately, so I thought that I would give this a try. I’m at the age where I am really starting to think about wrinkle prevention, and skin hydration. Many of my friends go to day spas for expensive treatments, but I do not want to spend $100s of dollars on facials like they do.

The mask is literally a piece of lace that is “face shaped”, for lack of a better description. It’s very sturdy, and doesn’t break. The mask fit comfortably on my face, and stayed in place with no issues. There are loops that can be used to go around your ears if you want to do that, I guess so you can move around or treat the skin behind your ears. I just sat it on my face while I relaxed and watched TV, so I didn’t use the ear loops. There’s a lot of the treatment in the lace, and you can feel it working on your face. It smells great. My skin feels very soft after using the mask. It says to use it 2 to 3 times a week, I am going to use it again in a few days, and start incorporating this into my skin care regimen.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column14:
I received the Braun Series 9 9090cc Electric Shaver with Cleaning Center as part of a promotion from the brand.
I was always skeptical of using shaving machines on my face. I have tried several that have not come close to using an actual razor. I’m the type of guy that grows a beard over night and in a weekend I can have a full beard. All my friends say I’m amazing at growing facial hair. How do you keep it tamed? I must say, I buy razor blades after razor blades which get very expensive. I usually go through one or two blades a week. I have very coarse hair that somehow destroys blades.
After opening the Braun Series 9090 I was impressed with the packing and style of the machine. It was very compact, fit well in my hand and also came with a travel case. On my first try the Braun Series 9090 was simple to use and maneuvered around my face well. For the true test the Braun Series 9090 has converted me into a true believer that it can cut my facial hairs just as good as any razor blades can. I must say it left my skin feeling smooth with no stubs. I was amazed that it did not pull on my hair or irritate my skin. After using the Braun Series 9090 my face felt just as soft as baby’s skin. I’m looking forward to many skin close shaves to come using the Braun Series 9090.

column6: Nano Ionic Facial Steamer | Personal Facial Sauna SPA System - Skin Care Beauty Steamer For Home - Portable Facial Steamer For Skin Care, Acne & Black Head
column13: MIRA Nano Ionic Facial Steamer Helps Open Up My Clogged Pores And Makes My Skin Feel Alive!
column14:
This MIRA Nano Ionic Facial Steamer is an absolute wonderful beauty tool! I have clogged pores and this steamer literally opens them up and makes my face feel so much more alive! This steamer is very relaxing especially since the steamer isn't loud. It's very easy to operate since it plugs into a wall outlet,pour purified or distilled water into the tank which is in the back of the steamer,flip the switch to on, and you're spa steamer is up and running. I love the way this steamer cleans my skin which is so much easier then a harsh towel. I really like that this steamer is extremely lightweight yet sturdy at the same time so you don't have to worry about having problems moving it/carrying it around yet it won't fall over. it's not overly big either so it won't take up too much room. The flow of steam is very good as it's not too light yet not overly powerful. I would definitely recommend this MIRA Nano Ionic Facial Steamer!

column6: Emu Oil Pure Premium Golden Powerful Skin and Hair Moisturizer - 8 fl.oz.
column13: Miracle in a bottle for health and beauty, for people and pets
column14:
Emu oil is a miracle. I’ve been using it since 1996 when I first discovered it. Emu oil is fat rendered from the emu bird. It is liquid at room temperature and remains stable (not rancid) for very many months and even a few years.
As for all the health benefits and how I use it, there are many uses for PEOPLE.
• It's known to heal burns and dramatically accelerate healing, provide soothing relief, and improve scaring. Emus are native to Australia, as I understand it, and Aborigines use emu oil specifically for healing, especially for burns. Clinical studies of burn victims, again as I understand it, have shown how dramatic emu oil is to rapid healing.
• I use emu oil after doing my own chemical peel, which I tend to do strong (called medium) chemical peels at home with serious peeling, swelling, bruising. It's the absolute best for healing most quickly - better than coconut, olive, and other nut and seed oils - which are all excellent healing oils.
• Emu oil is known for increasing the efficacy of other chemicals used with it, so it is considered a ‘carrier oil' like almond oil is. That means when I apply copper serum to my skin first and then emu oil; it amplifies the benefits of the serum. This is especially helpful after my chemical peel when I apply copper serum, it stings and emu oil soothes my inflamed skin immediately and provides soothing for hours after application. Emu oil is supposed to be excellent when combining with arthritis rubs because it's such excellent carrier oil.
• Because of its benefit of a carrier oil and it's so emollient - its consistency is slippery and viscous - emu oil is amazing to rub out existing bruises and swelling that leads to bruising. I'm a bleeder and a bruiser. It's bad. When I do paralytics, I'll rub in the emu oil where I had the injections as a preventative measure so I can keep my secret (and tell the world on Amazon. So much for discretion!) As for fillers, also use emu oil on the entire area where the filler is injected. Emu oil is perfect for doing the deep rubbing and massaging necessary to make the filler supple, soothe the swelling, prevents worse bruising, and integrate the filler into its area.
• Apply emu oil to rashes for quick healing and soothing. It is especially helpful with eczema, psoriasis, shingles, and herpes outbreaks. It helps to break open the blisters with an antiseptic like alcohol, hydrogen peroxide, or witch hazel. Rashes that are contagious spread through the liquid in the blisters when they break. This is how rashes spread on yourself (like from mouth to genitals and vice versa for herpes) and from different places on your body (like eczema). For the love of God, check with your doctor if you have something as painful as shingles. I recommend this as a home remedy, but there is no substitute for medical intervention when you need massive doses of medicine just to get by.
• Emu oil is to be antibacterial, antiviral, anti-fungal, and anti-inflammatory. This is also true of very many nut and seed oils like coconut, almond, olive, and so on. So apply emu oil to cleansed cuts, scrapes, scabs, scars, boo boos, ouchies.
• Emu oil helps a ton with insect bites. I overreact to mosquito bites where it swells to a quarter size wheal. It's worse on my feet and ankles where multiple bites swell that appendage. Using my mom's trick to eliminate the itch and sting, apply ammonia or Windex that contains ammonia to the bite sight. It then develops a bubble of water that becomes salt, which you just brush off. (How does this work? Bug bites are acidic and ammonia is base. Adding an acid to a base creates water and salt - basic stoichiometry in chemistry! Bug bite acids are the same 'strength' as vinegar (acetic acid), and an equivalent 'strength' base is ammonia. A much stronger base is bleach, which I would probably use to neutralize a scorpion sting - God help me.)
• Massaging emu oil into the scalp stimulates hair growth andtreats dandruff. It's great to treat dry, brittle hair. You can sleep with emu oil on your head and face and it won't permanently stain your sheets in that it washes out completely and easily. That's true of all natural oils: animal fats, vegetables and nut/seed oils. Know that synthetic oils don't wash out, like mineral oil or Vaseline that's petroleum based. I'm reminded of the eternal clothing stains when black men enjoyed the Jeri Curl of the late, great eighties.
• It is an amazing lubricant for your nether regions. Instead of KY, use emu oil. It’s longer lasting, doesn’t dry out, you can eat it (tastes like chicken!), and it causes no infections the way synthetic oils can. You can also use emu oil (and coconut oil) to lubricate devices inserted into uncomfortable spots.
• Chewing on hangnails is huge source of illness from infection. I know because I do it to myself all the time. It's compulsive. But if your immunity is compromised, an infected hangnail could cause serious problems or worsen existing ones. Yipes. To treat it, rub emu oil all over your hands, drenching the cuticles. Then wear nifty little cotton gloves to keep them covered. I've used a pair of white cotton sox when I didn't have those nifty little gloves.
• Same treatment goes for your feet, especially if you have those big, thick, nasty callouses and cracked dry beds for the soles of your feet. Try and remove the callous to the extent desired or possible, then slather on emu oil and slip on your socks, then wear your slippers if walking around (or you might leave footprints).
As for all the benefits of emu oil for PETS, they are also many.
• I feed my new little rescue puppy emu oil along with his raw food diet many times throughout the day. After we rescued him, we realized that he was starving and extremely thirsty. To build his health and help him gain weight – he is skin and bones, you can see his little ribs and he has a really big hollow between his ribs and hips– I load up his frequent meals with decent doses of emu oil (and salmon oil, coconut oil, olive oil – no walnut or macadamia oil because that is toxic to dogs).
• Emu oil is wonderful to rub on your dog or cat’s skin and fur. My other dog, also a rescue with health and especially immunity issues – that’s how we discovered the raw food diet by Darwin’s and The Honest Kitchen), developed a painful and itchy rash on her belly down to her lower legs. She used to bite herself incessantly and go crazy. I rubbed her belly and all along her legs with a slathering of emu oil. It was so soothing and helped resolved the problem.
• If a food safe to eat, then it is safe to apply to skin. Same for pets as for people, but so many ‘people things’ can kill or harm dogs and cats. So having the peace of mind of applying emu oil to their aggravated skin, knowing that they will lick it off and that it is safe and healthy, is a wonderful thing. When they lick it off, keep reapplying it! It’s good for them.

column13: I guess I'm the odd one out -- not a successful experience.
column14: After reading the myriad great reviews I was really excited and hopeful about trying these products (I purchased a serum and cleanser as well), but unfortunately they weren't for me. I liked the idea of a really powerful, all natural and almost all organic line, but from the day I started using these products my skin became very dry, I broke out, and developed these random patches of scaly, tiny bumps on my face. I stuck with it for about 2 weeks hoping it was just a transitionary thing, but eventually I couldn't stand what was happening to my skin. Switched back to a tried and true line (I've learned my lesson) and my skin is already looking better after 1 night, and on the road to recovery. If the the switch didn't make it so drastically clear that the Oz Natural products were doing my skin a disservice, I may have thought, "Hey, maybe these just aren't the best products for me." However, I've tried other products that maybe didn't transform my skin and I didn't necessarily *love*, but none have actually made my skin worse. Not to say that these products don't work for others, but I guess you have to balance out the thousands of success stories with at least one unsuccessful one :/

column6: Skinceuticals Retinol 1 Maximum Strength Refining Night Cream, 1 Fluid Ounce
column13: You're skin's supposed to peel at first
column14: I see so many people here saying they stopped using this or only use this once a week because of the peeling. I investigated this and it's supposed to happen. It's called retinization, where your skin adjusts to using it and unfortunately you have to go through it to get results. Still follow directions (start with the milder strength, only use once every 2-3 days, work up to daily, etc) but your skin's going to be sensitive and/or peel for a while. Everything I've reads says if you only use it weekly to avoid this, you are not going to get the benefit of retinol. I backed off using any other product with "actives" and extra exfoliation during the adjustment period, which took weeks but I feel has been worth it.

column13: Bold and Charming Coffee Essential Oil!
column14:
I have not been disappointed with any Plant Therapy Essential Oils. I love this coffee product! I read both positive and negative reviews before buying and was a little worried what this would smell like due to negative posts!

I love it and actually as an avid essential oil fan I have found my newest favorite blend to diffuse: Patchouli and Coffee! Since Patchouli is a stronger scent I use 3 drops Patchouli and 7 drops Coffee and let it fill my home with a warm and inviting scent. I adore the smell; so welcoming and not too girly or manly. Give it a try!

My only wish is that all companies switched their tops to child resistant but that's just because I fear I will forget and leave one out and a curious child will get into it, never happened but can't help but think of this as a plus to an essential oil company!

This is a pure, rich, and charming scent of coffee. I have learned that coffee is a good antioxidant, great for making cosmetics, wonderful with respiratory issues such as asthma and bronchitis, and even a treatment for whooping cough. Of course any of these benefits needs to be carefully read and looked at before just making a DIY at home without any knowledge but it's good to know just how many different beneficial properties this oil has.

I was given a discount due to the company changing labels and clearing old label inventory but felt it would be great to leave an honest review for those like me that are looking for reliable companies to buy my oils from. I love Plant Therapy and couldn't be more pleased with a company that has service and products! Also love the added touch of the oil label on the cap; makes grabbing what you need faster and easier.

column6: Eye Primer/Neutral
column14:
IT WORKS. I had no idea a primer could grab so much powder! I got it for eyeliner pencil that kept disappearing, and it helps everything stay put. It doesn't have a lot of drag when going on. Since it starts creamy I've had to set it with powder to avoid creasing, but be careful! You only need the smallest amount and it will take layers of powder, be careful not to put too much eye shadow on because this will grab it. This is good if you want to cover up the light tint completely with a color. I'd suggest carefully applying it just exactly where you apply your eye shadow.

I also tried it under my eyes and in the inner corners to enhance concealer. It certainly works and my dark circles were covered all day. But the primer, concealer and powder combo brought out little eye wrinkles (I used it with Lancome concealer and Tarte Smooth Operator face powder).

Color: Despite the photo looking flesh toned, this does look almost white going on. I have very fair skin and wear physical sunscreens that leave me even whiter, but it was still too light. That said, you don't need much. A tiny bit applied smoothly is not very visible. I do apply it before anything else to blend or cover with sunscreen or foundation.The reason for this is partly because it has mineral sunscreen as an ingredient (titanium dioxide). Which is a bonus if you don't want eye wrinkles long term.

Compared: I also bought the elf eye primer at the same time and this is superior. Gabriel primer takes less and has an even, smooth consistency. Again, it holds a lot of powder too.

Sensitivity: I have very sensitive eyes, they are often itchy and irritated even if I haven't worn makeup for weeks. So all eye makeup is a bit irritating, but this primer doesn't cause itching or burning or swelling- nothing that I don't experience with all other makeup. My eye makeup stays on better, but it does require a make-up remover with this primer.

Gabriel line: New favorite! It's natural, non-toxic, non-irritating. The Gabriel liquid foundation has really impressed me too. Gabriel foundation is moisturizing, it has some sun protection, and the color is really amazing; warm and pigmented, but not yellow like so many other natural foundations.e! column6: Bremenn Hylexin For Serious Dark Circles .5 oz Boxed
column13: Beware of Fakes, Knock-Offs, and Immitations
column14:
I have ordered this product directly from the manufacturer in the past, and to be fair, the product I received directly from Bremenn Research Labs does help with dark circles. I believe it is more of a cosmetic affect than anything because the dark circles return when I wash my face at the end of the day, but there has been a slight permanent improvement and either way, the darkness was significantly reduced.

I recently ordered this product through Amazon instead of Bremenn and I believe what I received was a fake. First of all, the original shrink wrap had been removed and then the box was re-packaged with a sample packet of another product enclosed under new, and somewhat less professional-looking shrink wrap. That didn't bother me too much except when I opened the box, the tip of the tube had been snipped off and the product was easily dispensed. This has never been the case when I received the product directly from the manufacturer. I returned that tube thinking it was a one-time issue and received a replacement in exactly the same condition, both with respect to the sample/shrink wrap and the open tube.

At this point I contacted the manufacturer to verify that the product they sold was completely sealed and required the tip of the tube to be snipped off in order to dispense the contents. They verified that this was the case and stated that they could not guarantee the quality or authenticity of the product if it were not in the original shrink wrap, or arrived already opened.

I suppose the fact that the product sells on Amazon for almost half the price of what the manufacturer sells it for should have been a tip-off, but I put my trust in Amazon and ordered it despite my nagging doubts. I returned the second tube I received as a replacement and never tried either to see if they compared to what I know to be the genuine product, but I'm not interested in experimenting if I can't be assured that the product is the real thing, not to mention the question of why it was opened and then re-sealed before sale. Your experience my differ, but beware and draw your own conclusions accordingly.

(Please note that any damage to the shrink wrap in the attached picture was caused during opening. Otherwise, the product was received exactly as described)., not to mention the question of why it was opened and then re-sealed before sale. Your experience my differ, but beware and draw your own conclusions accordingly.

column13: Nice Addition to Skin Care Routine!
column14:
I got these masks to try out because I am always looking for a refreshing way to treat my skin and relax. I have adult acne, and I have a regimen that I religiously follow, but in the summer months, that regimen can end up making my face feel dry. I’ve heard that sea water treatments are really good for hydration, so I decided to try this mask. The product has instructions in English, but it’s fairly straight forward, open the bag, remove the mask, and put it on your face. The mask is thin, and sticks to your face very easily. The smell is very pleasant. I left it on my face for 20 minutes, during which time, it did not slip off, and stayed comfortably in place. As per the instructions, after I removed the mask, I massaged my face. The instructions say that there is no need to rinse after, but I did and followed up with other products in my facial routine.
My skin feels hydrated, and smooth. I will definitely add this product to my regular routine.

column13: Great product, best company....MADE IN USA
column14:
I usually don't write reviews, but I feel I have to share my experience with Island Deodorant. I have been a loyal customer first to the product for how well it performs day after day working often in the hot Floridian sun. I love the fact that it has completely natural ingredients and it is made in Florida instead of China.
Recently I received a jar that it did not meet my usual expectation and since the owner of Island Deodorant always follows up with her customers, I decided to reach out to her. I would like to say that she has provided me with the best customer care service that I have ever experienced. She did not just explain to me what I have to do to fix the problem with the product, but also that in case the products did still not meet my expectation she would replace it. This might sounds to you as a regular warranty call, but I have to assure you that she has been in complete contact with me throughout the process and when at the end I still had to replace it, no questions asked, she sent me the replacement right away.
At the end of all this I'm not only happy with the product, company but the customer service as well and they have me as a lifelong customer. I'm recommending this product to my family and friends as well. Thank you Jennifer for your help and your great products.

column6: Palmer's Cocoa Butter Formula Swivel Stick, 0.5 Ounce
column13: I've used this stick for 10 years--it's THE BEST
column14:
I've been using this cocoa butter stick for 10 years. I first found them when I was in high school and was made fun of because it looked like I was using a glue stick on my lips, so yes it is huge but I LOVE that about it. It's so much easier to find in my bag.

I use this on my lips every single night before bed and that stick lasts about 6 months, as does the one I keep in my purse to use when I go out--and this is applying it liberally. It feels so amazing on my lips with no nasty taste (like some sticks I've used before). There's no "fun flavor" for anyone who likes that kind of thing. I don't, so this is perfect. My lips are immediately softer and, if I don't use it for a while during the day and get chapped lips, it only takes a day of using it regularly to get them back to normal. But really, I don't ever have an issue with chapped lips because of this stick.

The only problem I ever found was not being able to find them. I'd randomly find them at a store (and I look at pretty much every store) and buy in bulk. They're usually about $4-5 at the store, so when I found these on Amazon last night I immediately bought them! I can't even express my excitement at knowing I can easily buy these when I need them. I have other sticks around the house now, because I haven't found this stick anywhere for months, and I plan to toss them all.

column6: Reusable Premium Cosmetic Makeup Sponge Egg Drop Applicator Smooth Puff Foundation Blender for Beauty by JGOB
column13: This make up beauty blending sponge is actually worth the money because of the amazing qualities and capabilities it has
column14:
Neon Green Applicator Makeup Puff Blender Sponge for Beauty by JGOB https://www.amazon.com/dp/B011B25WIK/ref=cm_sw_r_awd_eN6YvbS3BAQXK

Okay so these little make up sponges have been extremely popular lately because celebrities have been using them for several different reasons. This make up beauty blending sponge is actually worth the money because of the amazing qualities and capabilities it has.

There are definitely some off brand beauty blenders with this being one of them, but with that being said, it still works exactly like a beauty blender and does the same thing. I love the color, neon green, that I recieved.

My experience with this make up applicator sponge was perfect. You have to soak the sponge in water before you use it and then dry it off with a napkin to get the water out. The key to these things is to make sure the sponge is moist so that way your make up doesn't just soak up into the sponge and your make up sits on top and you really get more make up than you normally would. This sponge doesn't waste your make up like a regular sponge would. The way my make up turned out was absolutely flawless like I had just came out of the beauty shop every time I used it.

The only thing I was concerned about was keeping the sponge clean of all my make up to keep its neon green color of all and also to keep out all of the excess make up that doesn't need to be on there for the next time you use it. I know there is some cleaning soap you can purchase but since I do not have any I just cleaned it with some dish soap for about five minutes and it was as good as new!

I truly love this product because it is very bouncy on my skin, moves my make up flawlessly, and leaves no make up left behind. It is definitely something to keep in your make up bag because it is the greatest make up applicator to use. You can also use this sponge for contouring, highlighting, and also dry powders, just make sure the sponge is moist when your use it. I would also change it out about every three months and get a new one, like you would any make up applicator.

column6: Blackheads & Pimples Remover Tools with Tweezers & Manicure Set By Marks Gouger; Professional Skin Care Comedone Extractors for Pimples, Whiteheads, Zits, Blemishes
column14:
What a terrific set for a fair price. I've paid more than this just for a good pair of tweezers, so I thought for sure the instruments wouldn't be of any decent quality. I was so happy to be wrong. The tweezers provided compare with my Tweezerman Slant, which costs more than the kit. The instruments are all surgical grade stainless steel and can be cleaned with rubbing alcohol in between uses.

The case itself is a hard shell covered with leather, with a nice button to open it. Perfect for travel or just for storage in a drawer-- I have often had trouble keeping track of where I put my instruments, so this solves that problem nicely.

In short, I'm really impressed by the quality here. The only thing it lacks is in-depth instruction on how to use the tools, but you can find that on YouTube. I had never used two of the skin extractor types, so I wasn't sure under what circumstances to use each one (for blackheads and whiteheads). It would have been nice to include more of a booklet to explain this.

I received this set for review.

column6: FOOT SENSE All Natural Smelly Foot & Shoe Powder - 3.5 Oz/100 Grams - Foot Odor Eliminator lasts up to 6 months. Safely kills bacteria. Natural formula for smelly shoes and stinky feet. Safe & natural. Protects disinfects and deodorizes.
column13: Apparently I have swamp feet..nope, HAD
column14:
Not just swamp feet, but creature from the blue lagoon swamp feet. Since I'm a nurse, I'm on my feet and booking it 12+ hours a day. I also live in tennis shoes. My tennis shoes are almost a year old, and I walk 2 to 5 miles a day, per fitbit.

Odor eliminating foot powder has been a staple for a long time. Put in before work. Put in after work. Wipe down feet with alcohol after work. We joke at work about stinky feet. It's part if life, right?

Wrong! Not anymore! I bought this as part of the Amazon Day Sale (please, stop applauding, everyone knows it was awesome). And, as per reviews, I used it once, and, still a smell in the shoes. Ok, no miracle. Day two, full day. Feet feel and smell better. Shoes smell 60% better. Sigh. And on it went. My feet smelled way, way better
Basically, no smell at the end of a long day. My shoes had a drastic improvement, but, still the odor persisted. The company emailed me to ask about the product, and I told them that it was working, but, I was waiting on a cure. They were very supportive, encouraged me to continue using the product and sent me more product so that I could continue to use it daily until I achieved a cure. This really impressed me. Especially since I told them that I really felt that I was the issue, or at least my shoes.

After two weeks of use, my feet and shoes are odor free. I'm off to deodorize the rest of my family, which is moving along rapidly. Lol. You really can't go wrong with this company. They truly stand behind their product. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND !!!

column13: Natural, mild, and effective spot treatment
column14:
This is a really effective spot treatment and is mild enough to use on sensitive skin. My skin is very sensitive and I am able to use this spot treatment morning and night without any ill effects. Within one day it helps to reduce the inflammation and redness of acne. I let my sister use it and she was so impressed she bought some of her own. I really appreciate that the salicylic acid in this product comes from willow bark. However I am an even bigger fan of some of the "inactive" ingredients, especially calendula oil. Calendula flowers have natural antibacterial and anti-inflammatory properties. This herb also stimulates the production of collagen which minimizes scarring and helps to brighten skin. Basically its perfect for acne. :)

If you have any questions, feel free to ask them in the comments and I will do my best to answer them based on my experience.

column14: It's nice. It works well. The picture is misleading. I'm a little frustrated in how some sellers, such as this one, represent their products in pictures. They show three in the main picture that comes up first. If they are only going to ship one, then the primary picture should show one. The description does say "horn", not "horns". So if carefully read, then you will realize you are getting only one, but the picture in my opinion NEEDS to show exactly what you are getting, which is only one. So, four stars for the product, and two stars for the picture averages out to three stars. I think Amazon needs to address this issue with sellers as well. Don't show multiple items in the primary picture if you only intend to ship one unit. They may not have intended to mislead, but it did and it will happen again if pictures like this are shown.

column6: InstaSkincare Blackhead and Blemish Remover Tool Kit - Esthetician Skin Care Set for Facial Acne - Easily Cure Pimples, Blackheads, Comedones, Acne, and Facial Impurities
column13: Great product for the price, durable and well made.
column14:
Great value set and will do exactly what it is supposed to do. 100% stainless steel, easy to clean an sanitize. The case is a black leather like material with a red velvet type material liner. Each tool is double ended and very durable, and well made. Considering if you bought each tool separate with no case, they are between 5-18 bucks or so each and some are cheaply made, (One I got at Walmart broke the first time I used it, the loop just fell out of the handle). These are made well and will not fall apart. I would recommend this set based on the above information.

The reason I only gave it 4 stars is this, easily fixed, by me after I received it already. First the lancet tool was dull, really dull, no way was that popping a pimple. Husband fixed it right up easily with a small grinder and sharpened it. Second mine had tool residue all over them from the tool work shaping them and putting them together. It was a black, silver dust I though at first was dirt gathered in the pattern of the handles and around where the wires and loops are attached to the handles. I started to wash them and noticed I got a small splinter, metal splinter in my finger. I then looked very close and took a sharp knife and scraped this off a spot and rubbed it in between my fingers and yes it was all tiny tiny pieces of metal dust/shavings. It rinsed off with water....... I went ahead and washed them good and dipped in alcohol before first use. They recommend you to sanitize them before first use anyway of course. So after they were washed and hubby sharpened the lancet took, they are perfect............ especially for the price they are well worth the money.

column6: Philips Sonicare for Kids Connected Sonic Electric Rechargeable Toothbrush
column14:
My daughter is 3 years old and the dentist is already "watching" 4 of her teeth (the ones all the way in the back). I knew we had to get more serious about brushing. I mean, we were already brushing, but the focus wasn't on being thorough.

While I was excited to give this brush and the app a try, I had two concerns. First, that it would be too intense for her, and Second, that the app would be too complex. I was happily surprised that neither is an issue. Her first reaction was to giggle at the vibrations, and the app is simple and intuitive enough, that she had no problem following. That said, I think it's also not too babyish for a child quite a few years older than her either.

So overall this brush is a big hit with my 3 year old. We don't bring out the iPad each time because it is a hassle sometimes, but another great thing is that her brushing time is recorded and recognized the next time we open the app, even if we weren't using it at the time. And that's great, because my daughter would otherwise insist on using the iPad every single time she brushed.

column6: Retseliney Acne-Treatment Oil-Control Moisturizer Cream with 2% Salicylic Acid and Vitamin C
column14:
This skin treatment is a white lotion with a mild fragrance mostly of clove oil. It disappears when applied to the skin and eliminates any oily sheen.

It is a good alternative to harsh acne treatments and is effective when used on a regular basis. It will not only treat mild cases of acne, but will also help clear blackheads and whiteheads and generally freshen the appearance of the skin. It is also helpful for adults who have oily complexions or an occasional blemish.

The formula uses mostly botanical ingredients to unclog pores, gently exfoliate, and moisturize and protect the skin to prevent dryness. Even the active ingredient against acne, salicylic acid, is derived from willow bark.

A small drop should be applied after thoroughly washing the skin and patting it dry. The 2 oz. or 60 ml bottle has a pump cap that dispenses just the right amount.

Retseliney provided a bottle for evaluation and review.

column6: Revision Skincare Nectifirm, 1.7 oz
column14:
I had Ulthera done on my neck area a few months ago (49 yrs old with good skin, often mistaken for late 30s). While i got nice results under the chin and a tighter jawline, my neck skin had a reaction to the procedure. I have a few wrinkle like lines on my neck (same places where welts were - they are not platisma bands) and skin looks blotchy in places. Fortuntately its not overly noticeable. My Dr told me to use nectifirm. I bought some on "the bay" as a bunch of sample tubes offered by someone there were cheaper than a jar, and much cheaper than at the Drs office.

i do not see any difference in my skin and have started to use bio oil instead and am looking into DMAE and MSM lotions, hoping they will work better (and they are cheaper, although I would have kept buying this regardless of price had it worked). Also the nectifirm has a fairly strong perfume scent. Not unpleasant, but i again not what i want to use on sensitive skin. I may use the remainder of it on the back of my hands and see if that helps my hand skin look better.

column6: Cetaphil Cetaphil Restoraderm Skin Restoring Body Lotion
column13: Can't recommend - caused new breakouts on my hands
column14:
I tried Cetaphil Restoraderm Eczema Calming Body Moisturizer for dishidrotic eczema on my hands, which causes periodic breakouts (small itchy, weeping bumps) followed by extremely dry, cracked, and peeling skin.

My eczema was mostly confined to the palm side of my fingers, but I made the mistake of applying the Restoraderm product to both the palms and backs of my hands. As a result, the backs of my hands (which previously were NOT affected) broke out in a red rash. Discontinued the product immediately, and after some recovery time the backs of my hands are mostly normal again. Based on all the good reviews it sounds like this product works well for many people, but beware - a number of people appear to be very sensitive to it. If you must try this product, spot test it for a couple of days first to be sure your skin won't react.

I have had much better luck with a product called Triple Cream Severe Dry Skin/Eczema Care. It is greasy for sure, but if you apply a little bit all day long, and more at night (ideally without covering), it slowly improves the dryness. In my case the Triple Cream did not seem to cause any additional skin reactions. The skin on the palm side of my fingers still gets dry, but the peeling and cracking issues are greatly improved.

column6: Philips Satinelle Essential HP6401, Compact Hair Removal Epilator
column14:
My mom warned me about her adventure with the original EpiLady, and I listened. I threw caution to the wind and bought this guy. Now, I have a pretty good pain tolerance, but this was different. Yes, it was painful... but not like any pain I've ever felt. It felt like needles sticking into the skin (I don't have tattoos, so I'm not sure if this is the best thing to compare it to... but it's what I imagine it feels like). The shin was the worst part... holy cow that's sensitive! I made it through, and it didn't take too long. All of the hair was not grabbed, as some was too short. I'll go back again in a few days for round #2. I did epilate my underarms... I have waxed them before, but thought this would take care of that problem, at least a little. The underarm was not bad, honestly. It took some maneuvering to get my skin taut, but I figured it out :)
I don't have any complaints so far... and I'll edit this later, if need be. BTW, the cord is really long, so it shouldn't be a turn-off if you are looking at this one, versus a cordless, more expensive epilator.

***I will say, you should follow the instructions and do this at night. I didn't, and I ended up with little red bumps and larger hair follicle holes (I have no clue what the actual name is, lol). Next time I will do this at night, but I had just received it in the mail and lack impulse control.

column13: especially good in combination with a detangling spray; works for very long hair
column14:
This is a pretty good detangling brush. It has bristles at three different heights (they're nylon, I think, but without large beads/balls at the ends like some detanglihg brushes). It's very lightweight, as well.

I have waist-length hair that tends to get a bit tangled. After towel-drying my hair most of the way, I spray it with detangling spray (my favorite right now is \\\It's a 10\\\\\" Miracle Leave-In Treatment). Then I use a detangling brush to work the product through my hair and to detangle (followed by air-drying). This brush was quite effective at detangling without a lot of pulling or pain, and I was done quickly.

I also used this in the morning just to brush my (mostly air-dried) hair. It was pretty good at that, as well. I got a bit of tugging/pulling at the ends, but nothing I couldn't handle. My old brush would have done the same.

I tend not to use the handle for this brush but instead just to grip the back of the part the bristles are attached to. It's curved but easy to hold on to. (I do sometimes use the handle when brushing out my ends.)

Overall, a good brush at a competitive price. It appears to be good quality, as well (haven't lost any bristles yet and hasn't pulled out a lot of hair). There was no plastic or chemical smell when I opened the box, either (although the box was a bit damaged in transit).

Product provided by the seller for evaluation purposes."

column6: Bdellium Tools Professional Makeup Brush Green Bambu Series Mineral 5pc. Brush Set
column14:
I really like these brushes so far. I bought this set at the same time I bought the mineral set and the smoky eye set, plus a few individuals. I would say that the ones in this set are the ones I use the most.

959 - I love this one for blush. It took me a long time to find a blush brush that was right for me, but this one is finally it. I use it every day now, and even bought another one since from RealTechniques but I went back to this one again. I don't know if it was intended for blush, but hey, who cares :) I like to use it in a dotting motion to pack the color onto the outer apples, and then blend it up - it really works well.
942 - I like this one for applying my highlighter to the upper cheekbones. I also got the fan brush separately but I like this one more.
934 - I can't really find a use for this one, personally. This one just sits in the bag for now.
787 - I like this one also for highlighter, or for any other blending. I even used this for blending on my eyes when I'm doing an all-over color (it's kind of big for detailed blending). Very soft and useful though.
778 - I also used this for all-over color on the eyes, and also for concealer. I admit this isn't my most-used brush, but it's still a nice one.

All of these are high quality, and I've already washed them 4 times or so and there hasn't even one strand of shedding. I'll buy more, but I'm still looking for my magic set. Frankly I wish I had just bought all the individual ones I needed instead of getting sets.

column6: Plus White Bleach Whitening Gel, 5 Minute, Original Flavor, 2 oz.
column13: Amazing but buy the mouth guard
column14:
It would be 5 stars except I think they should tell you to use this with a mouth guard only. I know the directions said to wipe it off your gums but how can you keep your lips away from your teeth for 5 minutes without using a mouth guard? I used it for 5 minutes and it made my lip pretty raw. So I can only imagine if you leave it on for 15 minutes without a mouth guard...yikes.

BUT it works amazing. I noticed whiter teeth after 5 minutes, just using it the first time. I know this sounds impossible. When I read other people's reviews who said the same thing, I didn't believe it. But it does work...just think about buying the mouth guard. I have mine on order.

column6: NIVEA Men Sensitive Shaving Gel, 7 Ounce Parent
column14:
This is by far the best shaving cream out there. And, it's been the best since Aveeno reformulated their oatmeal gel, which is no longer very good. But this is awesome! I've tried about forty different shaving gels, looking for the best one, and believe me, this is it! It's a very thick gel that turns into a gel-like foam. It's so much thicker and better than Barbasol, that I was reluctant to say that the gel foams. It does, but still in a very thick way. That's super important for shaving, since this thick foam holds in a lot of moisture, which makes it the perfect shave gel.

And, it lasts for a long time. They cram a lot of this into a small container.

I use this every day to shave with. It gives a very close shave without razorburn. It's awesome, and I highly recommend it.

column6: Pure Body Naturals – Vitamin C Toner - 4 Fl 0z
column13: Great product, excellent for combination skin. Please read instructions, not to be sprayed directly to face!
column14:
This is a great product. It has a pleasant smell, but I personally prefer scent-free products. I did not read the instructions too carefully, so I sprayed it on my face (it says to spray on a cotton ball.) I was a little concerned about spraying anything in my face, as my eyes are sensitive (of course, I closed my eyes.) But that was user error (however, after reading some other reviews, it seems like most people are spraying it directly to the face, so I'm not alone.

As it dried, which does quickly, it does leave the skin feeling soft and smooth. I have combination skin, but T-zone tends to get quite oily, and the rest, quite dry! So it is a challenge to find products that target my bi-polar skin!
This was not greasy, but was moisturizing, so for me it worked great for both zones/areas in my face. It is a generous amount, the bottle is quite big, and for the small amount you use, it should last a long time. It was also carefully wrapped, which is good. It comes with the spray adapter separately, so it is optional (and since you are supposed to use a cotton ball or a pad, so it's your call, really.)

My only suggestion to the manufacturer is to make the straw smaller! At least the one I received, it was too long, It almost curled back up (it formed a letter J shape inside the bottle). So it was at least an inch (or a little more) longer than what it needs to be.

column6: PURA D'OR Hair Loss Prevention Premium Organic Argan Oil Shampoo,16 Fluid Ounce (Packaging may vary)
column13: Nice Product, subjective results, Definitely well worth a try!
column14:
I bought this shampoo when i was looking for chemical free hair products. I was moved by all those positive reviews and decided to give this a try.
The Shampoo comes in, exactly as pictured. After using this for a while now, i do feel that my hair has become healthier than before.
I could not say that there is a reduction in hair loss, it remains the same, no more no less. However i could see new tiny hairs around my forehead area and that is interesting. I don't have any other hair issue and i tried this shampoo only to get rid of the ones with harsh chemicals.
This has a mild fragrance which is not the best but definitely acceptable.

1. This product claims to prevent hair loss, which may work in many, but in my case i am waiting to see the results.
2. Shampoo claims to support healthy hair growth and yes, i have seen the results myself.
3. Best part is that you get the satisfaction that you use the shampoo that is chemical-free and is also good for your hair.
4. Price, i feel this is little overpriced comparing the long time it takes to give you actual results.

Overall, this is a nice product and definitely well worth a try if you are suffering from serious hair issues.
This has definitely helped in maintaining healthier hair. I will continue buying this product, and i hope to see changes in the hair loss pattern soon.
The review shall be updated again later.

column14:
There are two unique feature sof this serum compared to other C serums, and one notable feature about the packaging here compared to most other C serums out there:

Serum:
-It has a scent that I would say is something like rose-hips or some variation of floral. It only lasts a couple moments, but was a surprise to me at first.
-It is a bit more of a gel consistency than a watery liquid. This really allows to manage application in a controlled way, and I far prefer this consistency

Bottle:
-It has a pump, which is SO much better and easier than the eye droppers! Very pleased about this!

At least at the time I purchased it, it was a very good value and I've had it function just as well as all other C serums that I've used. No concerns recommending this one, with those particular unique features.

I started using C serum a year or more ago and it helped me fade away summer freckles. I am now in a daily maintenance mode now and use it daily.

column6: Royal Wood Stick Cotton Swabs 1 Box - 300 Count
column14:
Yes it's hard to go back to paper shaft or plastic shaft cotton swabs after one has experienced the really "firm control" of good quality wood shafts.
But just to cut to the chase.. NO wood stick cotton swabs of the standard 3" or so length, that are available on the market today, are anywhere near as good as the old Q-tips brand that were sadly discontinued a decade ago or so. Those were of consistent quality with thick sticks and plenty of cotton, and excellent quality control. That era is OVER. That being said, I tried all the other brands I could find and these are the best of whats currently available. They have enough cotton to not let the shaft break through and scratch or cut your ear, probably about 2/3 of what Q-tips had, but enough to do the job in pretty deep without being scary. The shafts are inconsistent as to thickness, and wood grain direction, so yes, a certain amount of them break, generally in the middle, usually at first flex, and it's not a big deal, they don't get stuck in your ear or anything. All current brands have this issue.. with these, you can tell when you get a thinnish one.. and relatively few break. 80% or so of the sticks are pretty decent, which floats my boat, in this post wood Q-tip era.. So I'm ok with this B-grade product. I do worry about the cotton sometimes, as to how much bleach, chemicals etc was used in the processing of the cotton, whether it was washed out properly (wherever it is they make these), and the degree of sterility one assumes they have. I mean, hey- We stick these into our ears!! No company makes these for love of the human ear. Just filling the little niche left when Q-tips decided there was not enough profit in this product. All the brands available (imho) are too expensive, with the cheapest ones being really worthless and dangerous. By the way, used wood Q-tips (with ear-wax) are great to toss in with kindling as fire starters.. if it doesn't gross you out too much to keep a baggieor jar of them till winter.

column13: Beware Hollywood Eau De Toilette Users
column14:
I've been Using Hollywood for more than 15 years and this is the second time I've had this problem.
First was Perfumania which I returned.
The second was here at Amazon.
Now, Amazon may or may not know this but they are advertising and charging for Eau De Toilette...however, their supplier is shipping Cologne, which is much cheaper than the Eau De Toilette. One can tell the difference in the color. Cologne is Green and the Eau De Toilette is Blue.
A difference in the fragrance is noticeable to me and anyone else that is a regular user.
I tried unsuccessfully to contact Mr Hayman but he's in his 80's and probably long since retired and sold out to someone who cares about nothing but the bottom line.
Sadly, since I can't get the product I want and I'm paying for, I've discontinued using Hollywood.

column14: I searched for some time to find a natural/organic sunscreen and repellent so it is a keeper. As a sunscreen it works pretty well. For me, with my skin, it would be better at 45 SPF equivalent as I did get a bit pinkish but I did not get red, so that was good. As a repellent it did very well. While bugs did continue to congregate around me (I seem to be a big magnet), they did not land. That was a blessing. The smell is not overpowering...in fact, it is fairly pleasant. It does not take a lot to cover skin areas so be conservative when you apply it at first or you will have more than is needed. And, this is also a moisturizer. While I didn't particularly need this, it is a nice bonus. Being natural/organic (and Deet free) this combo is an easy 4.5, rounded to 5, for me. Definitely recommended. Warning: when your friends see you apply it they will ask to borrow it.

column6: Braun Silk Epil 7 Skinspa Wet & Dry Epilator Hair Remover For Face and Body
column14: When I got home from work today I had a package waiting on my front porch. I was so excited because I had been waiting for the Braun Aquila Silk-Epil 9 to arrive!  This is my first bzz campaign and I've been looking forward to the experience.  At first glance, this product can be a little intimidating- it has a swivel head with small tweezers covering a surface that spins-  which is how it removes unwanted hair.  It also has a brush attachment for exfoliation and several different attachments that can be used according to the selected area.  I read the directions carefully, seeing how I was a little apprehensive about anticipated pain that could be associated by using this product.  I decided to try what I assumed would be a "tough" area on my body, so I selected to remove the hair on my arms.  I switched the product to the "on" position and the spinning tweezers started whirring.  I placed the head of the epilator onto my skin, and to my surprise, the pain was minimal.  In one stroke, I had removed an entire swatch of hair (there was fuzz flying).  I continued this process until I had completed both of my arms.  I love that this product has a very bright light attached to it that allows you to easily see the areas that you may have missed.  My skin is a little red and irritated afterward, but the instructions state that this is natural and is the reason epilation should be done at night time.  So far, so good!  I'm looking forward to using this device again soon!  Cheers to a hair-free life!

column6: Global Keratin GK D600 Titanium
column14: I didn't want to give only one star... because this was a phenomenal flat iron while it lasted. Worked great, heated up very quickly. BUT... After 5 months of moderate use (maybe 3 times a week, on shoulder length hair) the on/off button got "stuck" and wouldn't pop back up no matter what I did. The only way to get it to turn on would be to unplug it, then plug it back in. But it would stay on for a few seconds and then shut off again since the off button was permanently stuck in place. I am EXTREMELY disappointed, because this was a great iron... And it wasn't cheap. Now I am doing extensive research on which iron to buy next. I think I will stay away from digital irons to avoid this problem. Also, I learned a valuable lesson that when spending this much money on a product, I need to fork over the money for a warranty in case something like this happens. So Sad!  UPDATE: Soooo This GK iron failed me about 6 months ago... Since then I have been looking for a new iron. I have purchased 2 others that have been in the same price range as this one and have had great reviews.... but they don't compare. Long story short, I am about to order this one again. This time I will save the warranty and take better care of it so the button doesn't break again.   The reason why I love this iron is because no matter what temp I set it to, it NEVER damages my hair and gives me "frazzled" ends that need to be cut off. I am getting married in a couple months and I have been trying to grow my hair. I had to cut an inch off yesterday because of the Babyliss Pro Iron I purchased last week fried the crap out of my ends with ONE pass, only on 360. I am taking it back today, and ordering this one again. I have A LOT of hair, its wavy hair but the stands are very small and delicate. This iron has been the ONLY iron I have ever used that doesn't fry my ends. I highly recommend this iron, just take good care of it and save the warranty in case the button breaks.

column14:
A couple things to note before we get started, a) I got this product as part of a promotion, b) my hair is relatively long (6-8 in), c) I usually use hair pastes, but figured I'd give gel a shot.

Overall, this gel of weird. When I first received it, the first thing I noticed was the inconsistencies in lids. Odd, right? Two of the three packs came with "smooth" lids while the third came with a sort of "slitted" lid. Pretty weird.

Next thing I noticed was the consistency of the product. Grabbing the gel out of the jar is like trying to scoop jelly from a jar with just your hand. It's slippery and just plain strange.

Lastly, the smell of the product is something between good and bad. I definitely could smell it as the day wore on.

To be honest, even though they send three containers, I'm likely to only use one and give the others away. Not my type of gel.

Tl; dr. I'm not a fan. Likely not to purchase again. "Hold" wasn't enough.
