column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column13: Finally Found a Reason to Retire My Norelco!!
column14:
I received this shaver as part of a promotion from Braun. It did NOT influence this review.

To get straight to the point, the Braun Series 9090 shaver is one phenomenal shaver. I have an incredibly coarse/thick beard and most electric shavers I have tried have a tough time cutting the hair on my chin. They bog down and sometimes painfully pull or pinch the hairs instead of cutting them. In addition, they do a poor job of cutting the hair on my neck which tends to like to lay down as opposed to stand up and allow itself to be cut. Happy to report that my coarse thick beard and uncooperative neck hair were no match for the cutting panache of the Braun Series 9090 shaver.

To really put the 9090 to the test, I tried it on 3 days of beard growth. After all, it says right on the box that it's rated for 3 days of growth! Although it took some time to shave my entire face (you have to work slowly), the Braun 9090 cleaned up my face without issue. It easily trapped and cut the longer hairs on my face. To my delight, my thick beard never bogged down the cutting head of the shaver. Further, it was able to grab and cut the hairs on my neck that like to lay down. It shows right on the box how Braun has engineered the cutting head specifically to cut in many different directions, and also to trap and stand upright those pesky little hairs on your neck that will give most other electric razors problems.

Upon completion, I placed the 9090 into its charging/cleaning stand and pressed the clean buttton. The stand comes with an alcohol reservoir which cleans the entire cutting head of the shaver. This gives you a 'just out of the box' shave, every time you use this razor. A cool feature of this cleaning system is that upon completion of the cleaning cycle, a fan kicks on that will dry the blades completely.

All in all, I'm super impressed with this razor. I'm retiring my old elecric razor in favor of the Braun Series 9090 shaver. Highly recommend for any electric shaver aficionados. Try it, you won't be disappointed!haver aficionados. Try it, you won't be disappointed!

column6: Anti Cellulite cream, Defining Gel, Active PPC, It works for Firming Tightening, Reduce the appearance of stretch marks, Concentrate cream 3.5 Oz .
column13: A cellulite cream that you can see results with.
column14:
I've been under the assumption that cellulite creams that state that they're going to help get rid of it was a gimmick. I'm not saying that I'm right, but I've talked to several people who have tried random brands and all they got was less money in their pocket. I saw the reviews on this Anti Cellulite cream and thought that I should give it a try, since it seems promising.

I place this on in the morning, after my shower, and prior to bed when I get my pajama's on and having used this for over the week, I'm loving the results. Within minutes of placing this on you can start to feel the skin warming and what feels like tightening. It's nothing that is painful or hurts, just something that you would feel that is different. It smells wonderful and it's nothing that you have to hold your breath to get it on real quick and cover it up - it's enjoyable.

You are to put a decent amount of the cream in the area that you're aiming to remove the cellulite from. Upon placing it on your skin, you're going to want to rub it in in a circular motion to work it into the skin. I place this on my thighs and I'm just loving the firmness that it starting to take over. Though it's not a night and day result, but a slow steady change, you can see that it's working. I'm hopeful for more improvement as I continue to use this and look forward to the results. I did receive this at a discounted rate for my unbiased review. My opinion was not influenced by the discount that I received.

column6: Sebastian Cellophanes - Red Brunette (New Name: Chocolate Brown)
column13: Unsung Hero of Hair Color, Ladies!
column14:
I wanted to wait a while before I left a review because I felt it important to have a solid impression of this product before I wrote about it. I'm 47 and I'm about 30% gray now. Initially, my plan was to grow out my old permanent color without having to deal with a line of demarcation... which, if you've ever had to deal with one, is a long term bummer. I was also toying with the prospect of eventually stoping the coloring altogether and going gray which this product allows you to do since it washes away in about 4-6 weeks. Well, I'm 18 months into using this product and I can't even adequately describe why I love it so much... But, I'm going to try!
First, this product is so much kinder to your hair than a permanent or semi-permanent color. It doesn't matter if you pay $120 in a salon or do it yourself with a $9 box of hair dye- anything that lifts the cuticle of your hair leaves it compromised and dry. The beauty of Sebastian Cellophanes is that it is pigment only. It just coats the hair leaving it looking and feeling shiny, thick and healthy. Your hair stays in its virgin state so it looks altogether less fried and can sustain itself against the other abuses you subject it to. FYI: the ammonia and peroxide you find in most commercial hair dyes is not only bad for you hair, it's also bad for your thyroid, Ladies! Low thyroid can cause hair loss. This is what happened to me and was one of the reasons I switched over to pigment only. Something to consider if you are struggling with hair loss.
Second, this product is relatively cheap. I get 4-5 colors out of one bottle, so I'm averaging $3 a color! Sure I have to do it myself and I do it more frequently (every 4 weeks), but it's still significantly less cost compared with my salon visits every 6 weeks.
Third, did I mention that my hair looks great? My husband says all the time now how much he loves my hair- so much more than when I was getting it done by a professional. Hilarious, right? So youare probably wondering about whether you can use this if you have gray hair. The website says up to 30% gray, but I'm there now and I think it's fine. My gray just turns into a lighter version of the color, so in my case using Red Brunette, I get a ton of coppery red highlights that actually look gorgeous in the sun. So if you have some gray, you get highlights thrown in for free. What's not to love? Overall, I highly recommend this product and find it a star among affordable beauty products!

column6: Plant Therapy Sesame Seed Carrier Oil. A Base Oil for Aromatherapy, Essential Oil or Massage use.
column13: Great carrier oil with many skin benefits!
column14:
This sesame seed oil (Sesamum indicum) came well packaged and well sealed. It is listed as a cold pressed oil, rich in vitamins E and B, and in minerals such as calcium, magnesium and phosphorus. It is an excellent emollient, is of a medium consistency, and absorbs well. It is not supposed to stain sheets, which is important to me, as I use it in a sleepy time Essential Oil roller bottle at night to help me sleep.
This Sesame Carrier Oil has a very distinct seed aroma, which could have the potential of overpowering other scents, but could be easily mixed with a less scented carrier oil if need be to reduce its aroma. Personally the scent does not bother me and I am pleased with it by itself because it is such a good natural moisturizer.
I store this (as most of my carrier oils) in a cool spot, out of direct sunlight, although refrigeration after opening is recommended.
Sesame seed oil is said to detoxify and repair dry skin, and protect again sun damage. It is also supposed to be good to prevent wrinkles, and to heal chapped skin. Plant Therapy is a trusted source of carrier oils (and essential oils) for me, and I am pleased with this product!

I’ve been using blades for many years, and, frankly, shaving that way has become a tedious – yet necessary – chore. So I was pretty stoked about being given the opportunity to use the Braun 9090cc as part of a promotion.

First off, I was really surprised by how quickly the shaver reached a full charge: right out of the box, it took no more than an hour! Secondly, I found this shaver to be a well-balanced instrument that really felt good in my hand. For my first shave with the 9090cc I decided to give it a good test: so I tried after not having shaved for 3 days. I may have had to spend a little more time shaving, but the Braun 9090cc did a good job with no discomfort in spite of having to cut through 3 days of growth! The trimmer is located on the back of instrument, and when in the raised position offers plenty of clearance to see what you are doing. Lastly, cleanup was a breeze: simply rinse the shaver’s head under hot running water, then remove the head to let it dry.

Okay, there are guys who have a beard thicker than mine, but mine is plenty challenging for any electric shaver; and the Braun 9090cc is a great shaver. It out-performs any electric I've ever used. While it does not give me as close of a shave as I get from a blade, it can quickly give me a decent shave.

column6: Spice Cream & Sister Freeze Wax - New & improved (100g/3.52oz)
column14:
Bottom line: this is by far the best hair styling product I have ever used. Buy it now, you won't regret it!

In-depth review:

I have medium-short hair that is naturally VERY thick. When I style my hair, I try to go for a semi-messy look that includes having my bangs up (i.e. not touching my forehead in any way). I have unsuccessfully tried more styling products than I could possibly list within the constraints of this review, but some of the more popular ones include Gatsby Moving Rubber (both the purple and pink varieties), American Crew Fiber, and Milbon Prejume Wax 7.

Both the American Crew and Milbon were incapable of holding my hair up for more than a few minutes even with the aid of hair spray. The Gatsby products were a little better in that they both could hold my hair up, but only if I used copious amounts of hair spray. This was overlooking the fact that they also gave my hair a plastic-like look that, simply put, made my hair look more like a wig than my own real hair.

Then I stumbled upon Arimino Spice Sisters Freeze Wax! I am able to achieve exactly what I have in mind just about every time I style my hair. It will leave your hair exactly where you put it if left untouched, yet manages to be pliable enough that if you decide to style your hair a little differently in the middle of the day, you can do so while while still maintaining the original hold strength. It is so strong that I haven't considered using hair spray even once! Just be certain to use a very small amount at first and add more as needed, because otherwise it will won't hold and will make your hair look greasy.

The scent is pleasant and, while definitely noticeable, never seems overwhelming. I am able to wash the leftover wax from my hands with a single scrub/rinse, and it typically washes out of my hair after a single wash.

Another problem that this product solves is that it can withstand surprising amounts of wind and even a little bit of rain/snow without being affected. I also like that the texture looks totally natural. If you like your hair to look greasy, I'm afraid this isn't the product for you.

The only drawback is that the container is rather sensitive to heat. Make sure that you don't keep the container in the same room you take your shower in, or else the remaining wax's hold strength will be severely impacted (this goes for dry heat too).

Overall, it is everything I could want in a styling product. Be sure to try it; I'm sure you won't be disappointed!

column13: Starting to work after only 2 weeks!
column14: Let me first say that I do not normally use anything on my face except for soap and water and I never have. I am 50 years old. When I was younger I was often told I looked younger than I was but that isn’t quite the case lately.  I have been noticing wrinkles, dry skin and just a generally lackluster look lately so I was willing to give this a try. I started using Advanced Age-Defying Face Cream By Anaiti on July 25 and after 15 days I was starting to notice a difference. The lines are around my mouth were not as pronounced, my chin dimples didn't look as deep and my neck looked smoother and firmer. It is still early so I haven't noticed any change around my eyes yet but I really don't have too much problem there so I may not. I would have to say that if used faithfully morning and night this cream can make a difference in your appearance without any needles. Who would do that? I will continue to use Anaiti Age-Defying Face Cream and am sure to see even more dramatic results ahead.  Disclaimer: I was given a jar of Anaiti Age-Defying Face Cream to try in exchange for an honest review. #AntiAgingCream

column6: Manic Panic Flash Lightning Hair Bleach Kit 40 Volume.
column13: Another bleach almost blinded me, and this product is still the worst bleach I've ever used.
column14: UPDATE: MY HAIR IS FALLING OUT IN CLUMPS. DO NOT BUY THIS.  TL;DR version: Cons: -does almost nothing to lighten hair -extremely irritating, even after rinsing. -tiny amount of product for the price -very damaging -MAKES YOUR HAIR FALL OUT Pros: I honestly can't think of any. full review: So, it's been 2 days since I used this bleach. I left a deep conditioner in for 12 hours yesterday and I'm doing another right now. My hair is FALLING OUT. I have bleached my hair many times and this has never happened before. I've been dying my hair for about 7 years. In all of that time, I've probably used every popular bleach there is. I decided to try this one because of all the positive reviews, and I am very dissatisfied. I'll be wearing a hat to the beauty supply when I get a better bleach to fix this crap. To start off, this bleach is pretty weird to mix. The instructions to say to mix it until all lumps were gone. No matter how much I stirred, the product was still kind of lumpy and powdery. It might be that it didn't come with enough developer. I got all the developer it was possible to get out of the bottle. The product also "thickens" after a minute. This made it really airy, like weird, powdery mousse. It was pretty hard to spread because of this texture, so there was just *barely* enough to cover my very short hair. The final product was the worst part about this bleach. It made my head itch like crazy while it was on. Also, after about 15 minutes, it completely stopped working. I left it in for another 20-30 minutes and it didn't get any lighter. It turned my roots (virgin hair) a very lemony, dark yellow. It did absolutely nothing to my ends. The ends of my hair were a medium brown when I put this bleach in, and they were medium brown when I rinsed the bleach out. This is also probably one of the most damaging bleaches I've used (which is weird since it barely did anything to my hair.) I have very healthy hair that I take good care of, and after rinsing this, an unexpected amount of my hair was falling out. It dried to a very straw-like texture and it's crinkly, almost like I got my hair crimped. Some of the bleach came into contact with my skin while I was applying it and while i was in the shower rinsing it out and caused awful irritation. Even now, hours later, my skin on my neck, back, and shoulders is burning and itching like crazy. I have no known allergies and this has never happened to me with other bleach products. I also got a migraine shortly after using this product, which may or may not have been related. In conclusion, don't waste your money on this. I've bought off brand bleach from sally's (I believe it was called prism, and it had a lovely apple scent.) for a fraction of the price that was way better than this.

column6: InStyler Ionic Styler Pro Ionic Hot Brush and Ceramic Flat Iron, Purple
column14:
The InStyler Ionic Styler Brush is the best beauty tool purchase I've made in years.

I watched many demonstrations, full of envy, as the models in the Perfecter demos used their styling tools with such ease, free from the fear of burning either their scalp or hair. I knew , from experience with the Calista Tools Hot Paddle Brush, that the Perfecter just wouldn't work for me. My thick, coarse hair requires HEAT.

So, I did what I always do, after a search of online reviews of 2015 best beauty tools, I turned to Amazon.com. There isn't much hype in the ad for the InStyler, but from the photos I surmised that this one might be what I needed. The teeth are long enough and broad enough to protect the hands and scalp from high temperatures and spaced widely enough to detangle, to guide the hair through them without breakage. The handle is ergonomically designed for ease and safety of use. The higher heat setting is exactly what I need ! And- at the amazingly affordable price I could afford to take a chance.

Once I had this wonderful styling tool in hand I was elated, oh so glad I took the plunge. This is everything I need. I can flat iron from the root , ending with a twist around the barrel at the ends to accomplish two tasks at once ! I can use the locking feature to effortlessly curl whatever didn't get curled with the first pass through, even at the nape of the neck, even at the crown. The higher temperature allows a once-through finish, without burning , without having to hold the styler in place for extended periods of time (as is required with the Perfecter even by those who aren't challenged with thick, curly locks) . This styler is phenomenal !

The InStyler Ionic Hot Brush may not receive the press that the competitors receive but it should. The ratings should be higher. I'll admit I made this purchase as a "why not", an alternative to the more highly rated, better advertised BaBylissPro. But the BaByllissPro has bars of thinner, more breakage-prone, hard teeth that slip back and forth along the barrel, clacking with a tinny noise while in use. The InStyler, in contrast, has stationary broad, smooth cool touch ionic bristles. They don't shift, tug or pull. They don't make you feel like you settled for less, again .

The InStyler has heft without being heavy, a reassuring, more substantial construction. The sliding bar on the stem locks the barrels together into a stable curling brush, securely apposing the surfaces of the flat iron. BaBylissPro has a fragile flip top hinge at the end of the wand, which I doubt will last through many uses.

There aren't many choices for a woman with the grade of hair the industry considers as an afterthought. Until now, the traditional, dangerous, curling "wands" were the only effective tools out there. We had curling irons in the fire, literally, then scary electric branding irons. What a find this tool is. The fear, the dread is gone ! I can straighten, wave, curl with confidence, with ease, and get fabulous, smooth, lustrous hair. (keeping all my hair on my head instead of lamenting the dozens of broken strands I usually have to pull off of brush/comb/curler )

Ladies blessed with lots of dense, coiled hair, don't hesitate ! Don't overthink this one. So, all the others have disappointed you ? I am convinced that you'll never regret buying this versatile, effective, safe, state of the art CERAMIC flat iron/ curling iron with IONIC bristles.

ps: it's on sale today, a further reduction by Amazon.com ! I bought a backup !

column6: One N' Only Colorfix Packets Kit (Pack of 2)
column13: IT WORKED. NO DAMAGE, YES IT SMELLS.
column14: First, my hair is dark brown naturally. Haven't seen my natural hair color since I was 13 which is when I first started dying it burgundy, then anywhere from blonde to blue to black then always back to burgundy over the years. I decided I want my old chocolate brown hair color back or at least for a little while lol, (you hair color gals know what I mean) so I bought one box of color fix from Sally beauty via online from their site. Did not wash my hair for five days prior to application. The directions are on the box and u will need a bowel, hair applicator brush and gloves. I straightened my thick long hair first before applying. Now I started the application. By sectioning my hair into five sections, then using the brush started at the bottom of my hair not touching the roots and applies once done I emptied the rest of the mixture onto my hair and massaged onto my roots and all over like championing my hair making sure I got it all, put a plastic bag on my head secured with clips then went and Sat outside in the sun in a chair from 10:15 to 10:50 then went to the shower and shampoos my hair out six times using bed head urban anti dotes shampoo, then got out towel dried my hair the best I could. Did NOT brush my hair, mixed. One cup mayo & one tablespoon vanilla in a bowel and applied to my hair at 11:07 put my hair up in a plastic bag and wrapped in a hot towel (fresh out of dryer) left in till 12:15 then put shampoo in hair with mixture still in, inside shower, (using bed head anti dotes shampoo & conditioner) then shampoos out using warm water, then once I felt it was all out, conditioned I rinsed in cold water then jumped out of shower and towel dried hair, brushed and let air dry. Then at 1:45 I dyed my hair using (from sally's beauty) L'Oreal Mega Browns Chocolate (2 bottles 2oz each with L'Oreal 20 developer *4 oz) left on hair for 5 min after application and quickly rinsed out then conditioned.  Overall It worked GREAT! Only downfall it does smell like boiled eggs... not as bad as people say tho... TRUST ME you will live lol...  it is not as bad as perm smell but close.. no damage done to my hair... im happy with my results... my hair would of turned the same color if i had bleached it.. only done ALOT of damage so yeah i think its worth the $$ to buy i have thick hair down to my back and i used 1x box and it was enough. i did skip step 3 (the processing lotion) during my process, to to so many reviews sadvising against it... but even after my mayo treatment it turned darker than when i had originally got out of the shower. Good luck to everyone i hope my review and pics help :)led eggs... not as bad as people say tho... TRUST ME you will live lol...  it is not as bad as perm smell but close.. no damage done to my hair... im happy with my results... my hair would of turned the same color if i had bleached it.. only done ALOT of damage so yeah i think its worth the $$ to buy i have thick hair down to my back and i used 1x box and it was enough. i did skip step 3 (the processing lotion) during my process, to to so many reviews sadvising against it... but even after my mayo treatment it turned darker than when i had originally got out of the shower. Good luck to everyone i hope my review and pics help :)

column14: I have had two of these dryers. While the price is great, and the dryer itself works well, they eventually failed where the cord attaches to the handle. column6: Peter Thomas Roth Max Complexion Correction Pads (60 Pads)
column13: My favorite skin product: Not for the faint of heart but definitely gets the job done.
column14:
These things are fabulous - I swear by them and recommend them to all my friends. That said - they are strong, maybe even "caustic" would be a good word to describe these pads. I don't consider my skin to be "sensitive" but if I did I'm not sure I would like these so much.

Anyway, I use them at night (ever few days) after washing my face with a gentle cleanser and in the morning my skin so SO SMOOTH. They really tighten up your skin, remove any little bumps, even your skin tone and make your skin look bright bc they like slough off dead skin. I am in my late 20s so don't have significant wrinkles (just to give you a bit of perspective) but any little thing that I am fixated on is easily gone by the morning with these things.

I came across these pads bc I was researching Proactiv and trying to figure out what made Proactiv work so well. It turns out it is the combination of salicylic acid and glycolic acid in Proactive that gently clears your skin up over time. This product is one of the rare few that contains both these ingredients and in a pretty high dosage hence the overnight results.

One review I read said that they cut the pads in half and use half here and there (since they are both $$ and pack a lot of punch an entire one seems almost unnecessary). If you have sensitive skin you could try that route and also maybe just use on occasion? Honestly if these were a bit less expensive I'd use them every night.

column6: Herbatint Permanent Herbal Hair Color Gel, 2N Brown, 4.56 Ounce
column14: I know there are folks who complain of a rash or other problem after using this or any hair coloring product, but I can't help but wonder if they actually did the recommended Sensitivity Test first, right up front - as every hair coloring maker suggests. That said, I have been using Herbatint for several years - after first doing the sensitivity test - because every time I used a particular Clairol product, my scalp would have a burning sensation. So I knew I had some sensitivity. But no problem at all with Herbatint. Except it doesn't come with a squeeze bottle so I have to buy ketchup bottles to mix and apply the dye. I was happy to have found a Good Housekeeping Beauty Products Hair Dye Review of non-toxic hair dyes called "Finding Safe Organic Hair Dye Products". The author admits "There is no such thing as organic hair dye. There are synthetic versions that work well and contain a lot of chemicals."  In the Good Housekeeping "list of seven brands I've heard are quite pure", the author ranks Herbatint at the top of the list. Well, it's topped my list for a while now. Overall, the author also hopes that "consumers make educated choices" about their hair coloring. Her Review is a straight-forward, well-balanced, no-hidden-agenda, research-supported Good Housekeeping piece that might help you make your next hair coloring decision, whether it's this product or another. Check it out at http://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty-products/hair-dye-reviews/advice/a17382/non-toxic-hair-dyes-55021302/.

column14: NOT SILICONE.  There must be hundreds of sellers on Amazon now describing their products as "silicone" when they are NOT.  These are made of some smelly, flimsy material -- probably TPE or one of the newer synthetic formulas.  A lot of people seem to think that everything flexible that's clear or white is silicone!  Silicone is very durable, odorless, usually transparent, and is inert so it can't cause any skin allergies or other reactions from the human body.  This stuff has a nasty chemical smell, and gives me contact dermatitis if used.  It's flimsy and tears easily.

column6: Dickinsons Original Witch Hazel Oil Controlling Towelettes
column14:
Using witch hazel as a toner is beneficial for your skin but the scent of Dickinson's is a huge turn-off. This specific brand's witch hazel has a very medicinal scent to it that lingers long after you put it on your face. So now we just use it as a first-aid for superficial cuts and scrapes and it works fine because it has anti-bacterial properties.
If you want a great witch hazel toner that's actually pleasant to use you should check out the Thayers brand. Thayers adds more beneficial ingredients such as aloe and rosewater to their witch hazels and they smell lovely. Their toners actually work better than anything from the expensive department store brands.

column14:
My favorite top coat! Dries several layers of polish to the touch in about a minute, and depending on the type and number of layers it's completely dry in about 30 minutes. Super shiny and evens out streaky polish and smudges very well.

One word of caution, don't use this with peel-off base coat (like you'd use under glitter) It's so effective at drying all the polish layers down to the nail that it forms a bond and when you go to peel it off it takes your nail with it.

Don't let that stop you from buying, though. It works great!

column6: Redken Fresh Curls Curl Refiner, 8.5-ounce
column14: Now that this product is discontinued, and word on the internet is that their new curl line isn't nearly as good, I looked around a few review sites and message boards to see what people were using as a replacement--and I found a GREAT product that I hope will help other people looking for the same thing. It's called Beyond The Zone Noodle Head Kick Up Your Curls Curling Creme and they have it on Amazon too. It works wonders--and may even be better (for my needs) than the Redken curl cream. Like the Redken cream, I use it after using gel and diffusing my hair until it's almost dry. After that, I use 2 small pumps of this cream to add more curl, bounce, and softness before diffusing again. The Beyond he Zone cream prevents my hair from staying crunchy from the gel and really does kick up the curls! It also smells great--like coconut, but not overpowering.

column6: Lovely Perfume by Sarah Jessica Parker for women Personal Fragrances
column14: The Elizabeth Taylor “White Diamonds” is a quality perfume. The fragrance is very pleasant and has good lasting qualities. When first opening the bottle the fragrance seems sweet and strong. A light sample to ones wrist leads to a totally different conclusion. The fragrance is pleasant and grows on you. As the perfume is warmed by the body the fragrance becomes lighter. The perfume has a good staying power. Twelve hours after application the fragrance of the perfume could still be noted. When applying the perfume, keep it light so that it is not overpowering. When the perfume was worn in public several friends said complimentary words about the fragrance and asked what was it, they liked it. To find out how Elizabeth Taylor “White Diamonds” perfume reacted with different body chemistries, I sprayed a small sample on the wrist of several friends. It was interesting to note that there was a identifiable difference between the aroma on each individual after a little time was allowed for “White Diamonds” to mellow and be warmed by the body. All of the variations were very pleasant. Elizabeth Taylor “White Diamonds” perfume would be great for special occasions as well as for every day use. The sweet fragrance could be enjoyed by both teens and adult women. When I opened the box and removed the bottle, my wife’s expression was WOW!!!!!!! The spray bottle is beautifully designed and decorative. The attractive bottle would look great on a perfume tray or dressing area counter top. The size of the bottle is a nice size for taking along when traveling. The Elizabeth Taylor “White Diamonds” perfume would make a nice gift for a family member or friend at a very attractive and competitive price. Elizabeth Taylor brand is well known for offering great products. This definitely is one of the good ones. I was provided this product at no cost for review.

column14:
As a product tester I compare dozens of skin care products, and I've arrived at a list of key considerations from fragrance to long-term results. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Mild herbal, no added fragrance
~ Color and texture: Cloudy, slightly yellowish thick liquid.
~ Feel during application: Wet, slippery, and smooth
~ Feel after absorption: Leaves a film on my oily face that is slightly tightening and sticky. On my normal-skinned hand, you can feel the slight tightening but no sticky.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Should be fine for all. It doesn't seem drying, and my sensitive oily skin is fine with it. May be a little sticky on oily skin.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 1oz blue glass bottle with squeeze dropper.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Very slight reduction in fine lines. I was having a bad skin day when I tested this, and about an hour after putting it on half my face, the side I used it on was less blotchy and flushed than the other side.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Vitamin C, niacinamide, hyaluronic acid, arginine ((2s)-2-amino-5-guanidinopentanoic acid on the label) and retinol are all key ingredients and some of the most popular anti-aging active ingredients. The herbal extracts and oils, aloe, squalane, rosehip seed oil, tea tree, lavender, ylang ylang, horsetail, geranium, and dandelion are all good for your skin.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

column13: Great razor for sensitive skin and nickel allergy!
column14:
I've been pleased with my purchase of the Panasonic ES2216PC Electric Razor. I developed a nickel allergy and could no longer use a regular razor, because none of them are nickel-free or hypoallergenic. This one caught my eye because it is specifically made nickel-free!! I like a nice close shave and figured I'd have to give that up by switching to an electric razor. I have found that if I am patient and use this shaver slower than my old regular razor I can still get a very close shave. If I race through the process I do not get a close shave.

I really like that this electric razor is fully immersible so that I can use it in the shower! I don't have to give up my old habits while switching to an electric razor. I have found a wonderful shaving cream by Kiss My Face which I use with this electric razor; it gives my legs a silky feeling while I am shaving. There is a pop up blade for longer hair and a bikini trimmer attachment. This shaver is rechargeable and the charge lasts for a few shaves before needing a recharge. You don't have to charge it after every use. I can highly recommend this as a high quality razor, particularly for people with sensitive skin or nickel allergies!

column14: When you shamefully go through life with sweaty armpits like I do, you need something that provides greater stink-covering protection than the other brands. So I have no choice but to say Dove Men + Care Antiperspirant is overrated because it's ineffective.  Come on I'm a guy here! column14:
It has a woody/spicy fragrance to it and compliments an oil diffuser perfectly. A lot of people use this and lavender oil to sleep and relax.
I did a little research to find other uses and here is what I found. Uses of Frankincense Oil:

Frankincense oil has long been revered in the Middle East, where it’s been used in religious ceremonies as an anointing oil for thousands of years. It is also a popular ingredient in cosmetics, and has even been found in the remains of Anglo-Saxons and ancient Egyptians.

I believe that frankincense oil is one of the top essential oils you can use for your health. It’s known for its comforting properties, and is useful for visualizing, improving one’s spiritual connection, and helping overcome stress and despair.

In aromatherapy, frankincense oil is either inhaled or diffused via a vaporizer – a very effective sedative that induces a feeling of mental peace, relaxation, and satisfaction, and helps relieve anxiety, anger, and stress.

Frankincense oil promotes healthy cell regeneration and keeps existing cells and tissues healthy. It’s useful for skin health, and can help treat dry skin, reverse signs of aging, and reduce the appearance of stretch marks and scars.
Frankincense oil’s astringent properties help:

Strengthen gums and hair roots

Stop wounds from bleeding

Speed up the healing of cuts, acne, insect bites, and boils

Benefits of Frankincense Oil

The health benefits of frankincense oil are mostly attributed to its anti-inflammatory, astringent, antiseptic, disinfectant, digestive, diuretic, and expectorant properties. It also has cicatrisant, carminative, cytophylactic, emenagogue, uterine, and vulnerary effects.

Frankincense oil is considered a tonic, as it benefits all the systems operating in the body, including the digestive, respiratory, nervous, and excretory systems

column14: I was trying to pin point why my hair has been so wonderfully soft and frizz-less recently and then I realized it coincided with when I purchased this leave-in conditioner. I became a big fan of Nexxus products a couple years ago when I decided to start using a better quality shampoo and conditional (better as opposed to Pantene or TRESemme). Their shampoo and conditioners have suited my hair well since I started using them and after using the 'for dry hair' and 'for color treated hair' types, I decided to try the Lightweight version. I notice a big difference in the way my hair feels, the light weight formula makes a noticeable difference. So when I was in need of a new leave-in conditioner, I searched out Nexxus brand. I prefer this spray leave-in type over the pump/wipe in type, it's far easier to apply. As soon as it settles, I am able to brush my wet, knotty hair, it smells very nice and doesn't leave any greasy feeling. My hair only feels soft and light with a light scent. And it looks wonderful! I have very bushy and frizzy hair, especially when I wear it natural, which I used to hate doing, but now with this spray, it looks so nice and managed that now I do not mind not styling my hair for work...it brings control to my unruly tresses! I am over-the-moon with this product and am so glad I did the subscribe and save option for this product as it is now a staple in my hair styling regimen.

column14: This was my  first time to order Shea butter. This huge block of Shea butter was so easy to work with. The Shea butter is very smooth and I found adding it to my homemade face and body cream very easy. I received recipes from the company so it was nice to see how to use the Shea butter in different ways. I melted the Shea butter and I added some essential oils to tone down the natural scent of the Shea butter. Once it was cool, I whipped the Shea butter with a little coconut oil, sweet almond oil, and argon oil. I was looking for a light airy cream. My finished product feels like softened butter.  While the Shea butter does not have a bad scent, I just wanted a softer scent for my neck and face creams. My husband thinks the finished product has a better scent than just the Shea butter without the essential oil added! I used about a fourth of my big block so I have a huge amount leftover.  I will be making much more of body and face creams in the future! Better Shea Butter is an awesome company with great customer service!

column14: This is the best alternative to manics rockabilly blue. Which is their WORST blue. This is almost identical to it and doesn't stain 1/4 of the way as much as rockabilly blue. I've been dying my hair and others hair unnatural colors for 5 years. My first blue was rockabilly and after I swore never again until I tried this. I don't have any cosmetology degree or whatever but from personal experience this blue still will stain (SKIN, pillowcases, bathtub, necks of clothes, hats etc.) (blue on pillowcases will fade after several washes and time.. I had pastel pink pillow cases that were promptly pink with blue spots), but as I said, not as much staining as rockabilly blue. Stains can come out of course. Fades to green after. Frequent dying to maintain color will almost have to occur if you wash your hair often. My hair falls a little below my collar bones and a jar will do. I've never had the displeasure of bleaching and putting blue dye on and it turning green tho my friends have. So bleach your hair a pale yellow and strand test (: you can sleep with it in and it won't harm your hair. Hope I helped a little bit.

column6: Sterling Beauty Tools Hair Cutting Scissors, Made from Japanese Stainless Steel, Includes 7 Inch Carbon Fiber Styling Comb with Bonus PVC Storage Bag
column14:
After learning how to cut my own hair I purchased the usual scissors they sell at the majority of retail stores. They got the job done, but I honestly didn't realize how low of quality they were until I tried these scissors. I could immediately tell a difference just by moving the scissors in and up and down motion. These were very smooth feeling, no type of resistance, or unusual feeling of lines on the blade. They cut my hair amazingly, I found that with my past scissors I would have to take small sections because to much hair would cause the scissors to cut unevenly. After I trimmed my hair, I took some scraps just to see how much hair these scissors would cut at a time and the amount was impressive. While it's probably not recommended while actually cutting hair, it was nice to see what these scissors could actually do. The comb is a very nice quality, it's not flimsy and unless extreme use was going on, it didn't feel like I would have to worry about it breaking. The scissors and comb came in a very nice pouch for storage, I usually ended up losing my previous pair in my container due to so much stuff, but the pouch will make this pair incredibly easy to locate them when I'm ready for a trim. I am so happy to have upgraded to these scissors, and am looking forward to much smoother trims.

I received these in exchanged for my honest review.

column13: Picture and item don't match! Why not fix this [known] problem?!?
column14:
It's my own fault for not reading the comments/reviews first, because I agree with many of them. The picture is of the standard "Mod About You" color while it's actually for the "Pastel" version, which as anyone who uses this polish knows, is very different. Anyone who uses OPI gel polish also knows that any "Pastel" colors have the word "Pastel" on the bottle handle, rather than the polish name. Which is exactly what I received: the "Pastel" version of the polish---with the "PASTEL" wording on the handle label. What I wanted was the standard "Mod About You" color, which has that name on the bottle handle, as this pic here shows.

I see many, many people have complained about this being confusing, and resulting in an incorrect [non-returnable] order, so it's perplexing, and disappointing the seller has not fixed this. Seems like it's intentional at this point....

column14: Didn't order from Amazon (found it cheaper at the wholesale store), but since I've followed Am reviews when deciding what hairdryer to buy, I wanted to leave a review here. This was my first usage and I'll update if any issues occur. This was my first time using an ionic blow dryer, and I must say I'm pretty impressed, my hair is smoother and shinier than using a regular one! My hair used to be all puffy after blow drying and needed 12+ hours to recover,so I'm very satisfied by immediate results. I have long, thick, straight/wavy and dry hair and have used hot/low setting to dry it. It took me less than 10 minutes (old blow dryer- around 20 minutes). Cold shot functions good and yes, you do need to hold it. Even so, I have a few cons, so in short: Pros: ionic technology does work! shinier/smoother looking hair and half off drying time; regular "volume" (not quiet, but not too loud) Cons: heavy, tiresome for hands; stiff cord that doesn't rotate; cord could be longer to improve overall function; big appliance and not foldable (complicated for storage)

column14:
The first time I used this my skin automatically went from oily and shiny to matte and normal! I apply as directed and sometimes (accidentally) leave it on for longer than recommended. With my hands, I slowly get a part of my face wet and start rinsing/washing/exfoliating with the sugar. Another reviewer said that if accidentally ingested it'll taste like sugar. Well... it does, but with a weird aftertaste. That only makes accidental swallowing while using in the shower better! And as far as the cap issue goes, I keep mine clean. It opens and closes perfectly fine. If it doesn't, I'll rinse it and clean it so it does. That's no big deal, and to me not a big enough hassle to where I'm removing a star. Amazing product and I'll buy more once I run out!
::EDIT 8/23/15::
I've been using this mask daily and everyone has been asking me what I've been doing to my face! However, a few days ago I took it a bit too far and accidentally/purposely (will explain) went against the recommended leave-on time and left the mask on my face for at least 20-35 minutes.
I applied the mask as I usually would and decided that I would leave it on a bit longer this time. Now, I was expecting to leave it on for another five minutes (11 in total; I leave it on for 6), not 25! I sat in front of my computer and played a few games while still very aware I had the mask on my face. I'm not sure anyone else has this problem, but I apply a small amount to my upper lip and when I breathe out of my nose it burns/stings a bit. Well as I was on my computer, my entire face started to do this too! I thought it was doing something to my face (it was... not a good thing, lol), so I left it on longer. The burning never subsided and actually got so bad to the point where I had to get up, rush to my sink, and immediately rinse the mask off my face while (almost painfully) exfoliating and rubbing the sugar off. The burning/stinging feeling was still irritating my skin even after I washed it off, and while I went to bed (after I used my Palmer's face oil, it soothed the stinging a bit and I realized that my skin was probably the smoothest it's been since I was younger). The good news is that I don't see any noticeable damage and it didn't leave my skin red (but did make the peeling around my nose quite worse), but even though there isn't anything I can see, there was definitely something that caused the irritating burn and possibly some damage to my skin that I have yet to find out about. From now on I'll leave the mask on as directed and do what I was doing before; no more experiments, I'm concerned about my skin even more. And even though I'm sure there isn't really anyone out there who'd leave it on for this long, PLEASE DON'T DO THIS! Oh my goodness, especially if you have sensitive skin. I couldn't imagine!to bed (after I used my Palmer's face oil, it soothed the stinging a bit and I realized that my skin was probably the smoothest it's been since I was younger). column13: I guess I'm the odd one out -- unsuccessful experience.
column14: After reading the myriad great reviews I was really excited and hopeful about trying these products (I purchased a cleanser and eye gel as well), but unfortunately they weren't for me. I liked the idea of a really powerful, all natural and almost all organic line, but from the day I started using these products my skin became very dry, I broke out, and developed these random patches of scaly, tiny bumps on my face. I stuck with it for about 2 weeks hoping it was just a transitionary thing, but eventually I couldn't stand what was happening to my skin. Switched back to a tried and true line (I've learned my lesson) and my skin is already looking better after 1 night, and on the road to recovery. If the the switch didn't make it so drastically clear that the Oz Natural products were doing my skin a disservice, I may have thought, "Hey, maybe these just aren't the best products for me." However, I've tried other products that maybe didn't transform my skin and I didn't necessarily *love*, but none have actually made my skin worse. Not to say that these products don't work for others, but I guess you have to balance out the thousands of success stories with at least one unsuccessful one :/

column6: Rimmel Scandaleyes Waterproof Kohl Kajal Eyeliner, Black, 0.042 oz
column13: Glides on easliy with work around for poor sharpening
column14:
The only thing I don't love about this is how hard it is to sharpen, which, from what I read, is a universal complaint. I use a very small sharpener and it just seems to crumble just about the time it is sharpened. What a waste of product. It isn't exactly what I would call waterproof but it's close. It does travel under, and in the corner of, my eyes as the day goes on and I only put it on my water line. It is very smooth, very black and glides on easily. I really love it if I could just figure out how to sharpen it without losing half of it in the process.

UPDATE:
This is not my original idea but it worked for me: When my pencil was new and not yet sharpened, I cut the blunt/top end of it off with a pair of side cutters from my tool box. That part appears to be made of plastic. I had to turn the pencil several times and squeeze the cutters really hard but they finally cut through. This exposed the round hole where the product is located. I used a cotton swab to gently push the product through the exposed end. Now I have no more product loss due to poor sharpening. I put a cap over the end from another pencil that had been used up. So far, so good.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column13: Made me appreciate electric shavers again
column14:
I received this shaver as part of a promotion from BzzAgent.
I am normally a blade user, and haven't used an electric shaver in quite some time. I have a light beard , and generally shave only a few times per week.
My past experience with electrics was not particularly favorable, but I was looking forward to trying this product as everything I've ever heard about the Braun brand has been positive.
I received my Braun 9090cc about a week ago, and it came with the the shaver, cleaning unit, power cord, one Clean & Charge cartridge, a reinforced cloth travel case, cleaning brush, and instruction manual.
The shaver is made in Germany, has a matte gray plastic front, is comfortable to hold, and light, but solidly built. The cleaning somewhat bulky, and takes up some room on the counter.
I have used the shaver several times, and it provides a smooth, fast and comfortable shave. Even with the rather large shaver head, I was able to shave all parts of my face with ease. Though I did have to go over a couple of trouble spots repeatedly to get all the whiskers shaven. This is not unlike virtually all other electrics I have used. Additionally, this product is a bit noisier than most of the electrics I have used.
As with most other shavers I have used, the trimmer is awful. Positioned as it is, flush with the rear of the shaver head, it is nearly impossible to see what you are trimming, and as a result offers imprecision and difficulty in maneuvering.
The cleaning unit, while bulky, operates fantastically. It cleans, disinfects and dries the shaver in about 45 minutes, and does so pretty quietly and efficiently. If you are travelling, or simply don't want to use the cleaning unit, this shaver can be rinsed under the tap.
Overall, I would recommend the Braun 9090cc. While it probably won't make me abandon my blades altogether, this product is now an excellent option for those mornings that I just want a quick, smooth, comfortable shave without the hassle of using blades. The Braun 9090cc has most certainly changed my negative outlook on electric shavers - I am definitely a convert.
PROS:
Smooth comfortable shave
Excellent cleaning unit
Waterproof for cleaning
Excellent battery life, and a quick charge
Tremendous craftmanship

CONS:
Horrible trimmer
Expensive at $350+
Not usable wet, with gels and foams
A little on the noisy sidehout the hassle of using blades. The Braun 9090cc has most certainly changed my negative outlook on electric shavers - I am definitely a convert.

column6: Real Aloe Gelly 8 Oz Unscented Gel 15% More Free
column13: Cures contact dermatitis and facial eczema
column14:
I bought this in my local store based on the ingredients which are: real aloe vera, purified water, Irish moss, xanthan gum, and citric acid.

This product literally saved my sanity.
I didn't know it at the time, but I was suffering a severe allergic reaction to a common ingredient in every shampoo. I had long term contact dermatitis in the form of blistering eczema, bright red rash, extreme acne, and my face had been swollen 3 times it's normal size for about 2-3 weeks after a round of oral steroids did nothing but make the situation worse. I frantically searched for something to at least ease some of my itching and rawness of the skin and I grabbed this product and hoped for the best.

That night, I mixed this aloe with some cold pressed Argan oil and put it all over my face. I noticed a decrease in itching and redness immediately. Over the next few days, I put the same combination on about 5x daily, or whenever I felt the skin starting to dry up and hurt. After 3 days every single symptom cleared up entirely, and to be honest, my skin looks better then it did before I started using this.

Now I use this same mixture every day, morning and night, and underneath my makeup. Every day my skin gets better, my pores are smaller, and get this- when I accidentally use something I'm allergic to (usually on my hair or in a soap by accident) and my face starts getting "angry", I put this aloe on and it stops any allergic reaction/rash/irritation in it's tracks. It's insane. I've never seen something have that much power. Maybe my skin responds really well to aloe, or maybe everyone could benefit as well.

I highly recommend this to anyone who suffers from eczema, rashes, acne, troubled skin around the eyelids and under eyes that appears to be red, dry, and raised. Even a baby that has problems with eczema and cradle cap. If you have extremely dry skin I do suggest you combine this with cold pressed Argan or jojoba oil, even alternate with castor oil at night (because it would be too greasy during the day). Especially for babies, you want to mix it with a nice cold pressed oil to condition the skin and prevent tightness.

Sorry so long, I hope this helps anyone who is looking for something to help their problem skin. I am grateful I have been able to cure my awful rash and I wish the best to anyone else struggling. Don't give up! There are natural options out there, you do not need to keep taking these awful steroids and cortisone creams that only cover up the problem. Keep trying different natural elements and you will find something that works.

column14:
We bought this toothbrush and love it. We don't really use the Bluetooth feature as much. It has a holder for 4 different brush heads. We bought one main toothbrush and several heads for everyone in the family so we can all use it. That helped me justify the price. It cleans *SO WELL* I feel like I am leaving the dentist every night. I feel like I notice a difference in the color of my teeth just in the month we've had it.

Some users commented about the vibration being too strong. I have used a traditional toothbrush my whole life and had no problem transitioning to this. It didn't bother me at all. It holds its charge well.

I also love the travel case. It kept it well protected on our trip. After we brush we just wipe it down--it cleans well and everything on it is well enclosed.

I like the features it has. We use the basic mode most often. It lights up green to remind you to move to a different quadrant in your mouth and lights up again when it's been 2 minutes. It flashes red if you are pushing too hard.

I like the brush head it came with and we also bought some sensitive brush heads. We got the whitening ones but don't like those as much. (It included a coupon for $3 off a brush set so it was a good way to try some different brush heads)

column6: VITABATH LOTION SPRING GREEN 20 OZ
column14: I have loved this scent for over 30 years.  I first came across the Vitabath green gelee in the 80s when my first roommate received a bottle as a gift.  When she used it, the entire bathroom smelled wonderful.  She did permit me to use it occasionally and I absolutely loved it.  The fragrance is fresh and crisp with a hint of lemon and lime and other wonderful green scents, like fresh mowed hay and green leaves.  There's simply nothing else like it.  Back then, there wasn't a companion lotion, which I would have loved as much as the gelee.  I purchased a set of gelee and lotion at Ulta a few months ago and I was very happy to discover that I still loved the scent.  It's very hydrating so you don't need much and the fragrance is just as potent as it is in the gelee.  I really love the combo of gelee and lotion and I'm pretty sure the fragrance lasts at least a few hours.  And my entire bathroom smells wonderful, lol!  I definitely recommend both the gelee and the lotion.  If you want soft radiant skin and love fresh, green scents, then the original spring green formula is a must have.  They are holy grail products for me.

column13: Perfect for styling, coloring, sectioning and daily use
column14:
I have thick and heavy hair. When I blow dry or straighten my hair I need to use few clips to separate and hold them while I work on one section of the hair. I always look for nice clips which can hold my hair tightly. Luckily I got the opportunity to try the Croc hair styling clips from hair Tamer in exchange of an unbiased opinion.
These hair clips come in a pack of 6. Nice and decent packaging. The clips are available in various colors and patterns.
The croc hair styling clips have great grip to hold and use on the hair. The Clips hold the hair tightly because they have double hinged design. No slipping or budging when you use the croc hair.
I use these clips for holding my bun of place. Just one clip works great for me.
For straightening, styling, coloring, blow drying and for daily use these clips work perfectly.
I love that the clip does not slip. My hair stays tight all day long.
These croc clips are perfect for summer to keep hair away from your face.
I am highly satisfied with these clips and I would recommend them.
As I mentioned earlier, I got this product in exchange of an unbiased opinion.

column6: Sally Hansen All Over Body Wax Hair Removal Kit, Net.WT 6oz/170g
column13: This wax kit is fantastic- it easily grabs hairs and removes them with little pain
column14:
This wax kit is fantastic- it easily grabs hairs and removes them with little pain. I have very sensitive skin and it doesn't irritate my skin at all. I would definitely recommend.

HOWEVER. There is such a thing as too much of a good thing. This wax takes no prisoners- Once this wax stuck to my hairs and skin, the only way it was coming off was on a paper strip or with the provided azulene oil. It takes quite a bit of effort to get the wax residue off my skin after I'm done. Additionally, never get this product on any hair you intend to keep because you will be SOL. I did not use talcum powder or baby powder and maybe this would have made a difference.

If you are looking for an effective way to wax hair without all the residue, I recommend Sally Hansen sugar wax, which comes off with a warm shower no problem.

column6: Pantene Pro-V Truly Natural Hair Co-Wash Conditioner 22.8 Fl Oz
column14: After reading reviews I decided to give it a try.  But first let me tell you that I drove to 2 Walgreens, 2 Targets, 2 Walmarts and 1 CVS in my area before I found it!  All of the stores had the other Pantene natural hair products (conditioner, custard etc.) but they were all out of the co-wash except CVS (and CVS didn't have many).  I figured it must be really good stuff since it is so hard to find.  So, I tried it yesterday and I really like it.  It works like other co-washes I've tried but the bonus for me is that it does a great job of detangling.  The others I have tried didn't.  It's not as thick and heavy as other co-washes and I think I would prefer it to be heavier to help control this thick hair I have but the detangling properties make it a real winner for me.  I don't really care for the fragrance.  It's not bad, but it doesn't smell of natural ingredients.  It's fragrance is rather strong and artificial instead.  I paid $6.99 for it at CVS.  MUCH less than here!  But it is good to know that if I can't find it in my area it is available here.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column14:
I just received the Braun Series 9 shaver from BzzAgent! To be clear, I have always been a blade shaver.
The Braun Series 9 shaver comes with the usual package which includes all the important components. These include:
• Braun Series 9 9090cc Shaver packed in a travel case
• Cleaning station
• Charger that can be used for the station as well as the razor
• Travel case including small brush
• One cleaning cartridge
• Relevant documentation- warranty and manuals

The shaver does not come fully charged and must be charged to start using it. It took about an hour for the Braun Series 9 to be fully charged on the first charging.

My first impression is that is a very high quality shaver.

On the whole, the performance of the Braun is very good. The shaver removes all hairs. With a three-day beard though, you will have to do a few passes to completely remove the stubble. Also it seemed to have a hard time getting a closes shave under eh jaw. The Braun is a four-stage cutting system with two trimmers. One criticism that I have with this shaver is the large razor head. While this feature is an advantage when tackling areas of the face such as the neck or chin, it presents a problem when shaving the nose and mouth area.

As for the cleaning station, there is not much to say really. After connecting the razor and pressing the start button, the cleaning process immediately starts. The cleaning liquid is flushed out of the cleaning cartridge through the shaving head thereby cleaning it. The used (dirty) then flows back into the cartridge.

Pros
• This is a very good quality razor that delivers a clean and comfortable shave even with long hairs.
• The double trimmers do a good job of removing all hairs. In addition to this, the cleaning station performs very well leaving behind a clean shaving head. Another plus is that the shaver is very quiet.

Cons
• The price. The shaver does not come cheap at about $350+ on ebay. (Its not available on Amazon yet)
• It had a hard time giving me a clean close shave under my Jaw
• The shaving head is too large for the nose and mouth area.

In conclusion, I would recommend the Braun Series 9 shaver to anyone who can afford it. In my view, the shaver comes close to a blade shaver in terms of closeness. The price. The shaver does not come cheap at about $350+ on ebay. (Its not available on Amazon yet)
• It had a hard time giving me a clean close shave under my Jaw
• The shaving head is too large for the nose and mouth area.

In conclusion, I would recommend the Braun Series 9 shaver to anyone who can afford it. In my view, the shaver comes close to a blade shaver in terms of closeness.

column6: Remington PR1285A R8 Wet & Dry Rotary Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver, Blue
column13: It Shaves Me Close, Has a Quick Charging Time, and I Can Get It Wet!
column14:
In July 2014, I received my first electric shaver from the Amazon Vine Program--the Remington PR1235 R3 Power Series Rotary Shaver ([[ASIN:B00IMNLD4Y Remington PR1235 R3 Power Series Rotary Shaver, Black]]). I fell in love with it because it gave me a quick, comfortable shave within a few minutes. There were some drawbacks, however. First, it didn't give me as close a shave as my disposable razor blades. (However, the Remington PR1235 never sliced me open.) Also, I once told a coworker, \\\I am not a drag queen; I don't need a smooth, hairless face.\\\\\" Furthermore, the Remington PR1235 only stayed charged for thirty minutes and took forever to re-charge (sixteen hours). It had no quick charge function that would allow me to continue shaving in case the battery died in the middle of my shave. I'm not the type who keeps an eye on flashing lights. Also, I couldn't get the Remington PR1235 wet. This is hard to accomplish when you are shaving in the bathroom

A year had passed and I was still using my Remington PR1235. It was time to buy new blades ([[ASIN:B00WD7Q0VG Remington SPR-PR Head and Cutter Assembly]]), which are nearly the price of a new low-end shaver. Thankfully, the Amazon Vine Program sent me the Remington PR1285A R8 WetTech Lithium Rotary Shaver. I love it even more than my Remington PR1235. Initially, I had to charge it for twenty-four hours prior to its first usage. Afterwards, it only needs to be charged for a mere ninety minutes. I used the Remington PR1285A for nearly two weeks before it needed charging. I was in the middle of my shave and I felt the shaver losing power. Then it died. I plugged it in for five minutes. (I timed it with a kitchen timer.) The shaver came to life and I had ample time to complete my shave. I like the fact that I can use the shaver when it is wet. I don't have to worry about dropping it in a sink full of water and ruining it. I have never used it in the shower because I need to view myself in the mirror while shaving.

I have shaved myself when my skin was dry. However, I get a closer shave when I use the Remington FaceSaver Pre-Shave Stick ([[ASIN:B002SO8IMS Pre-Shave Stick]]). I've also received close shaves when using the Williams Lectric Shave ([[ASIN:B0013NB7DW Williams Lectric Shave, 7 Ounce]]). I have also used shaving cream ([[ASIN:B001E5E9RK Gillette Foamy Shave Cream for Sensitive Skin, 11 oz. Bottle (Pack of 12)]]) over the sink, but it was messy. I prefer the Williams Lectric Shave because it is easy to buy, easy to use, and very economical. The Remington PR1285A came with its own charging base, which keeps it from rolling off my vanity. My former one, Remington PR1235, didn't have one and, because of its cylindrical design, it rolled onto the floor; fortunately, it didn't break. One must be careful to ensure that the Remington PR1285A is situated properly in its charging base. When charging, always remember to plug the cord into the shaver first before connecting it to the electrical outlet. When charging my iPhone, I've been told to do the same thing.

The Remington PR1285A R8 WetTech Lithium Rotary Shaver, Blue, is a beautiful, sleek, easy-to-hold, lightweight shaver. I love that it gives me a close shave no matter what I put on my face: powder, liquid, cream or gel. The shaver quickly charges so that I can always shave twice a day if I needed to do this. An LED light lets me know when it is charging or if it needs to be charged. But who takes the time in the morning to look at lights? I'm glad it has a quick charge function that allows me to continue my shave if the battery dies. This Remington PR1285A would make a wonderful gift for any man who uses an electric shaver. [For a young man who is just beginning to shave, I would buy them the least expensive model such as the Remington PR1235 R3 Power Series Rotary Shaver ([[ASIN:B00IMNLD4Y Remington PR1235 R3 Power Series Rotary Shaver, Black]])]. Myonly suggestion for Remington is that they take this model and give it a power system that is \\\\\"cord/cordless\\\\\" so that the shaver can be used with or without the power cord.only suggestion for Remington is that they take this model and give it a power system that is \\\\\"cord/cordless\\\\\" so that the shaver can be used with or without the power cord."

column13: Great Oil-Free Moisturizer for Oily Skin!
column14:
This moisturizer has done wonders on my face in conjunction with the [[ASIN:B00027EG9C Neutrogena Fresh Foaming Cleanser, 6.7 Ounce]]. When I say that I've spent thousands of dollars on remedies, concoctions, and miracle creams to help with my oily skin, I am not exaggerating. I started using this duo about a month ago after doing some Amazon searches. I went from having abnormally oily skin to now having skin that looks as if I have a healthy glow. I didn't realize what it was at first (because I've tried so many things in the past), but the end of the day would come and I would realize that I hadn't blotted my skin nor seen my reflection in my nose all day!

I can't say whether it was one product or the next, but I will say that for those with oily skin that think they don't need moisturizer, that's a myth because your skin then only overproduces oil in order to compensate for the lack of moisture. This is a great moisturizer to fill that void.

column6: Colgate Enamel Health Mouthwash, Fresh Mint - 250mL, 8.4 fluid ounce
column13: I can't taste my food anymore :(
column14:
BUYERS BEWARE.

I purchased this mouth wash based on my hygienist’s recommendation as she lives by Colgate Optic White and claims that this is the best mouth wash and whitening agent ever. This product surely helps your teeth achieve a whiter shade, no doubt about it, but at day 3, I am not sure this product is the best option for teeth whitening.

My mouth feels raw and burned. To the point that I cannot taste my beloved chocolate cookie dessert or the buffalo chicken sandwich, whereby any food tastes super mild and bland. Not sure what is in this formula which strips all sense of tasting from your mouth, but I’m telling you- my pearly whites do not compensate for the lack of taste as of late.

I have to say that you can feel this product effectively working in your mouth. The fizzing/burning sensation is no joke and I indeed sucked it up with the 60 second swishing. I would love this product if my food tasted the same. Something just isn’t right here folks….. Let’s just pray that my ability to taste comes back.

column6: Incoco Nail Polish Strips, Nail Art, Sweet Surprise
column14:
I've tried a number of nail wraps. The old Kiss wraps were my favorite, because of the quirky designs. But sadly, they're practically discontinued (or at least, every single design I love doesn't exist anymore).

I bought these on a whim, and I honestly expected to be let down. The design is absolutely precious and reminds me of cupcakes with sprinkles. The packaging stunk, and made applying a little more difficult. But they stuck on and stayed on for the weekend, without a topcoat! One nail chipped, but I was not careful at all, and treated my nails like they were naked.

Two minor complaints:

- If you have long, bendy nails, they will crack all over the place.
- ...you have dyed hair. I didn't even need to wash my hair for the dye to rub off onto the polish. I would just brush my hair out with my fingers in the morning, and the blue dye would tint my nails. When I did wash my hair, my nails were *very* blue. This is pretty typical of most nail polishes--and a top coat can't save you.

But, considering that I only wanted them for a weekend, I am beyond satisfied. Had I been less abusive, had false nails, or real hair, these could easily last me a week.

column6: Almay Smart Shade Skintone Matching Pressed Powder
column13: An alternative to more expensive brands!
column14:
I've been in the market for something that could replace my Clinique Stay Matte pressed powder in Invisible Matte (i.e. translucent) for a while now. I'm tired of paying nearly $30 (with shipping) for something that doesn't seem to last very long and which, at my age, has begun settling into my wrinkles. I also wanted something that was more of an actual translucent shade, i.e. that didn't really impart any of its own color, but just worked to set my foundation and stave off shine.

So far, the Almay Smart Shade Smart Balance pressed powder has met all my requirements. It sets my foundation well, reducing shine while using very little product (Clinique's pressed powder was a bit too "loose" for me, and I always ended up with too much on my brush and my face). To my eye, it did not impart too much additional color, though I noticed it did help even out the places that my foundation missed. I also don't end up with nearly so "ghosty" a look as I did with my other powder. My skin just looks natural, even toned, and matte. I bought the light/medium shade. I'm of Irish decent, and have very ruddy skin, and I think this shade matches my skin nicely, though I feel like I could have bought the medium shade and had it work just as well.

As a last thought: I have very sensitive, cystic acne-prone skin, and have always liked Almay because their products seem to aggravate my temperamental skin less than many other brands. My skin will usually let me know within 24 hours if it doesn't like something, and I've been using this product for a week with no ill effects.

column6: OZNaturals Facial Cleanser - This Natural Face Wash Is A Superior Cleanser That Deep Cleans & Unclogs Pores With Ocean Minerals, Vitamin E and Rose Hip Oil For That Healthy, Youthful Glow!
column13: I guess I'm the odd one out -- not a successful experience.
column14: After reading the myriad great reviews I was really excited and hopeful about trying these products (I purchased a serum and eye gel as well), but unfortunately they weren't for me. I liked the idea of a really powerful, all natural and almost all organic line, but from the day I started using these products my skin became very dry, I broke out, and developed these random patches of scaly, tiny bumps on my face. I stuck with it for about 2 weeks hoping it was just a transitionary thing, but eventually I couldn't stand what was happening to my skin. Switched back to a tried and true line (I've learned my lesson) and my skin is already looking better after 1 night, and on the road to recovery. If the the switch didn't make it so drastically clear that the Oz Natural products were doing my skin a disservice, I may have thought, "Hey, maybe these just aren't the best products for me." However, I've tried other products that maybe didn't transform my skin and I didn't necessarily *love*, but none have actually made my skin worse. Not to say that these products don't work for others, but I guess you have to balance out the thousands of success stories with at least one unsuccessful one :/

column6: L'Oreal Paris Youth Code BB Cream Illuminator, Light, 2.5 Fluid Ounce
column14:
I gave this 2 stars because I like the ingredients. They contain sunscreen and are non-comedogenic. I am EXTREMELY acne prone, and after a few weeks of use this hasn't caused me any new breakouts. I took away stars for the following reasons:

- More of a tinted moisturizer than a BB cream - the consistency is very thin and provides minimal coverage at best. It also makes my skin look shiny if I don't follow up with a matte powder.
- The "light" color is NOT light enough for fair skinned people and even made me look a little orange
- Has a perfumey smell

Overall, if you have very few flaws and a mostly even complexion and want this more as a moisturizer/sunscreen, it might be for you. If you have any type of blemishes, look for a BB cream with better coverage.

column14:
Using witch hazel as a toner is beneficial for your skin but the scent of Dickinson's is a huge turn-off. This specific brand's witch hazel has a very medicinal scent to it that lingers long after you put it on your face. So now we just use it as a first-aid for superficial cuts and scrapes and it works fine because it has anti-bacterial properties.
If you want a great witch hazel toner that's actually pleasant to use you should check out the Thayers brand. Thayers adds more beneficial ingredients such as aloe and rosewater to their witch hazels and they smell lovely. Their toners actually work better than anything from the expensive department store brands.

column14:
In all honesty, I am not much of a risk taker and normally I would balk at spending money on products that I didn’t hand pick myself. I’m so glad I took a chance on this purchase! After purchasing the lot, I sent a request to the seller for any face makeup to be in the colors to be in fair/light if it were possible. I received a quick response from the seller (which is Vera’s Boutique, just a head’s up in case the supplier changes) that they would make note of my request and I’m happy to report that I received the colors I wanted.

I received 16 products (2 were duplicated of concealer, but no complaints here.) In my lot, I got 1 cc cream, 1 liquid foundation, 3 concealers, 1 cc tinted moisturizer stick, 3 lip glosses, 1 nail polish, 3 eyeliner pencils, 2 roll on shimmer eyeshadow sticks, and 1 eyeshadow tin. The only colors that I’m not too stoked on are the purple and green eyeliners, but I’ll definitely try them out anyway. All in all, I am definitely happy with my purchase and I would order again.

column6: Carpe Antiperspirant Hand Lotion, A dermatologist-recommended, non-irritating, smooth lotion that helps stops hand sweat, Great for hyperhidrosis
column13: I'm working out harder because my hands aren't sweaty!
column14:
(This is actually Vicki writing this review.) I like Carpe' a lot. I''ve used it for my exercise class, Pure Barre. It turns out that it's easier to do the barre exercises without sweaty hands. With Carpe', I don't have to wipe my hands on my pants repeatedly, and I can hold on better and for longer.

I'm not surprised that Carpe' works. I've witnessed the incredibly thorough work the developers have put into this product. What I am surprised about is how having un-sweaty hands changes my workout. Even though the rest of me is sweating and clearly working hard, the fact that my hands are *not* sweating seems to be some sort of cue that I need to work HARDER. I did not expect this!

The lotion goes on easily and works quickly. You only need a little bit. The scent is clean but a little medicinal for me. But Carpe' works! Definitely try it.

column6: Gillette Fusion Proglide Sensitive Shave Gel, 6 Ounce
column14:
I received a can of Gillette Fusion ProGlide Sensitive Shave Gel + Skin Care to try from Gillette. I honestly have to say Gillette has done it again with another great product. I get a really close, smooth shave and after shaving with Fusion ProGlide Sensitive Shave Gel, my skin feels soft and smells great!
In addition to a great shave gel, the folks at Gillette have come up with the perfect can. First off, there is no cap! You just turn the top of the can to dispense the gel and there is no oozing gel or mess when you close it. The second feature is the plastic bottom of the can, this may not sound like a big deal, but my wife sure is happy that there are no rust rings on the bathroom vanity anymore since I started using Gillette Fusion ProGlide Sensitive Shave Gel + Skin Care. Lastly, there is a gauge on the side of the can to let you know how much you’ve used and how much is left in the can. No more running out when it feels like there’s still some in the can!
Personally, this is my new go to shave gel and I highly recommend trying Gillette Fusion ProGlide Sensitive Shave Gel + Skin Care!
