column6: BEST Dead Sea Mud Facial Mask + FREE BONUS EBOOK - Cleansing Acne & Pore Reducing Anti Aging Mask for Clear, Radiant Skin - 6 oz
column14:
Ok, I am so, so disappointed in this product. I had planned a spa-type night with my two teenage girls, and when the opportunity to review this product came up, I was so excited, as I had heard such good things about dead sea mud, salt, masks, etc. I was so excited. It didn't last.
The texture is nice, smooth, with just a few little smaller particles in it. But, hey, it's mud, so, all's cool. The scent in the jar is pleasant. It spreads on smooth, and it does go on thin. That's a little different than other masks I've used, but it was nice. We applied a thin layer, leaving large spaces for our eyes. All went well for about a minute. What began as a pleasant tingle became more and more intense, until my face was on fire. Not " oh, it burns a little." It shot right past that into your brain screaming "Get it off! GET IT OFF!!" The RED ALERT was sounding in my head! At this time, my oldest child was near tears saying her face was also burning. We grabbed washcloths and washed it off. Water made it WORSE. My face was red, shiny, swollen. My eyes were also red, watering, burning, and hurting. The swelling took ten minutes to start to subside. The burning continued for almost a half-hour. I found that water, no matter the temp, made it worse, as did Aloe Vera gel. It is now the next day, and my face has a rough texture red bumps all over my cheeks and burns if I place coconut oil or Shea Butter on it. I'm at a loss. I feel like our pet bearded dragon, and that's just not how you should feel after a beauty treatment.

I have looked over the ingredients, and I am still not sure what caused this reaction. The ingredients are : dead sea mud, organic Shea Butter, organic sunflower oil. Organic Aloe Vera juice, organic vegetable glycerin, organic jojoba oil, hickory bark extract, organic calendula oil, filtered water, xanthan gum, eucalyptus oil.

I've used almost all of these ingredients except for hickory bark extract and calendula oil. I have never used eucalyptus near my face, so maybe? Oh, and, of course, dead sea mud. Something lit my face on fire and caused a reaction. I wish I knew what, as I would avoid it forever. My one kid was unaffected, my kid that also had a burning face had no lasting effects after about 20 mins. After removing the mud, a very strange smell lingers. It starts off very mineral, progressing to slightly fishy, and finishes off pure lake mud. A nice citrus hand soap will take the smell off your hands.

I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest, unbiased review. All opinions expressed are my own.e never used eucalyptus near my face, so maybe? Oh, and, of course, dead sea mud. column13: My Smile has NEVER Been Brighter
column14:
It is hard to put in words just how THRILLED I am with the Crest 3D White Brilliance Daily Cleansing and Whitening System! I have tried many, many different whitening toothpastes, gels, strips, lights to get rid of stubborn coffee stains. Each product has left me unsatisfied-whether it was from the shade of my teeth or to how much my teeth hurt afterwards. Rest assured, I have found my go to whitening product that I am absolutely in love with. Crest hit it out of the ballpark with this whitening system!

Step one is a cleansing system. I squeeze a pea size amount onto my toothbrush which is plenty. This step honestly makes me feel like I had just left the dentist's office. The paste has a tiny amount of grit in it to make your teeth feel super clean. I love how my mouth feels after using this step. In just one minute, I feel like my mouth has never been cleaner.

Step two is the whitening gel. Again, in just one minute, your teeth are brighter, whiter, and all around more sparkly than before. I was worried I would feel sensitivity at step two. However, I never once felt any sensitivity or pain after! This is a huge deal to me. I usually feel like someone is stabbing me with pins and needles after whitening my teeth. I wish I was kidding with that, but that's how sensitive my teeth are. Again, not one side effect almost a month later. Hurray!

Pros:
-Whole process only takes two minutes
-BRILLIANT white teeth with results within a week
-Banished my stubborn coffee stains
-Whitened my canines which no product has ever done successfully
-Teeth feel super clean
-Absolutely zero sensitivity

Cons
NONE!

Please do yourself a favor. Go grab this Cleansing and Whitening system immediately. Your whole mouth will thank you. Your teeth will never have looked better! Thanks Crest and BzzAgent for letting me try this amazing product. I have a new staple in my daily routine and am beyond thrilledwith my results. Never again will I need another whitening product!

column13: Entirely less functional than it could be
column14: What was unclear to me before ordering this is the design. The black lines you see halfway down the sides are pockets, which I understood before I ordered. However, I assumed the side pockets were the full length of each side with the openings just placed halfway. This is not so, the side pockets are just the lower half of the "briefcase." I guess if you need to put something bigger than the height of the side pocket, it just has to go into the middle, unsecured. I have a similarly sized makeup organizer by Con***ts that does have side pockets with opening zippers about halfway down but where the pockets are the full length of the case. With this bag, expect all your contents to be in the bottom half of the bag and no real usable storage space above the zippers halfway down. Not terrible, just not terribly useful. The vinyl is a decent thickness, I would not expect it to puncture or rip with  regular use. Zippers are not great, I had one come off almost immediately but I was able to get it back on the tracks with a little work. I would not order this again nor would I recommend for storing anything other than maybe paper and pencils. For everything else, there are better products out there. I just wish I had chosen the "City Lights Carry-All Make Up Bag, Large, Clear" from this seller as I think it would serve my purposes better.

column6: Vanicream Lite Lotion, Pump, 16 Ounce
column13: Very good skin cream, a bit heavy, but long lasting
column14:
I've tried many, many different skin creams due to living in a hot, dry climate and having eczema that I need to keep under control. I would give this cream 5 stars for hydration. It really does the job of keeping my skin well hydrated ALL day or night. I give it 3 stars for the "quickly absorbed part" for an even 4 stars. The label says "non-greasy" - well, maybe not greasy, but tacky for at least a half hour to an hour. It's a very "heavy-feeling" cream. The label says "long-lasting" - definitely. Absolutely. The label also says "quickly absorbed" and here I have to disagree, but then again, they didn't say "compared to ..." so the meaning is relative. Compared to other creams I've used, it is not quickly absorbed, but that can be the upside for someone with extremely dry, cracked skin. If so, this really is for you. The label also says "for sensitive skin" - I agree with this statement too. I have very sensitive skin and other than the tacky feel after I put it on, it does not bother my sensitive skin.

I like that Vanicream is fragrance free, and without parabens, and comes in a decent sized jar so I don't feel like I've just been ripped off with some little bitty jar of cream. I also like that it has a pump on it so I can dispense only what I need and I don't have to put my fingers in a jar to apply it! If you have really dry and temperamental skin, I can honestly recommend it - if you don't mind tacky skin for awhile. It will keep your skin hydrated all day!

column13: Love using a natural clay mask on my face!
column14: The Native Vitality Revitalizing Healing Clay is really starting to grow on me. I received this product in exchange for an honest review and I have used it once a week for about a month (on my face as a mask) and I've learned that the product seems to work a lot better when used with just a little bit of apple cider vinegar (like they state in the instructions). I was heisitant at first to put vinegar on my face but it really seems to help clump it all together and dry more evenly on your face (and my sensitice skin is fine with the vinegar). My face feels very smooth after washing it off (it comes off easier when u let it dry completely, even if it starts to feel tight, and then a little help from a washcloth), although I am hoping to see more results upon continual use. The instructions state to use 2 tablespoons of the clay but I can cover my face in a thick mask with just a little less than 1 tablespoon, so use only a little at a time, or else u might get stuck wasting some product. I am anxious to use this in other ways (than my face) that were mentioned in an info sheet sent to me, but I highly think this would be helpful to get sent out with the product so everyone knows just how to get the full usage out of the clay.

column6: Dentemp Dental Cement Size Ea Dentemp Maximum Strength Dental Cement
column13: Didn't work for a side filling at all
column14: This is an embarrassing subject but because I know that many people are looking for help with temporary fix to cavities until they can afford to see a dentist, I feel it's important to share my experience. So here it is... I purchased Dentemp and it's competitor, Dentrek. I am in the process of getting dental implants and needed to fill 3 cavities to hold my 3 front teeth together for the next 40 days until my procedure. Perhaps the product may work on molars, but I was trying to fill a small whole on the side on my tooth from where my partial deteriorated the tooth. I tried the Dentemp first and it NEVER lasted more than 3 hours. I followed the directions carefully and tried several times. It just didn't stay in. That being said, it is very difficult for a cavity on the side of a tooth, especially the front tooth, to hold a filling. Even a dentist has to place these types of filling with extra care because they are so hard to keep filled. So perhaps the reason I was not able to use this product is because of the placement. I then fried Dentrek and it will last all day before coming out. The Dentrek doesn't last more than a day in the front tooth so I do have to refill it every morning; however, I also used it on a tooth with a typical cavity (on top of the tooth) and it's been there for 5 days and is still holding up. This product didn't work for me at all. The reason I gave it 2 stars was because I realize that the type of cavity I needed to fill is not likely to hold any temporary filling for long.

column6: Soobest Professional Beauty Cruelty Free Kabuki Synthetic Makeup Brushes Set Cosmetics Makeup Brushes Kit with Carry Bag (Golden White)
column13: Beautiful, Luxuriously Soft, Amazing Quality Brushes!
column14:
My first thoughts on these brushes were obviously the packaging - it blew me away! They're incredibly beautiful, and look so stunning. There was a slight plastic-y smell coming from the brushes, but it wasn't overwhelming, and faded quickly.

As far as the brushes themselves, they are honestly so soft, and they work amazingly. They blend foundation into the skin sooo well: in fact, it almost looks airbrushed. Since they are synthetic, they work really well with both cream, and powder products! I have many other synthetic brushes similar to these from other companies, such as BH Cosmetics, SixPlus, and Sigma - and these hit the mark with my expectations from all of those brands! (Yes, even Sigma!!)

The nice thing about this set is that there is a very big variety of essential brushes, and they are all very unique. Though they are similar to other brushes out there, the bristles themselves are very short, dense, and soft. I really don't have anything else like these in my collection!

Another plus - I only experienced shedding with these brushes when I very first pulled them out of the package. Now, that may not be an issue for everyone; but being a professional makeup artist, it's important to have tools that won't leave fibers on your client's face! So with that being said, yes, I would definitely recommend these to any makeup artists, makeup enthusiasts, or even just someone who wears makeup frequently!

If you're looking for amazing, luxurious brushes without spending an arm and a leg, look no further! These are fantastic!

[These brushes were sent to me for review purposes - though that does not effect my opinion whatsoever.]

One con to this is that the tube is metal instead of rubber-like more pliable material, so it takes precision in pressure to extract the right amount of the cream. I don't have freckles, so cannot attest to the cream's efficacy regarding this type of skin discoloration. column6: Microplane Colossal Pedicure Rasp Foot File
column14: This thing is amazing!! It completely removes dry skin from your feet. That being said, there is definitely a slight learning curve. I recommend working with an extremely light hand because it's very easy to take off too much leaving you with potentially raw painful skin or even gashes. Just take your time, work on one area at a time with light pressure and you shouldn't have any issues. Calluses form to protect you so all you really want to accomplish is just removing any access dry spots that have formed over the callus NOT the actual callus. Before using it, make sure you lay down an old towel or just go outside because the dead skin it removes creates a dusty mess. To use it I apply very light pressure and slowly move the rasp up and down until my desired results in each area of the foot. I usually follow up with a scrub and Mr Pumice in the tub to make sure everything is smooth and clean.

The bottle came safely packaged in its own plain cardboard box and the shipping was fast.The oil is a nice golden color, naturally odorless, and non-comedogenic. The bottle is amber colored glass and the dropper is also glass. There is also a sticker on the bottom of the bottle that tells you the "best if used by" date (mine says December 2017).

Jojoba oil is one of my favorite oils because it gets absorbed quickly by the skin and does not leave you feeling greasy.This oil is technically not an oil, but a wax ester which is the most similar natural compound to the oil produced by our skin (sebum). So in theory (This has not been proven as of yet), jojoba oil can trick the skin into producing less oil, thus balancing out oil production on the skin and scalp. Jojoba oil is also very stable, so it can be kept for a long time without it going rancid or losing its antioxidant properties.

The uses for this oil are almost endless! So far, I have used it for DIY anti acne masks, as a facial moisturizer after clay masks, hair oil treatment, aftershave, leave in conditioner, cuticle oil, and to treat dry skin on my heels with good results. This, along with argan oil, rose hip oil and coconut oil, are some of the oils I try to always keep handy for their versatility and usefulness! The bottle will also last a long time seeing as you only need a couple of drops for it to be effective (I have waist length thick,curly hair and only use 5 drops on it along with coconut oil.) Overall a good quality oil!

The ingredient list as stated in the back of the bottle:

100% pure and certified organic cold-pressed Jojoba Oil (Simmondsia Chinensis)

column13: Great Product for Flavor and More....
column14:
I got this product yesterday and really like it. I mixed it with "peanut flour" (de-fatted, ground peanuts), coconut oil, and coconut milk and made truffles. They were delicious. I was skeptical of the reports that the carob powder was sweet on its own because I have such a sweet tooth and am usually adding plenty of stevia when everyone else is quite content. However, it truly was sweet and I added nothing.

I did not react to it like I do cocao powder either. So, I'm off to develop some protein bar recipes with it!

Update:
This product helps keep my gastritis at bay. I had read it can do that, but didn't give it that much credence and certainly did not buy it thinking it could help. After using this a few months, I definitely have more tolerance for acidic foods.
I've started using it to make protein bars with the "peanut flour," pumpkin seed protein powder, carob powder, almond butter, small amount of raw cacao nibs, and mix with either coconut or almond milk. I make a mixture dry enough to form into bars, put them in plastic wrap, and freeze them so I have them to grab on the go.

column6: The Body Shop Sweet Lemon Body Butter 6.75 Oz.
column14: I picked up two of these tubs at TJ Maxx for $6 apiece.  The body butter is rich and thick and really hydrating.  I live in Florida so I don't have a problem with winter dry skin, however, the humidity here leaches out my skin's moisture, especially in the summer.  The intense sun makes my skin parched and thirsty for nourishment.  So I always use a thick formula of lotion, preferably body butter or a similar cream. I find that my feet, knees, elbows and hands are especially vulnerable.  I hadn't used a Body Shop product in many years because I've always thought they were overpriced, so when this lemon body butter showed up in TJ Maxx, I decided to take a chance and purchased two.  They are small containers, but for the price, I'm not complaining.  The texture is silky and smooth and it does a very good job of keeping my sun parched skin hydrated and soft.  I also like the sunny lemon fragrance, although it dissipates quickly.  I use this product on my driest areas and then use a Nip and Fab lemon lotion for the rest of my body.  The two brands work well together.  I'm pleased with my discount purchase and I think I paid a fair price.  But this product is definitely not worth the standard body shop price of $15-$20!!  I recommend this product for its hydrating properties and for the tart lemon scent.  It's perfect for a summer Florida day.

column6: Hydrotac Stick-on Bifocal Lenses (OPTX 20/20)- +1.50 Diopter
column13: There is a simple trick to getting better adhesion...
column14: Killer vision. The trick is to trim them using sharp scissors or a straight edge and an Xacto blade. Then run them in hot water along with your glasses. This will soften the stick-on lenses and let them form better to your lenses. Once you have the glasses and lenses as warm as you can handle in hot water. Take a small drop of dish soap and rub it on the glasses (both lenses) and then apply the bifocals on the soapy surface. Press out all the air bubbles and position them as low as you can without touching the edge of the lens. Try them on and adjust as necessary. You may have to widen or narrow them to get them in the correct position, depending on your interocular distance.  The soap will help adhesion -just like the soap in model airplane decals helps them stay attached. Left overnight, they will dry clear and adhered. If you missed a bubble, press it out. If you cannot get it totally clear, peel off and try again.  The key is positioning them, pressing them in position with your thumb, and then wiping off the bifocals and trying them on to make sure they are correctly positioned and clear. Don't worry about soapy spots on the rest of the lens, you can clean that off the next morning. The soap helps adhesion but you can still peel these off and reposition them easily using soap each time. Depending on the curvature of your glasses, these may slowly start to let go and they may require a re-do. For most glasses, using soap and hot water makes them really hold on well and not separate.

When I received this gift from Vidal Sasson and BuzzAgent in the mail I was a little taken aback by the bright, unexpected colour featured on the box. After weeks of waiting for my old henna colour to wash out I was ready to dye my hair with Vidal Sasson London Luxe 4RV Mayfair Burgundy.
The box contained a wonderful pair of gloves, the two bottles that when mixed were applied to my hair and a conditioner. I should have done a couple of tests including the strand test and the allergy test which I chose to forgo due to time constraints.
Mixing the products was easy and clean. The smell of the product was harsh and lingering (I don't use permanent hair colour products so I was not prepared for the strength of the smell). I found it a little difficult to apply evenly, but succeeded in the end. I don't think it is really possible to mess up the application as long as you are thorough. I waited the requisite 30 minutes during which time I cleaned up the drips on my skin and around the bathroom. The product did not stain my skin or the objects I dripped it on. It did not clump and I LOVED that I could apply it to dry hair.
After the time elapsed I began to wash out the product. It took me a little over 20 minutes to wash my hair out after which I applied the conditioner which I thought would set the colour.
I ended up with an even colour similar to that featured on the box. It had dimension and depth. It was brighter than I was used to and caused people to notice me.
I did find that after the initial few days the colour settled/washed out a little bit and became much more natural. After two weeks a little of my original colour is showing through which adds a nice balance to the red. Overall, I would buy this product again especially for this shade. Mayfair Burgundy is a winner!

column13: Decent basic set for kids; Not ideal for serious nail care
column14:
My first observation of this item was "It looks like a dollar store set" The packaging is not that attractive and I could not see giving this as a gift for that reason. If you are interested in this item for personal use, it depends. Here is why:

1. It says it is 9 piece set, but instead of the pair of gloves counting as one item, they count each glove. Not a big deal since it is very easy to figure out before you buy it, but it is trying to add value to this set where it does not exist.
2. The gloves are *small*. I have very slender hands with long fingers. I expect no gloves to be long enough for my fingers- so I was a bit surprised that for the most, they were long enough, however, they were very tight. Oddly, not as much on my palm, but on the fingers themselves. On most my fingers I wear a size 5 ring, so if your fingers are smaller than that, these might be OK.
3. Not only are the gloves small, but they are badly made. Neither is the same- the thumb is stitched differently on each one, causing one to fit fairly well, but the other to not come close to the web of my thumb. The seems inside are very bulky, which when added to the tightness in the fingers, makes it rather uncomfortable. They just feel very weird and are not something I would want to wear for any length of time.
4. The Sapphire nail file is cheaply made. The metal is OK, but on the thin side. The handle is solid, but the edges of it are rough. The file itself is decent, but not as rough as most files like these I have seen. The tip is also bent, however, I am unable to tell if this is on purpose. I am not counting this against the set since I cannot say for sure it is a defect.
5. The files are all the same grit. The better sets I have used had different grit which allows for you to really smooth your nails down, using the rougher files for the rougher spots as needed. You cannot do that with this set.

Overall, it is an OK set, but one I would only use with young girls who want a set to play with. Maybe a sleep over party where you could provide each girl with their own set. For anyone serious about their nails, I would pass.

column6: Remington PF7500 F5 Comfort Series Foil Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver
column13: A good, close shave, but the design...
column14:
I have had a Philips Norelco electric razor for several years. I use it several times a month, use a Gillette Mach 3 manual razor often, and, the rest of the time, I let the scruff grow. This Remington electric razor gives a closer, smoother shave than my Norelco, but it's difficult to maneuver around curves of the face and feels awkward in my hand.

Cons
Right out of its package, the Remington did not feel as good in my hand as my Norelco. It felt boxy and is not nearly as well designed and does not feel comfortable to hold.

When I turned it on, I was surprised how loud it was. This is likely a result of how the blades move under the foil, but it was a surprise.

When I first used it, I had about three days of scruff. For me, this is just about at the limit of an electric razor for me; with hair longer than this, I have to go to my Mach 3.

As a test, I shaved half my face with the Remington and the other half with the Norelco. Shaving with the Remington was a bit awkward. Its poor ergonomics and straight foil made it tricky, and it required much more re-positioning to get my neck. To be honest, I was not liking the experience and expected the shave to be about the same, only with more work to get there. However ...

Big Pros
Afterwards, I had my unbiased wife feel both sides and give her thoughts. Without hesitation, she chose the Remington side! The Remington did a much better job at getting the longer scruff that I'd usually have to get with a regular razor. Now to be fair, my Norelco blades had been used more, and the Remington was brand new, but I could feel and see a difference.

I have both razors side by side in my bathroom, and I keep picking up the Remington to get a closer shave. The other big pro is that the sideburn shaver gives a much closer shave. Unfortunately, when shaving my burns, the whole thing is even more awkward to hold.

Conclusion
It is an awkward razor to use, but darn it all, it gives a great shave for an electric razor! That said, I won't be getting rid of my old razor, as the Norelco is fully wet/dry, and that is very handy at times. It's also faster and easier to use for a quick shave that doesn't need to be super close.o use, but darn it all, it gives a great shave for an electric razor! That said, I won't be getting rid of my old razor, as the Norelco is fully wet/dry, and that is very handy at times. It's also faster and easier to use for a quick shave that doesn't need to be super close.

column6: Tweezerman Professional Stainless Steel Toenail Clipper 5011-p,
column13: Preferred for the big toenail only
column14: I compared it to a regular (no name) toenail clipper having curved jaws. My first impression is the difference in finish between the two. It doesn't take a trained eye to notice that it is stainless steel instead of chrome plating, as on the regular. Then of course I saw that its jaws were quite straight (checked them against the edge of a steel pocket ruler) and perfectly aligned. The next difference is its greater spring rate. Frankly though I don't think it needed a stiffer leaf spring than is on the regular clipper. Next I compared how the two worked. I can defnitely corroborate previous reports that the Tweezerman causes my largest toenail to make a relatively silent snapping sound. However, both clippers did an equally neat job. I'm going to hold onto the regular clipper for use on all but my big toe, because the curvature of its jaws is too small for that nail only.

column6: Maybelline New York Lip Studio Color Blur, 0.04 Ounce
column14: I have no idea how you're supposed to "blur" this lip color.  I tried using the blunt white end of the pencil to do this and the color won't move at all.  I got the lightest color and it's still quite bright and vivid.  It doesn't work like Maybelline is claiming.  It's basically a matte pencil and that's all.  It also doesn't last very long on the lips and it tends to sink into fine lines easily.  It's easily wiped off with a tissue and leaves behind no stain or color.  I'm not impressed with it at all.  It's just OK, nothing special.  I prefer a sheer lip balm look but of course lip balms don't last but 10 minutes, so when I saw the ad for this product, I was intrigued because it looked like I could feather the color and it would look more like a stain.  Not so!  Once applied, it sets very quickly and won't budge.  I've tried to work with it several times, to no avail and the blending end of the pencil is bulky and imprecise.  Granted, it wasn't expensive, but not only is the color far too bright for me and makes me look like a cartoon character, the formula doesn't lend itself to blending at all.  I wasted my $10!!  Save your money and buy one of the Nars Velvet Matte lip pencils.  The color payoff is gorgeous and the formula really lasts.  Plus, there are light, natural looking shades for those of us who don't want to look like caricatures.

column6: Paul Mitchell Super Skinny Serum, 5.1 Ounce
column14: I like this serum and used it for years.  Until I discovered that there was a much less expensive option with almost exactly the same ingredients.  Got2B Shine Serum is $5 and works just as well, if not better, than this Paul Mitchell serum.  I apply a small amount to clean damp hair and work it through the midlengths and ends.  Then, without adding any more product, I smooth the top of my head, but avoiding the roots.  Got2B controls frizz, provides thermal protection and adds tons of shine.  After styling, I take a single drop and work it my palms and smooth it over my waves and touch up the ends.  This gives me additional shine and softness.  I used Paul Mitchell serum for a long time because it was one of the only silicone serums on the market at the time.  However, since then, there have been competing products in every price range.  One day I was in the drugstore and compared the ingredients of PM and Got2B and discovered they were almost identical.  So I saved my money and purchased Got2bB (which is made by Schwartzkopf) and have never looked back.  I've been using Got2B for years and it works perfectly.  It's an excellent heat shield and the shine is to die for.  So if you want to save money and are a smart shopper, buy Got2B instead.  Super Skinny Serum is excellent, but Got2B is the same damn thing!!

column6: Double Edge Safety Razor for a Smooth Wet Shave
column13: Flat black DE razor is very attractive.
column14:
Over a year ago, I discovered how awesome double edge razors are. Yes, there is a big learning curve, and you will cut yourself if you're not cautious, but the benefits of learning are immeasurable. By far the best thing is the results of using a DE razor, a super close shave without the razor burn. Second to that is the savings, blades range from 10¢ - 65¢. I've personally bought 100 blades for about $25, compared to cartridge replacement blades, it's a substantial savings.

This particular razor is a very unique color, I've only seen one other completely black DE razor and it costs around $80.
I used this razor yesterday, on my legs. The first thing I noticed is the subtle texture of the handle that really provided a decent grip in wet conditions. Secondly, the weight of this razor is nice, there is no need to use any amount of pressure when using it, just allow it to glide across the skin. *If you apply pressure, you will cut yourself.*

In a comparison to my Edwin Jagger, this razor is slightly more aggressive, meaning there is a bit more razor exposure and more reason for caution but not so much that I injured myself.

Overall, I'm really enjoying this razor. My only concern is how well the black paint is going to hold up over time. Will update if paint wears.

I received this product in exchange for my impartial opinion and honest review.

column14: I absolutely hate making a trip to the salon just for my eyebrows so I've been sampling different at home wax sets. This is by far the best. After having mine waxed by an "eyebrow specialist" and threaded, this is the least painful by far. I've seen reviews that say they are too small but I think they're just perfect. They are small enough so beginners won't make too much damage if they make a mistake. I went a full month without plucking just to see how these would work and they removed my thick hair with ease. The only suggestion is to not press down the strip too hard. I did on one pull and it left a tiny irritation. This wax is strong, you hardly have to put any pressure on the strip to remove the hair.

column6: Plant Therapy Coffee Essential Oil. 100% Pure, Undiluted, Therapeutic Grade. 30 ml (1 oz).
column14:
I love coffee. I love drinking it, I love cooking with it, I love the colors and especially the smell! Now that I have Plant Therapy's coffee oil I can have that great coffee aroma all day long without having to constantly brew it fresh!

Proper oil content is important when picking coffee beans, but I never knew that that oil could be distilled and obtained on its own! This oil is a rich dark color a bit lighter than a cup of black coffee. The scent is strong straight from the bottle but mellows out considerably once it's in my diffuser. column6: Shampoo for Oily Hair & Oily Scalp - Natural Dandruff Treatment for Women & Men - Hair Loss Products - Hair Strengthener - Itchy Scalp Treatment - Beautiful Hair Care - Clarifying Shampoo Sulfate Free
column13: Long thick hair loves this shampoo!
column14: Let's begin with my hair type. I have long dirty blonde hair (past my shoulders about 1/3 down my back) and it is thick thanks to my Italian blood. I love my hair but I hate how weighed down and greasy it gets after only one day. I just felt like no matter what shampoo I used my hair was never really clean. I bought this brand on a why not kind of whim and was honestly surprised at how small the bottle was. I have long hair, i am used to using a lot of shampoo! I read the directions and kind of laughed at the "quarter size" amount it suggested but I decided to do exactly as it said the first try. Surprisingly, the quarter size amount was enough! The first wash it only really suds a little and I didn't notice any tingling so I left it on for three min like it suggests then rinsed and got my quarter size amount again. Second time my hair suds like crazy! I mean, hair stand up on your head giant ball of suds crazy. I waited the three min again then rinsed and decided to skip conditioner just to see what happens. That is where we lost a star. I wish this product conditioned a little or had a conditioner made to match because my hair was a kind of a hassle to get though. HOWEVER, my hair felt TEN TIMES LIGHTER. It was like I had gotten 4 inches chopped off. I couldn't believe it! The next time I showered the same thing happened and it felt lighter again except this time I made sure to condition my ends. All in all, awesome. Gets the gunk out and you wont have that greasy, oily, itchy shine start to come for two or so days which is about when to shampoo again anyway! I will definitely buy this again and maybe I'll try a few of the conditioners.

column13: My face has never felt so soft!
column14: I usually just wash my face with cleanser and my hands and periodically use an exfoliant. I had used an Olay scrubber at one point, but it was nothing fabulous. My sister has a Clarisonic and has had good results with that, but it is out of my budget currently. This one seems well constructed and good quality.    This Pleasingcare sonic face cleaning brush comes nicely packaged with a charging cord, a travel pouch, a breathable cover to keep it clean between uses, and there is even a headband included in the box, which is a nice touch. The bristles are soft to the touch, not abrasive, which is important for my sensitive skin. The charger seems to just connect magnetically. There are 2 speeds of vibration depending on how you like it. I use the lower speed for my sensitive skin.    I have been using it for about a week now and I am noticing a difference. I think my complexion looks brighter. The biggest thing I notice is how my face FEELS. Not only does it feel cleaner, but it feels so soft and smooth after each use. I think it is helping my serums and moisturizer absorb better as well. I have no idea how it compares to a Clarisonic, but I hope this Pleasingcare sonic face cleaning brush lasts a good long while, because I really like it. column6: Lipogaine for Men Intensive Treatment and Complete Solution for Hair Loss/Thinning, 2 oz
column13: Much better than Rogaine and other Hair Growth Products
column14: I have tried a majority of the products on the market but I find that Lipogaine is simply the best for my hair. With Rogaine and some of the Minoxidil based products, they simply weren't strong enough to keep my hair growing after more than a year. The problem seemed to be that they simply did not have enough of the DHT inhibitors and other active ingredients necessary to keep my male pattern baldness from coming back and I would shed my new growth after a few months. With Lipogaine, I don't have the dry powdery feeling of basic minoxidil, nor do I have the thick, greasy feeling that I get with other mixtures or proprietary concoctions on the market. Lipogaine keeps my hair full looking and my new growth is sill in place, well after 18 months of continuous use and I don't get the itchy feeling that I used to get with solutions that didn't effectively block the DHT in my scalp. Lipogaine also doesn't stain my pillow while I sleep at night which was another problem that I had with other products in the past. With Lipogaine, I love seeing my fuller, thinker hair in the mirror and I no longer have that regretful feeling anymore, wishing there was something on the market that worked. Lipogaine works for me!

column14: My 4 year old had somehow developed a severe nail biting habit, seemingly overnight. He had already kicked the habit of gum picking which has permanently damaged his oral health but he did it for so long... I needed to get the nail biting under control. I heard about this product from another parent (I am a pediatrician...) and decided to try it. As with any "quit" you need to be motivated, so we set a quit date for nail biting and we all decided together ... no one could have "hands in mouth" in our family from here on. So the product... It is gross. It takes hours to get the bitter taste out of your mouth. I tried it before I put it on my son. It worked immediately. We used it 4 weeks and now just at random to ensure compliance. It says every other day, we started every day and the last 2 times it was about every other week. The memory of grossness must be motivating... No more nail biting, no hands in mouth... Yay!  I used it on myself out of solidarity.

column6: The Honest Company Honest Sunscreen Lotion SPF 30 2-pack 3.0oz
column13: Product failure, needs to be recalled
column14:
My review below is the letter I sent directly to Honest Co regarding the failure of this product:

"My wife has been purchasing Honest Co diapers, wipes, hand sanitizer, and body wash/shampoo for the last couple years. We have been nothing but pleased with those products and stopped buying competing natural products because of our satisfaction.

This satisfaction came to an abrupt and very dangerous halt this last weekend when we tried your SPF 30 sunscreen at a Texas Gulf beach. Your product was applied on my wife, four children (7 down to 5 months), and myself. We applied and then waited before getting in the water, and then reapplied before going back in the water after lunch. We used a different brand natural product on our faces with the same application frequency. By that evening it was very clear that your sunscreen did virtually nothing to protect me and my family from the sun, and each one of us has varying degrees of severe sunburns. In stark contrast, the other brand product used on our faces protected us completely leaving no evidence that we had spent the day in the sun. Now three days later I have blisters on my back from the burns.

It is hard to express the anger, frustration and disappointment we have been feeling due to your product's failure. We have tried very hard to protect our children outdoors as we are aware of scientific research indicating the significant increase in cancer risk for each severe sunburn received as a child.

Your product failed, and after experiencing severe sunburns while using your product, our online research makes it very clear that countless others have been harmed due to your negligence.

This product should be recalled, pulled from shelves and online marketplaces immediately. No more, "we use it on our children" garbage that you believe may protect you from litigation as you avoid taking responsibility for this failure. In reviewing your company values, itis clear to me that you are not acting on your principles regarding honesty, service, outperform, and sustaining (not harming) life. This product is having the opposite result. I repeat, recall this product now!"

column6: Taylor of Old Bond Street Shaving Cream Bowl 150g 5.3-Ounce
column13: Awesome stuff! Don't hedge on buying this because of the cost, it is worth every penny.
column14:
The difference between this product and cream-in-a-can from the drug store or grocery store is like the difference between an off the rack suit and a hand tailored suit. I ordered this as my second "wet shave" cream during my transition from wasting money on razors every month to the more sustainable and less expensive life long habit of shaving with a straight razor. I've since ordered a couple other creams but this is still by far my favorite.

Between the straight razor and this shaving cream I realized what I've been missing out on what it comes to shaving for almost four decades now: I'm supposed to enjoy shaving.

I used to go to a barber to get my head shaved with a razor once in a while; taking time to shave with such a luxurious product feels a bit like that but I'm in my own home. A little dab of this stuff on a brush will cover your entire head so I'm guessing the one package I bought will last at least three or four months of every day-ish use. If you don't shave your head then it will last you even longer.

And not surprisingly, this higher quality item will actually end up costing you less money in the long term. Totally worth the money.

column6: Stretch Marks & Scars Cream – Best for Stretch Mark Removal - Body Moisturizer for Prevention and Reduction of Old & New Scars - Natural & Organic for Pregnancy, After Birth, Women, & Men
column14:
I'm not convinced that anything can actually get rid of stretch marks completely. I've had some yo-yoing weight (first I gained a lot, then lost a lot--I'm now just working on keeping it off) and this cream faded the very, *very* deep marks on my stomach 50-60%. They're so much lighter now that I wouldn't be able to see them if I was looking at them in the mirror across the room. I may buy another jar to see if it continues to fade the marks, but I'm reasonably impressed with this so far.

It also doesn't "wear off" like some other creams I've tried--once the marks have faded, they're faded for good. I ran out of my jar two weeks ago and they look the same as they did on the last day I applied it. It also works great on scars--I've had a road rash scar on my arm since I was a kid, and it's nearly gone now.

column6: NIP+FAB Energy Boost Body Lotion 490ml/16.6oz
column13: Great lotion with a zesty, tart fragrance.
column14: I really like this lotion.  It's lighter consistency makes it perfect for the Florida summer and the tangy lemon fragrance is fresh and bright.  It does do a nice job of moisturizing and it doesn't leave skin tacky and sticky, like so many lotions do.  I also have the companion body wash, which is wonderful as well.  I purchased these two products for $6 apiece at TJ Maxx because I really loved the fragrance.  I'm a bit of a shower gel/lotion product junkie and these two products were a nice addition to my collection.  The lotion is not heavy and is the perfect weight for hot weather days.  It sinks in immediately and leaves a nice soft sheen on the skin.  It's a rather large bottle, I'm happy to say, so I'll have plenty to use through the dog days of summer.  The lemon scent is tangy and tart but it dissipates quickly.  I can definitely say that smelling that fragrance surely does give me an emotional boost and makes me ready to face the coming day's events.  This is my first experience with this brand and I have to say I'm really impressed so far.  However, I don't know if I'm ready to pay the full price for these products.  I'll decide that once I reach the bottom of the bottles, lol!  But all in all, I'm pleased with my discount purchase and look forward to using these products up.  I definitely recommend them to anyone who likes a zesty, tangy fragrance.

column6: Wahl Chrome Pro 24 pc Haircut Kit #79524-2501
column14:
It's hard to beat this hair cutting kit for the price. You get more attachements and combs than you'll ever need, a cleaning brush and a small container of oil. We get better cleaning results using a can of compressed air instead of that little brush. The supply of oil included is sparse; one might want to buy a bottle of Wahl oil on Amazon or elswhere. It's not expensive and should last a long, long time.

This Wahl cutter is not unpleasantly loud and cuts cleanly without pulling. The self sharpening blades work as well as advertised. A cordless clipper gives one more flexibility and mobility, but a corded unit like the Wahl 79524-2501 has an adequately lengthed cord, more power than a cordless, and no waiting time for a charge.

I'd definitely recommend this Wahl hair cutting kit.

I had a minor issue and the support was great. 2015-08-12 US 175346 R16G9PZTEFCP87 B006840FE8 188451442 Beauty Blender Pure Blender Sponge - White - 0.15 oz Beauty 3 2 2 N Y Weirdly delicate, but performs well I bought this because it was slightly cheaper than the original pink blender and was touted to be better for sensitive skin, with the added benefit of zero dye bleeding. The blender looks extremely small in the packaging, which by the way was dented and looked used (though the blender inside was unmarked). However, when you use it damp, it expands slightly and looks like the proper size when placed against the face.

The blender performs as described and is great for blending away concealer, foundation, and cream makeup of all colors. I find that it gives me a much more natural finish than using a brush, and is also easier to clean than bristles. (I clean mine every 2 days of use and just use regular cleanser and water. Most of the stains come out this way, though you won't be able to avoid deeper stains over time. ALSO - be sure to air dry them before storing them!! THIS IS HOW THE MOLD GROWS.) I haven't tried traveling with it yet, but it's compact enough that I don't think it'll give me any problems.

The worst part about the blender is that it doesn't hold its shape. Mine came out a little dented and after the first wash (I squeezed it as gently as I could when wringing it out), the teardrop shape quickly became warped. It still works fine, but the blender wasn't as sturdy as I thought. Keep this in mind when you're handling the sponge. (I took off 2 stars for the crappy state it was in --personal experience-- and how easily it gets damaged.)

Bottom line: if you're not sure about splurging on the original, try out the white one. Just be sure to be gentle with it! column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column13: and I couldn't be any happier. I have been a longtime user of Braun ...
column14: I received the Braun 9090cc from BzzAgent , and I couldn't be any happier. I have been a longtime user of Braun electric razors, I currently used a series 5. It did a great job but the advantages the series 9 offers are really impressive. The series 9 is quick charging and it gives the most comfortable and extremely close shave I have ever had and that includes all electric and disposable blade razors. It doesn't matter which direction the hair is growing one pass is all it takes. The series 9 has a digital readout a floating head that can be locked in 5 different positions, and the razor is waterproof so it can be rinsed off under the tap. The series 9 also has a pop up trimmer for sideburns beards and it comes with the new clean and renew station. The clean and renew station basically tells you when to clean and then you have a fresh clean shaver after every cycle. It may be a little louder than the previous cleaning station but nothing to cause concern. This new 9090cc definitely rates 5 stars.

column13: For the price, it is a bargain.
column14:
At less than $5 a jar, St. Ives Facial Moisturizer, Timeless Skin Collagen Elastin is quite a bargain. Using it occassionally on my face, nearly daily on my feet and after a month or so I have not hit the bottom of the jar yet.

Be warned that the "light" fragrance is very strong when you initially open the container. I've noticed that the scent has faded (my smell sensitive daughter told me it "doesn't stink so bad" now) as the weeks have passed.

My biggest complaint is that the cream is so slick that it slides off my fingers before I can get it on my skin. Surprisingly, it does not leave an oily residue, the scent quickly fades and even with my sensitive skin and mixing this with magnesium chloride oil does not break out my face, nor anywhere else I put it (feet! this plus mag oil has my feet looking and feeling a couple decades younger!)

Decent product, great price, will probably reorder it as it works great on my feet and hands.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column14:
I received this shaver as a promotion from Braun. I'm not giving it praise for this reason, however. I'm not afraid to give a critical review for products I receive from manufacturers. This shaver deserves a good review, though!

I usually use a safety razor, but I am always intrigued by electric shavers. Every razor and shaver I have used disappoints me because I am spoiled by my safety razor. The Braun Series 9 is finally a great alternative for me!

I used the first Braun Series shaver with self-cleaning features years ago. I must say that the Braun Series 9 is much better. I have a beard, but I do shave the area from where my chin meets my neck downwards. As you know, this is a difficult place to shave because the hair grows upwards and sometimes in other directions. I found that I had to use several passes to get all of the hair the first time I used it, but I did have a few days of growth, so I cannot blame the shaver.

What I know, though, is that the shaver does need to learn my facial hair and skin. The second day I used it, the shave did a better job of cutting the hair. It still struggled just a touch with grabbing some of the hairs. I found that I really needed to pull my skin tight and move the shavers in multiple directions to get some of the longer-length stragglers.

As I use the shaver more, it gets easier to use, which is really kind of amazing. For the first time, I have a shaver that doesn't give me bumps!

Tips:
1. Definitely follow the directions and shave before you wash your face. The oils on your face help the shaver to glide. My skin gets irritated if I shave after a shower and the shaver doesn't glide as well across my face.
2. Be careful of longer hair. I had a few times where the shaver grabbed the longer beard hairs and pulled on them painfully.
3. Trim down longer hairs before using the shaver in order to get a closer shave
4. Follow the directions and pull your skin tight to get the best shave with the fewest passesn tight to get the best shave with the fewest passes

column13: worse, made my hands sting with pain due to ...
column14: I started using this product decades ago when I was working as a nurse's aide in nursing homes, hence very frequent hand-washing with cold water on rough paper towels, often in cold weather out east, USA. This gave me very dry hands with micro-cracks.  Most lotions I tried felt greasy, didn't help much or, worse, made my hands sting with pain due to the micro-cracks. Finally found this.  Worked very well, no greasy feeling, no pain, and fragrance free.  Even if you aren't allergic to fragrances, it's nice not to smell something when you put your hands near your face to eat something. I became impossible to find the fragrance free version on store shelves, but thankfully it's still made and I found it online.  I recommend this to everyone I see who picks up a bottle of hand lotion, and in the nursing world, that's a lot of people. I would also put some into a small bottle that I could carry in my pocket to use anytime: used empty "trial size" plastic bottles with screw tops so that none would leak out in my pocket or purse.

column13: Durable and attractive ring, easy to clean, ideal for situations that are tough on your hands
column14:
I am a historic preservationist and work on construction sites quite frequently and do a great deal of cemetery repair. One of my problems is though that I wear a number of rings daily and the kind of work I do isn't the best situation for fine jewelry. I don't wish to injure them, which such hard work often does, but if I don't wear them, my fingers feel incredibly naked. When I heard about silicone rings, I thought it was a great idea and I was excited to see how they worked for me. I thought that this ring would be a marvelous solution.

I ended up choosing the red band. It arrived in a plastic envelop with a little card inside with the company logo and some information on the ring. The band is only slightly rounded, not as thick as some, which means that it doesn't feel bulky. The sizing is perfection. It's a very attractive shade of red (not too orange but not fire engine red either) and it's easily cleaned. I've worn it to my work sites a number of times now and it's taken every pounding and still looks brand new. It's really durable and it saves my good rings. Very happy with this!

I received this silicone ring at a discount in exchange for a genuine critique

column14:
Packaged in a generous 4 ounce white plastic tub. Cream is very thick and white, no smell at all. I read the ingredients, was instantly impressed and opened it up and tried it on my elbows. My elbows are dry and they get easily irritated almost to the point of cracking in winter. Summers they are just super dry normally. Wish I could take a picture of my elbow but I can't. I am posting a picture of the ingredient list as I could not find it anywhere advertised and they are fantastic.

I get easily irritated on my chest area between breasts after a bad sunburn years ago, (when I was a lot younger). I just always have little red raised bumps that itch no matter what I do. I started using this in this area 3 days ago, twice a day with normal face skin care since I was using it on my face also. As of tonight the area is clear as possible, not a mark one and no itch at all, completely perfect and it has not been this way is 15 years. The Manuka Honey is a miracle ingredient. In the medical field I have seen it used for diabetics with ulcers that were thought to be beyond hope and it healed them right up sometimes. Seen it used on severe burns. Manuka Honey has so many uses and healing properties.

Now for my face, it feels wonderful, soft smooth, radiant, healthy, no irritation. This stuff is gentle enough for a baby and I am just betting it would make an awesome diaper rash cream also. If you have any skin problems that nothing else has worked, I would really recommend you so try this. I will be buying more I know by winter, just wished it came in a bigger tub as I am going to have a lot of uses for it.

column6: Remington D8700 T|Studio PROtect Dryer, Aquatic Green
column13: Multi-Feature, Great Styling Results - Don't be Deterred by the Size
column14:
I've used this blow dryer a few times now and am very impressed. It has two speeds and three heat settings, along with a cool shot. When the weather gets this hot and humid in the summer, it seems I get warm and sweaty when blowing my hair dry, even in central air. That's where the lower heat settings are really enjoyed. Even at the highest setting, my scalp doesn't get too hot, but I really like the cooler settings. Even in the lower heat settings, my hair seemed to dry fairly fast, but more importantly, it seemed softer and more easily styled with a round brush than with my other blow dryers. My hair is fine and very straight, so this is a bonus. I haven't used the other features, so I can't review those at this point.

Despite the relatively large size in comparison to most blow dryers, this one is surprisingly light. Between having small hands and my hand strength having declined from both age and the way I was affected by Lyme Disease before detection, I notice this and if I can handle the blow dryer, I think most adults would have no difficulty. The volume when in operation is fairly moderate - nothing as loud as you might think.

One little feature that I find handy is the little hook at the base of the handle near the cord, which allows you to hang it on a hook.

Overall, don't be deterred by the large size unless storage space is an issue. This is a really nice blow dryer and if it holds up as well as an older Remington model we've had for years, we'll be very happy.

column13: It burns, it's foamy, but it works.
column14:
I'm unfortunately predisposed to cavities because of my deep tooth grooves. The Listerine Total Care, along with using my Sonicare brush, has finally given me 2 cavity free dentist visits.

To join the chorus of other comments, this stuff absolutely burns and produces an abundance of foam. I started off with the original total care Listerine, and switched to this. My tongue and mouth were on FIRE, and I was so confused by the foam. Read the ingredients, and a lightbulb went off when I saw the peroxide. I eventually became used to the burn, but even time doesn't totally take away the burn. It is all worth it though, as this stuff works.

Not only has this contributed to less cavities, but it has brightened my smile significantly! I have been using a whitening toothpaste for years and they didn't help as much as I wanted. This mouthwash definitely helped using it at least 1x a day, and my teeth are so much brighter. As others have stated, this works well as a combination regimen. I think you'll see optimum results using this with a whitening toothbrush as well as lessening the consumption of staining food/drink.

I hope Listerine never stops making this!

I tried out my pedicure tool on my worst callus first, one that has been there since I was a kid from an injury. After I got all the dead skin off, I used some coconut oil to keep the skin soft. I love that my feet don't look like it's summer, and I can stay looking nice in my sandals. column6: Suavecito Pomade
column13: Great Pomade! Styles Great, All Day Hold, Washes Out Easily!
column14:
I love this pomade! I've tried a lot of pomades, some petroleum based and some water based. I love the hold and look of the petroleum based, but getting it out is a PAIN!

After trying lots of water based pomades, Suavecito is know the one I buy over and over again. I usually keep both the regular and firme on hand. It goes in my hair easy and comes out even easier. For my hair style, I find that adding it to my slightly damp hair and then styling works best for me and gives me the sheen I like. I get a great all day hold and don't even bother carrying a comb with me. The only down side of going with the water based pomade for me is that if you live in a rainy climate (like I do!) then a good rain can be disasterous for your hair. I've never had much luck re-style my hair with water based pomades, so if it looks like it is raining I do what I can to protect the hair.

The only reason I didn't give Suavecito 5 stars is because I'm not really a huge fan of the scent. It isn't terrible by any means, but I would prefer a "fresher" or "tropical" scent. Suavecito has more of an Old Spice scent. I don't find the scent too overpowering though, so it doesn't deter me from buying again.

I would definitely recommend trying this product if you are on the fence or just looking for a new pomade to try.

column6: Veet VTSH8705 Touchably Smooth Mains Epilator
column14:
Okay, I was really skeptical and hesitant about using an epilator for the first time. The concept is kind of like waxing, but rather than ripping your hair mostly all at once, this little gadget painstakingly plucks out each follicle one by one in really quick succession. I usually shave, so I haven’t had the painful experience of going through what sounds like a torturous experience. Sometimes I tweeze, but it’s just not the same.

Veet’s VTSH8705 Touchably Smooth Corded Epilator is simple to use, and I was fortunate to get this at a promotional discount for testing and review. The instructions they include are easy to follow and all the accessories include are self-explanatory. I charged the epilator for a few hours and took a warm shower before using it, which was a suggestion in the manual since your skin pores would be opened after getting wet.

I decided to try my underarms first, and lightly swiped the area of interest. The experience was a bit painful but really, it’s not nearly as bad as I thought it would be. I think you became acclimated with the painful sensation. I heard from regular epilator users that over time, you get used to the feeling of epilating and it no longer is as painful as the first time.

Granted, epilating seems to take a lot longer than shaving for me, but the results are cleaner, smoother, and more pronounced. It also takes longer for your whole hair follicle to grow back. I think the results may be worth it. There were a couple of stray small hairs that the epilator couldn’t get, so I used a tweezer to get those, but there weren’t that many.

Cleaning the epilator is like cleaning your razor, but without the sharp blades. The product comes with a little brush that you can use to brush the hair out of the cracks as well as the charging adapter. I do like how this epilator comes with two types of head attachment covers, one for smaller areas, and one for larger areas, as well as a cap for hygienic purposes. It also comes with a pre-epilation comfort spray that I used for my legs. I’m not sure how it’s supposed to feel with you’re using this on your legs, but I think it has made my experience less painful than it could be. Maybe I’ll try it without next time to see if it makes a difference.

Overall, I am satisfied with the results of this epilator by Veet. I will definitely keep using it and will update if anything about the gadget changes over time.for hygienic purposes. column6: Aveeno Skin Relief Moisturizing Lotion for Sensitive Skin
column13: Product formulation has been changed, not for the better
column14: Aveeno has apparently changed the formula for this product, which is not necessarily a 'good thing'. The main reason I loved this product was the amount of shea butter (Butyrospermum parkii) in the listed inactive ingredients (#5), and that water was the last inactive ingredient listed. The active ingredient in the pictured product is Dimethicone 1.3%. The amount in the product is 1.2%. The 'inactive ingredients' are listed in a different order on the product I received, as well. I believe the FDA requires the ingredients to be listed in order of highest concentration first. The first 'inactive ingredient' on the pictured product is Avena Sativa (oat) kernel extract. The first 'inactive ingredient' on the product I received is water, and shea butter is now #12. The formulation is obviously different,and the product is definitely not as effective as it was. The packaging is slightly different, as well, but still listed as Aveeno Active Naturals Skin Relief

column14:
I wore braces many years ago. When i got them off in 1991, my orthodontist put permanent retainers behind my upper and lower teeth to prevent movement over the years (in addition to retainers I wear at night). I started using these Super floss when i got my braces on and now 24 years after having them off, I STILL use them for my permanent retainers.
I have tried the other brands and frankly they suck. They are too thick and my teeth are still just as they were when I got the braces off, so i need these to get between without issues.

You can hardly find them anymore in stores, so i am glad that Amazon carries them!

column13: OK as a detangler, but strong synthetic perfume and little value-add overall
column14:
This works quite well as a detangler and shine spray. However, something to be aware of is the incredibly strong synthetic fragrance. I'm blown away that anyone likes it. It's so strong that a little on your hair is enough to drown out your perfume. And it lasts! It's there until you next wash your hair. It wouldn't be so bad if it wasn't so sickly - perhaps a poor chemical attempt at Ylang Ylang?
Oddly, I also find that it causes my fine hair to have more static, which my Sebastian shine spray does not do.
One more minor niggle is that it's a bit if a rort calling it an Argan oil product when Argan oil is a very minor ingredient. It's mostly silicones, as you'd expect for a shine spray. But hey.
Personally, I will not repurchase it because of the strong sickly fragrance.

column13: With Great Power Comes Great Responsibilty
column14: At first I thought this was one of the best products that I have ever purchased. I am a young male with some nice curly hair, but I just wanted to slick it back. Well this gel held it perfectly, but with only one issue..... I looked too good. I couldn't go out to the bars anymore without getting swamped by women. At first this was a cool experience, I never had to buy drinks anymore. However, too much of a good thing can become a bad thing. This gel turned me into a self-centered, egocentric male that started to lose most of my friends. I got so caught up in my hair and how well the gel was working I left my family and friends behind me. One day I looked in the mirror and realized the slick back was not worth it. I tried countless times to give up this lifestyle, but it had consumed me. If there was gel in the house, I was putting it in my hair. I talked to people and eventually went to some therapy. I finally decided that my only option was to shave my hair and get rid of these cursed curls. I am now sitting here, writing this review as a warning to all of the other potential buyers out there to use this gel with caution. I am working on building back my relationships, but it is a slow process. I can only hope my friends and family will one day take me back and I can earn their trust once again.

column6: Remington PF7400 F4 Comfort Series Foil Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver, Black
column13: Decent. Simple. But not as good as my Braun
column14:
"It's okay" really sums it up.

I alternate between a triple blade razor and electric during the week. I like the close shave of blades, but my electric is much easier on my skin. I've tried multiple brands, but keep going back to Braun as I find their electric razors give me the closest shave. I won't say which model I'm using now, because comparing it to the Remington F4 is a bit like comparing a Porsche Cayenne to a Volkswagen Golf.

Still: The Remington F4 is inexpensive and does work. It's easy to operate and is relatively quiet (not any quieter than my current electric, but no noisier.) The channeled double-foil head does bring to mind the quality of pricier shavers.

That said, I didn't get as close of a shave as I'd hoped for. Plus, the "Intercept Shaving Technology" that's supposed to pre-trim longer hairs appeared to ignore longer hairs as often as it trimmed them. Speaking of trimming, I found that the pop-up detail trimmer (for side burns, beards, mustaches) pops up at an odd angle and in an odd position. The way it pops up makes the body of the shaver block my view of the detail trimmer; making it nearly impossible to see the details I'm trimming. Defeats the purpose, in my opinion.

If you're looking to have an "emergency" shaver in case your go-to konks out, perhaps this might be a decent choice.

column6: OZNaturals Facial Sunscreen  This Anti Aging SPF 30, Broad Spectrum, Mineral Sunscreen with Zinc Oxide Will Help You Keep That Healthy Youthful Glow!
column13: A truly disappointing and expensive CHEMICAL sunscreen being sold as a \natural\" product."
column14:
DISAPPOINTED! OZ "Naturals" new sunscreen is loaded with a lot of cheap CHEMICALS and is being sold at a ridiculously high price. Their old sunscreen's active ingredients were Zinc and Titanium. That product contained mostly natural ingredients. This one has very little "natural" about it. The main ingredient is Octyl Methoxycinnamate. Pure chemical, not natural, and may be toxic. Do research. The rest of this product is loaded with chemical fillers and "goop" that you would expect to see in cheap supermarket or big box store brands. One such example is PVP (Polyvinylpyrrolidone) more commonly known as "liquid plastic" - not something I'm delighted to put on my skin and not something I would expect in a product from a so-called "natural" skin care company.

Lastly, price. OUCH! They made this product 1 ounce smaller (3oz vs 4oz) and increased the price from $17.49 to $21.49! YIKES!

I have purchased several OZ products in the past and have been very pleased. This shocks me. I am going to think twice and check twice before purchasing anything from this company again.

Here is a TRUE ingredient list of this product: Octyl Methoxycinnamate 7.5%, Zinc Oxide 7.0%, Deionized Water, Stearyl Alcohol, Glycerin, Glyceryl Stearate, PEG-100 Stearate, Glyceryl Dilaurate, Cetearyl Alcohol, Beeswax, Dimethicone, Cyclomethicone, Diisopropyl Adipate, Hexylene Glycol, PEG-40 Stearate, C12-15, Alkyl Benzoate, Aluminum Starch Octenylsuccinate, PEG-20, Carnauba wax, Dimethicone Copolymer, PVP/Eicosene, Copolymer, Sorbitan Tristearate, Stearoxytrimethylsilane, Steareth-100, Laureth-7, C13-14 Isoparaffin, Phenoxyethanol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Polyacrylamide.

column6: L'Oreal Paris EverCreme Sulfate-Free Moisture System Cleansing Conditioner, 8.3 fl. Oz.
column14:
Unlike a lot of reviews on here, I have never tried Wen. I can, however, say that without having a hair cut in over a year aside from 1/8 of an inch here and there, my hair was in desperate need of some TLC. I have to hairspray it into a pony tail in order to avoid the frizz, and wearing it down just isn't an option because pieces of my hair were wavy and others are straight.

I tried this once. Straight out of the shower, after wearing my hair in an unkempt purposely messy pony tail/bun full of product, I was able to run a brush through my wet hair just once without hitting a single tangle. I took it out of my pony tail today and it had the smoothest wave to it (the waves were all around from a twisted pony tail). It was shiny, I could run my fingers through it, and I had it in a pony tail without a single spritze of hair spray.

Other reviewers said they had to use a lot of product, but I trusted one reviewer that said it isn't necessary because you shouldn't expect a huge lather. That reviewer was right. I used maybe 3-4 pumps and that was more than enough for my armpit length hair.

Other reviewers mentioned that it's an overwhelming smell. I think what they're smelling is a lack of perfume in the product. This is a soft, clean smell. So many of us are used to picking something off a shelf, doing a sniff test and not even looking at what a product does before handing over our credit cards. I was smelling my hair all day and it was wonderful. I even got weird and asked my coworker to smell it.

I'm so excited to have found something that keeps my summer hair in check and already after one use makes it feel healthier. For the price, I love it. For not having to purchase it at an overpriced beauty store like sephora or ulta, I love it even more. L'oreal easily could have charged double for something of this quality. I don't think it will be long before this becomes the product every beauty blogger starts talking about!

column14: This lip stain does as it says. The reason I gave only three stars is as follows- Ease of application is a little difficult and takes some practice. It's very thick and sticky, you have to apply it quickly because if you contiue to touch it throughout application, the gloss starts to dry and peels up off the lip if you apply it too thinly and then try to add more. It's difficult to apply the right amount, quickly and neatly at the same time. With practice, it gets easier. Secondly, the colors could be better. column6: ToLB Vitamin C Serum for Face with Hyaluronic Acid - Anti Aging Anti Wrinkle Facial Serum with Natural Ingredients - Paraben Free, Vegan - Best Vitamin C with Hyaluronic Acid Serum for Skin - 1 fl oz
column13: Makes my skin look better right away
column14:
As a product tester I compare dozens of skin care products, and I've arrived at a list of key considerations from fragrance to long-term results. I hope these are helpful to you!
~ Fragrance: Hard to place - smells like cinnamon with undertones of witch hazel. No added fragrance.
~ Color and texture: Slightly cloudy tan color. It’s thin, but has a gel feel going on.
~ Feel during application: Slippery and moist.
~ Feel after absorption: Smooth, soft.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: I’d clear it for all types. Not oily or drying. I have very sensitive skin which cannot tolerate some Vitamin C serums, but this one is fine.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: Amber glass bottle with glass squeeze dropper.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Skin is visibly smoother and there is a noticeable reduction in depth of fine wrinkles. This is what got it its five-star rating.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Vitamin C and hyaluronic acid are the mainstays of this serum. These will both help your skin long-term. I would say this tilts towards the cosmetic and recommend it for immediate results, but would suggest finding something to use with it that contains more active ingredients.
~ Other notes: This exact formula seems to be marketed under a number of brand names including this one, Elleda, and Majestic Pure.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

column13: THIS IS DEFINITELY THE BEST FACE WASH FOR DRY SENSITIVE SKIN. PLEASE DON'T SKIP BY MY REVIEW,  IT IS A MUST READ
column14: My skin is extremely sensitive and very dry. Many products, not only, dry my skin, they burn and cause redness. I an fearful of introducing new face care products. After reading the reviews, I decided to chance it, and purchase Paul's Choice Skin Recovery. As I washed my face for the first time using this product, I was stunned and amazed! There was absolutely no burning or stinging. What even further surprised  me, was there was absolutely no irritation such as burning, stinging, tearing or bloodshot eyes when used to remove eye makeup. I'll not say this product made my skin 'as soft as a baby's behind.' However, my skin was softer and smoother than the garage sale items in the dreaded bathroom drawer. For the average working woman, Paul's Choice is on the pricey side. However, when computing the garage sale items lying dormant in the dreaded bathroom drawer, this is a steal. I am so impressed with this face wash, that after two weeks of use, I ordered a second bottle. Bear in mind, this is not a minature bottle, it is a large bottle, and will probably last me three months or more. A little of this cleaner goes a long way. I hope they never discontinue it. If given advanced notice that they are discontinuing this item, I will request they ship me a 55 gallon drum. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact me.

column14: I used my first bottle because I was trying to rid a single "wrinkle" that appeared under my eye after what I believe was due to a rash I had around my eyes.  Initially I thought it was working or at least "filling" the crease daily, once in the morning and once at night.  I started noticing after application and adding my daily toner/moisturiser (Cetaphil cream) my face would start flaking once I put on my Neutrogena sunscreen.  It looked as if I had dead skin everywhere, but it was merely the mixture gelling together creating an annoying flaky mess I would need to wipe off.  The exact same would occur if I didn't apply the sunscreen and used my BB cream.  So in the end, I would suggest not combining anything other than your daily toner/moisturiser with your Yeouth serum.

column6: Remington WR5100 Women's Rotary Shaver, Pink
column14: The first thing my wife said to me was, "I don't know about electronics in the shower."  Of course that was not a problem at all.  Be sure to charge it up for a full day and you are sure to get almost an hour of run time out of it.  That's about 4-5 days.  My wife liked how the pivoting head hit all the contours of her leg without nicks or cuts.  She liked how you could shave dry, wet, or with cream/lotion.  The pop up trimmer is a nice addition.  What she didn't like was the cut.  It's not a close as a razor.  The Remington WR5100 is a great concept, but cannot compete with the closeness of a razor cut, or the quickness of a razor cut.  You really have to take you time with the Remington to get a good close shave and you will still feel stubble.
