column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Good for maintenance, but not exclusively
column14:
I tried the Crest 3D White Brilliance 2 part system after receiving a sample from Crest. I've used some of their other whitening products in the past, such as white strips and whitening mouthwash, but was excited to try this new system.

Part 1 is a simple toothpaste. The flavor is not as minty as other Crest products I've used, but it's not bad. It feels a little bit gritty in your mouth and doesn't get very foamy, but it does leave my teeth feeling very clean.

Part 2 is the whitening solution. If you've used any teeth whitening agent in the past you'll recognize the flavor immediately-- it's a little chemically and not super pleasant. I avoid tasting this by just brushing on the front of my teeth that you can see (why do I need bright white molars, right!?). Be careful when you brush this on because it can cause sensitivity and redness in your gums.

When I first started using the product I followed the recommendation of brushing with this twice daily. This was too much for my gums. They became sore and sensitive, and even bled from the whitening solution. I've started using this product every other day and am not experiencing those sensitivities anymore.

Despite the unpleasantness of parts of the whitening process, I really am happy with the results. I feel like this product leaves my teeth feeling polished and shiny. I'd much rather do minor maintenance daily than use whitening strips for 30 minutes per day. This is good for maintenance, rather than trying to start whitening your teeth from your natural stained color. I think if you were to use a product like white strips, this toothpaste system would be an easy way to keep up your brilliant white smile.

column6: Aloe Vera Gel – 99.75% Pure, Organic Aloe Vera Skin Care – Two 4 oz Bottle for Acne, Razor Burn, Bug Bites – Irritated, Dry or Sunburned Skin -
column13: Works wonders and has many uses!
column14:
This is the closet you will get to real Aloe Vera! It does not have any chemical smell, and smells really fresh.

I have had some really good results with this gel. The best thing is it can be used for multiple things! Here are some usage tips from the creators:

- Hair gel. Believe it or not, even though our aloe is not very thick, it makes a great light hair gel! One note, if you apply it when your hair is dry, it won't make much difference. If you apply it when your hair is wet, you will be surprised at how well it actually works to hold your hair. Try it, you may be pleasantly surprised.

- Dry skin can be really annoying and sometimes embarrassing. Sometimes a little aloe will alleviate that problem. It’s not always the case, totally depends on the person and the skin (and not to mention what the cause is…). Apparently some have had such dry skin it was even cracking. They applied our aloe Vera gel and it got rid of the problem!

- Itchy scalp! Yeah, it’s not really a moisturizer but somehow, when massaged in your scalp, it can relieve itchiness! We can’t say if it helps dandruff yet but at least it can help get rid of that horrible need to scratch.

- Our aloe makes a wonderful aftershave. We are planning to create an aftershave in the future but for now, we have found that it really helps to soothe the skin and get rid of razor bumps and razor burn. If you have sensitive skin, we think you will be especially happy with this as an aftershave. This includes you ladies!

- Another one that we have found more recently, it makes a good base before putting on your makeup. After you wash your face, apply the aloe to your face and let it absorb. Then go about your normal makeup routine. You may just find that your face feels better, more hydrated and smooth.

- Hate those annoying, itchy bug bites? Especially those mosquitos or fleas? Well, put our Aloe Vera gel on there and see the difference. We have found that it will take away the irritation and itching (and even burning for those of you who really react!)! It may take 2 or 3 applications, but since our aloe absorbs so quickly, you can do those applications in just minutes and be done! This is really good for use on children, including young babies since it has no fragrances or anything else to harm them!

- Acne is a problem that plagues many people, young and old(er). Aloe Vera is amazing at rejuvenating the skin. It also happens to be non comedogenic (doesn't clog the pores). So you can put it on your face and it will help heal those blemishes.

- Have a burn? Afraid it might scar? Try a poultice. This is an old recipe I heard about recently. Try crushing fresh carrots and mixing it with our Aloe Vera (carrots have a high content of vitamin E so the combination with the aloe works wonders). Wrap it around the burned area and remove when you see the mixture getting dry (or sooner if you want). Repeat frequently. You might be amazed.

- On the subject of burns, particularly minor ones. If you managed to burn yourself doing something, cooking, starting a fire in the fire place, sunburn, radiation burn, fixing the engine on your car, ad infinitum, apply aloe. It can be ours or straight from the plant or even any other more natural aloe. Just put it on, it helps. We can say with ours, if you apply it a few times, you will find the burn goes away and the redness even gets better. Just please, do not apply it to open wounds, ie: really bad burns. That may not be a good idea.

- Here’s one you may not know. Damaged hair (this can work on dry hair too…). Get a raw egg, 2 tablespoons of our aloe Vera gel (or use aloe straight from the plant if you want and can), 2 tablespoons of olive oil and half a lemon. Mix it real well and then massage it into your hair very well. You want to get it all through the hair, not the roots. Let it sit for about half an hour. Then wash it out real thoroughly. You can do this once or twice a week and you should find a major difference in your hair!

- Now something people don't like to talk about, hemorrhoids. If you suffer from them, then you know how unbelievably painful and uncomfortable they can be. Well, use our Aloe Vera gel frequently. You will feel the difference. You just need apply it to the area regularly and let it absorb.

- Athlete's foot is another one. Feet are the unsung heroes in our lives. Day in, day out we pound them into the pavement and do little for them. Well, give them a little treat, after you get out of the shower or before you go to bed at night, treat your feet to a little of our aloe. Try rubbing some on those hard workers each day, at least once (make sure you get between the toes!). I'll bet you will get that stuff under control and your feet will thank you.

- We've heard that there're ladies out there who have gone through that amazing experience of bringing a baby into this world but who have then suffered from horrible, ugly stretch marks that just won't go away. Maybe some of you have small marks that you'd like to see gone. Our Aloe Vera is a great way to go. Keep applying it whenever you think of it, but at least daily. After a bit, you should see a difference. (By the way, we hear that vitamin E does wonders too, for any kind of scarring.)

Ultimately, I have to say that out of 15 years of trying to find a healthy moisturizing product, this is the best I've come across and I do not intend to stop using it anytime soon.

I've used oil on my hair before: Coconut, Apricot, Argan...etc but Castor oil is in a class of its own. I bought it because its suppised to help hair growth. It's extremely thick and it doesn't absorb as quickly as other oils do. I made the mistake of putting way too much on at first. A little definitely goes a long way.

I would probably dilute this with another oil to make it easier to apply. I used it 4 times a week and I did see my hair get thicker and it looked healthier as well. I didn't see much growth lengthwise but my hair is notoriously hard to grow out.

Tropical Isle Living is a good brand and the oil is high quality and a good price. I would order again.

column6: Aria Starr Beauty ORGANIC Argan Oil (4 OZ) For Hair, Skin, Face, Nails, Beard & Cuticles - Best 100% Pure Moroccan Anti Aging, Anti Wrinkle Beauty Secret, EcoCert Certified Cold Pressed Moisturizer
column14:
This review is going to be informational:

The founder Aria emailed me about my experience with this product. I said "I have been a little disappointed in that it feels greasy on my skin contrary to what I read in reviews. It also doesn't seem to soften my hair as people commented."

This is what she wrote back:

Please allow me to address your concerns:

Greasy Skin: With Argan Oil, a little goes a long way. So, maybe try using less (1 drop is more than enough) and massage into your skin.

Soft Hair:

Here's our recommended uses for hair:

For short hair: 1-2 drops
medium hair: 2-3 drops
long hair: 3-4 drops

Our recommended use is after a thorough wash. Apply the drops onto the palm of your hand and rub both palms together and then comb through with your fingers (do not pat on) and massage into your hair while your hair is still wet.

Aria was extremely gracious and generous with her time, feedback, care and concern. She really wants people to have a great experience.

I noticed he now doesn’t like to take pictures and tried to hide his forehead with hair, which makes acne even worst.

When Retseliney sent me their Acne Treatment products, my grandson visited me from NY for few weeks for the summer. So, I have him try all 3 of Retseliney’s acne product. To my amazement, even though I am not surprised since I am already a big fan of Retseliney’s skin care products, in about a month using the Retseliney’s Acne Treatment Skin care, acnes on my grandson’s forehead is completely gone! Not even trace of he ever had acnes. If I look really closely, I can see just a few spots, used to have acne, show discoloration. But from few feet away, no one will ever guessed he had acne ever. My grandson is so happy now and I can see his personality changed almost overnight. This is really AMAZING product. It’s been about 4 weeks now, but just a few days of using Retseliney, he started to see changes.

This is how he uses Retseliney products. I am not sure if this is the correct way to do it or not, but Retseliney’s customer service is superb and they will not have any problem answering if anyone have questions.

Everyday (7 days/week – at least 2 times daily ) AM and PM Skin Care. But if he sweats and have to shower, he apply same skin care again.
* He wash his face with Retseliney Acne Face Wash & Oil Control and apply Retseliney Acne Treatment Moisturizer Cream & Oil Control. (Only these 2 on his face)
* Every Wed and Saturday, he also apply Retseliney Acne Face Mask & Oil Control. He said he can actually feel his pores getting tighter. LOL. He only apply this on his forehead.

All 3 products are very gentle on his skin and cream goes on very smooth and he only have to use just little bit covers all affected area. He stayed with treatment without skipping a day. He really religiously stick to acne skin care regiment and he is so glad he did. He still have good portion of the product left. He said his face is all clear from acne but he will continue to use it.

column13: I've had mine for about a year and thought it was a good purchase based on the reviews
column14: DO NOT USE THIS HAIR DRYER!!!! I've had mine for about a year and thought it was a good purchase based on the reviews. However, while I was drying my hair this morning, the dryer started acting funny as if it was burning out (I'd only been using it for a few minutes). As I was moving the hair dryer down to look at it, the bottom near the cord suddenly sparked and burned! It ended up leaving a huge black mark and a burn on my left palm. It also hurt really bad. I tried washing off the black burn mark, but the pain was so bad that I did end up going to the doctor. The doctor confirmed that I had a contact burn and it was already blistering on the lines of my palm. I started doing some research after this happened and I've found that I'm not the first person who's experienced this issue with the hair dryer. Bottom line: don't buy it!!

column13: Perfect Straightener At A Perfect Price!
column14:
I have fallen in love with a hair straightener!! Yes, its true. I usually buy the cheap ones for $20 or so because well, I am cheap. I was given the opportunity to buy this one at a discounted rate in exchange for my entirely honest review. I can, honestly, say that this is definitely worth the price. It compares to the really expensive ones that my hair stylist uses.

So, here are my thoughts. Let me start by saying I have wavy, difficult hair to straighten and I was expecting to have the same difficulty with this straightener. First, I notice the extra length in the cord and I was quite happy with that. Then, I turned it on and increased the temperature, although it will heat up to 450 degrees, I just left it at 390 degrees. I don't want it too hot, but I need it hot enough to get rid of those difficult waves. Within seconds, it was heated up and ready to go. Alright, time to get to work. As soon as I applied it on my clean, dry, absolutely no products hair, it just slid right through it. Turning those difficult waves into straight and sleek strands. It took 5 minutes for me to complete my entire head of hair....and I have a lot of hair. My daughter came in and asked, "You're done already?" Yes dear, I am!!

The handle on this is so wonderful. It is designed to not slip through your grasp but it is still easy enough to not get stuck in your hand as you are trying to slide it through your hair. The cord is a great length, it heats up within seconds, has a LED display right on the front, the controls are on the inside, so as not to accidentally turn it up, down or off in the middle of doing your hair(which on others, this happens) and it has an automatic shutoff.

This is a must have for anyone that needs a flat iron. No need to spend a fortune for a professional iron when this one is just as good, if not better!!

This is a review for INTENSIVE WRINKLE FREE ANTI AGING EYE CREAM with Argireline® , Fiflow® and other potent anti-wrinkle peptides, 15 ml
from First Botany Cosmeceuticals ....

Product Description
Intensive Wrinkle-Free Anti-aging Eye cream is a novel eye cream that is extremely effective at firming and plumping the skin, quickly reducing the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles and addressing the issues of puffy eyes and dark circles under eyes treatment.

Main Ingredients in this Eye Cream:
• Fiflow® - Fiflow® has long-term effects due to its capacity to supply Oxygen to the skin. In cosmetic formulations, it acts in multiple levels (fast penetration, instant skin volume, muscular relaxation, cellular detoxification) to impart Botox®-like effect.
• ARGIRELINE ® NP- This ARGIRELINE peptide is well known for diminishing the appearance of expression wrinkles.
• Leuphasyl® - This is a revolutionary tandem when combined with ARGIRELINE ® helps in diminishing the appearance of wrinkle. These duo works great together.
• Cassia Angustifolia Seed Polysaccharide - Extracted from the seeds of the Indian Senna plant, botanical alternative to Hyaluronic Acid, demonstrating immediate and intense moisturizing effects that last up to 24 hours, plumping fine lines to provide a smoother, more radiant complexion.
• ChroNOlineTM- Peptide derived from Growth Factor derivatives helps in maintaining skin's firmness
• Borago Officinalis Seed Oil - It contains a high concentration of GLA (Gamma Linolenic Acid), combats inflammation and restores moisture to dry skin.
(Fiflow® is a registered trademark of Creations Couleurs)
(ChroNOlineTM is a trademark of Unipex Group Inc.)
(Argireline® and Leuphasyl® is a registered trademark of Lipotec, S.A.)

Some of the benefits that from this product are:
-COLLAGEN LOSS, MOISTURIZATION AND FIRMING: Intensive Wrinkle Free Anti aging Eye cream is a power house light cream packed with botanicals and anti-wrinkle ingredients that have multiple preventative functions which includes firming, building essential collagen and increasing moisture nourishment.
-BORAGE OIL and ChroNOlineTM: Borage Oil contains the highest GLA (Gamma Linolenic Acid) concentration, which helps to increase cell resilience and moistens the fatty layer beneath the skin in this anti wrinkle eye cream Borage Oil, along with other botanicals and ChroNOlineTM delivers a multitude of beauty benefits such as aiding collagen loss, soothing dry, scaly skin and combating the appearance of wrinkles.
-POWERFUL FORMULA: The formula for this eye cream exemplifies, 'luxury', and therefore it is formulated with the ingredients we would want to see in a luxurious product, including the successful pairing of 5% Argireline® (the most well-known peptide) along with 5% Leuphasyl®.
-FIFLOW®, ARGIRELINE ®, LEUPHAYSL ®: Fi-Flow makes the product feel like a soft mousse that is transformed into a light serum like a feather once applied to skin. Fiflow® has long-term effects due to its capacity to supply Oxygen to the skin. This Cream has an instantaneous dermal filling and muscular relaxation effect. Argireline ® 5%, Leuphaysl ® 5% and other ingredients are also blended in this anti wrinkle cream with peptides
Indications:
Effective at firming and plumping the skin, quickly reducing the look of fine lines.

column6: Plant TherapyCinnamon Bark Essential Oil 100% Pure, Undiluted, Therapeutic Grade
column13: Set the romantic mood with the pure, spicy scent of cinnamon!
column14:
This species of cinnamon bark, Cinnamomum verum, comes from the Ceylon cinnamon tree which is considered the best of 'true' cinnamon (as opposed to manufactured 'fake' cinnamons). I love to dilute this with jojoba oil and use in a diffuser to set a romantic mood - the spicy scent is known for its aphrodisiac qualities. Cinnamon bark essential oil can cause tingle on the skin or in the eyes/nose when diffused, so very diluted is best!

I love that this company adds some common uses of the essential oil and that there is an identifying label on the top. That is a nice add for those of us who have many oils and sometimes have to sort through them to find what we are looking for.

If you are looking for a cinnamon bark essential oil for its fragrance, this species is ideal.

I received this product at a discount as a product reviewer due to the company changing their labeling.

It looks like mud, feels grainy when you're scrubbing it in, smells terrible, and while the whole 72 hours thing was complete bull as I expected, it does it's job well enough. I bought clean and clear exfoliating scrub the day before, not at all expecting amazon to deliver the pronexin so fast and needed something to keep my face from breaking out horribly while I waited for it to arrive. When it did arrive, I didn't wanna let the clean and clear exfoliating scrub go to waste so I've been pairing it with the pronexin. First I wash my face with the clean and clear and then with the pronexin. Now, I'm not sure if its just the one face wash that works, or the combination of both but my skin has never been more clean and soft. I suffer from mild acne, it gets especially bad when my hormones are going crazy once a month. I'd get giant cystic zits everywhere that would take a month to disappear on their own and then by then the whole viscous cycle just starts all over again. On top of that, my skin would get really oily and other products just dried out my face and did absolutely nothing for my zits. So far, I haven't had any giant or new zits but then again, I've only been using the face washes for a week or two. I'll keep using both to see how they hold up against the horror that is my biological functions but so far I'm liking the results I have now. My skin is soft, clean, and oil free without the terrible drying and peeling other products gave my skin, and the acne marks I had before even cleared up. Anyway, here's to hoping this stuff keeps doing an awesome job.

column6: Braun Silk-épil 7 Wet and Dry Epilator, White
column13: Update: Holds up to first impressions... Wow and wow! Fast and thorough hair removal
column14: My Silk épil 7 came today, and had to try it as soon as I opened the box (I was very happy it came  pre-charged so I could satisfy my need for instant gratification ;-)  Initial impressions: the Silk épil 7 is outstanding! I've been performing some combination of shaving, epilating, and/or waxing over the past many years, and this gave me the best results I've gotten so far! I was a little reticent at first, because I had a Braun Epil a few years ago that was just ok, but I wanted to give the new one a try, and I'm so happy I did. This Silk épil 7 has so many great features, and it's performance exceeded my expectations. The additional accessories are a nice bonus, and the light is such a thoughtful addition (yikes! I hate to think about how much I've been missing with previous treatments...)  I tried it on my legs and face, and used the massaging cover as well as the sensitive area cover, and got the same great results with different combinations of accessory. I highly recommend the Braun Silk épil 7 to anyone, and look forward to using it again!  --------- 9/21/15 update:  I've had the Silk épil 7 for over a month, and have used it 2-3 xs per week since receiving it through a BzzAgent campaign. My first impressions still hold, this is a great epilator, with the battery life of an energizer bunny!   I had completely written off epilating several years ago after having frustrating experiences with other products (including Brauns' older models) and the Silk épil 7 has converted me back! Why you ask? There are 4 reasons: 1. The tweezing (or epilating) head is much more effective than any other I've tried. It grabs every hair without breaking it off, and does it quickly. I used mine for every area, and haven't had to go over the same area more than twice. 2. The head covers!  They help to give so much more control and accuracy than anything I've ever used. The high-frequency massage cap has made a big difference in whether I end up with in-grown hairs (not a single one yet!) 3. The light... wow! I can only imagine what I'd been missing before! and finally, 4. The battery!! Like I mentioned, I've been using this 2-3x's/week for about 6 weeks and other than the initial charge, I have NOT re-charged it yet, and it's still going strong (if only my cell phone had a similar battery!!)   I'm thrilled with the Silk épil 7 and cannot recommend it enough!

column6: OrganicGOLD Face Serum Pure Virgin Coconut Oil. Organic and Natural. Deep Moisturizing and Intense Hydration. Anti-aging, Antioxidant. For Smooth, Young-looking and Glowing Skin
column14:
This serum is exceptionally moisturizing, and it feels wonderful on my skin. It is truly expertly formulated and the packaging is lovely. That said, I do feel that the balance between the eucalyptus and vanilla is off, and could have used something...say some mint, perhaps, to balance it. I usually love blends of eucalyptus and mint, but I feel as though the vanilla in this is simply too heavy for me to wear on my face, I am able to use it on my hands, to moisturize, but the scent is too strong for my face, unfortunately, and for that I've had to remove a star. I do typically love perfumed products so this really surprised me, and I have been using this liberally on areas of myself further from my olfactory senses, because the coconut oil is quite lovely in its moisturizing properties, I wish I could use this on my face as other people seem to, and maybe if given the opportunity I will try the peppermint rose, as I love peppermint and roses.

The bottle is gorgeous, reminiscent of something out of an old movie to me, and I think it looks beautiful on my vanity, there is something just so pretty about how the dropper works with the gold button, its almost mystical or Victorian.
I got this product at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

column6: Secret Outlast Clear Gel Antiperspirant and Deodorant Scent, 2.7 Ounce
column14:
I had the pleasure of trying Secret Outlast® Clear Gel for FREE via BzzAgent for review purposes! My opinion is that of my own!

First trying this product I noticed a light, fresh scent! Which I LOVE because I do NOT like overly scented deodorants. I want to smell fresh and clean, NOT like I bathed in perfumed!
I really put this deodorant to the test! I read the claims of 48 hours of protection from wetness and odor. I put some on one morning and did not reapply for 48-hours. I was a bit worried I was going to stink, and noticeably so....
HOWEVER,
I did not! After jogging, walking, running, chasing after two kids, chasing after two dogs, and doing all that I do in a 48 hour time frame, not once did I notice my under arms to have a foul odor. I was amazed... not that I will wait another 48 hours ever again, but it's nice to know that the claims are not false!
Very happy about the clear gel formula, no more worrying if I accidentally get a little of my deodorant on my clothing (It can be my little secret and no one will know)!
I will also state I am also happy about the price point, for this deodorant! It's affordable and it works! Try it, you might like it too!

My best estimate is if using this twice a day, one tube will last one month or 6 weeks at best, depending on how heavy you put it on. I do admit I apply quite liberally. Probably more like a nickel's amount than a dime. I do like the tube form of this cream because many Korean creams come in jar form, which I find to be less hygienic.

column6: Philips Norelco BeardTrimmer 3500, cordless with adjustable length settings (Model # QT4014/42)
column13: Best trimmer for heavy stubble! (5~7mm length)
column14:
I have owned many different trimmers and clippers in the past decade years. This is hands down the best beard trimmer for heavy stubble and trimming it evenly.

The adjustable guard on this lets u change the trim size by very small amounts so u can find the ideal length to the millimeter (very important for me; i like to trim my goatee area 1mm shorter than my sides because of the differences in density of my beard hair in these areas).

I love that the size you are trimming at is clearly visible on the spin dial (on other adjustable guard trimmers, it is sometimes hard to see what length u have set. Which leads to cutting shorter than intended sometimes...).

Also the guard is locked securily in place (in some cheaper models of phillips adjustable trimmers, if you press too firmly down on your skin, you can move the guard setting to a smaller length and messup your beard!)

The blades are rounded edges so that when you use the trimmer with no gaurd to outline ur beard line, it doesnt hurt or cut you.
The guard itself is also smooth and doesnt needlessly stick out with points like many common guards do. So you don't stab yourself with the guard while trimming... and u can also trim more evenly the hard to reach areas like mustache and under the ears.

I searched for days for a trimmer that would allow me to perfect the heavy stubble look (5~7mm). All my past trimmers cut unevenly at heavy stubble or higher gaurd settings so I would get patches of hair noticibly longer than other hair, and lots of missed hairs. I was even willing to spend $200 on a trimmer if it would do a great job at cutting beard hair evenly. But it turns out that the best trimmer ended up being this model, which is relatively cheap.

With most trimmers, 1~3mm will give an even cut. However the longer you want your beard trimmed (5+mm) the harder it is to get even because the hairs bend down and most guards do not pick them up nicely.
Using this trimmer the guard is smooth and not bulky so you can trim ur beard in a circular manner to get the hard to cut hairs and the ones that get bent down. Using this circular motion I am able to get very nice results.

I think you should use this trimmer to define the neck line of your beard, but you should still have a razer to trim the bulk of the neckbeard for a closer shave.

For the record I also own the "phillips norelco multigroom 3100" and "wahl 9854-600 all in one trimmer." This trimmer beats both of them in everything, except i will admit the wahl seems to have more power to its blades trim speed, and i think the wahl is slimmer which I like better. In my experience wahl trimmers break easily, and phillips last a lot longer.

I think this trimmer could be improved by being a bit slimmer and straight instead of bent. But as far as all the other trimmers i researched and have owned, this is as good as it gets for heavy stubble!

column13: The Best Cream for Sensitive Skin
column14: This is the best moisturizing cream for sensitive skin. My skin is so sensitive that I store the cream in the refrigerator so that the cream goes on cold. Before using CeraVe, I was plagued with dry skin, redness and irritation. After four years of using this product, I get regular compliments from strangers who are shocked to see how flawless my skin is. Of course, I have applied SPF 50-grade sunscreen to my face everyday of my life, but this moisturizer is the keystone of my beauty regime. I have tried legions of moisturizers, from the $300-plus kind to budget varieties. I have used every kind of facial device, from a sonic cleaner to a blue-and-red-light device to those iPod-like heat devices. Nothing comes close to this cream in terms of maintaining my skin's health. I use it for my face and body, and pair it with CeraVe's non-foaming moisturizing cleanser and a physical sunscreen.

column14: This stuff is literally magic. I've had moderate to severe acne for around 5 years along with very dry sensitive skin. column6: 11 Pcs Makeup Brush Set Kabuki Powder Foundation blusher Cosmetic Bamboo Handle
column13: Very Nice, especially for the price.
column14:
I have been searching for some reasonably priced makeup brushes for a while. Nothing at the drug stores would do and the high end brushes are so over priced it is a crime. I do have several Sephora brushes (have no idea where I got them) and I know they are considered quality, high end. So after reading reviews on this set I took a chance. They just arrived today and, like the other reviewers said, there is an odor of paint but it was faint and washing them (which should be done anyway) got rid of the smell.

I compared them to my Sephora brushes and they did very well. They were just as good in the following:
softness-both are soft as rabbit fur
density of bristles-perfect! Dense enough for proper use but not too dense, no crowding
no shedding-No shedding!
usability-Holds the makeup nicely in the brush and distributes well. Easy to simply rub on a towel to clean between colors.

And I think the handles are superior to the high end ones. They are a bit thicker for better grip and are lacquered so makeup does not stain them, it wipes off.

I really have nothing bad to say about these. Perhaps the only thing would be that I would trade some of the bigger brushes for a couple more eye brushes but they give you the basics so I cannot really complain there either.

So I have to highly recommend.

PRO:
As good as or better than my high end brushes

CON:
nothing

column13: CALLING ALL LADIES, THIS IS A REASONABLY PRICED, QUALITY DOUBLE EDGE RAZOR
column14:
Okay ladies out there, I'm speaking to you. These aren't only for guys anymore. I will not pay hard earned money on rediculously high priced pieces of plastic, silly lubricating strip with single, double, triple or quadruple semi-sharp blades made in Vietnam, Taiwan, China, Mexico or any third world country!

I hate shaving! Unlike many women, I must shave daily, otherwise, I'd need to drag the string trimmer and blower into the bathroom. My legs are long and extremely difficult to shave. I can easily go through two or three so-called quality, name brand disposable razors. I even use men's disposable razors with half a can of Barbasol. Now you know why I hate shaving. When I began shaving, I would sneak my father's butterfly razor into the shower. I'll not quote my father's response, as this is a family friendly site. I'll only say, he was not happy when he began shaving with a dull blade.

I decided to try both a butterfly and a three piece double edge razor. This razor is fantastic! Add Feather double edge blades, and you'll be amazed at the results. You will effortlessly remove the dreaded stubble for a fraction of the cost of disposable razors. You can purchase large quantities of blades for very little cost here on Amazon, or in ebay.

There is absolutely no reason to fear shaving with a double edge razor and Feather or, any other quality double edge blade. You have everything to gain, and nothing to lose.

column13: Pleasant Scent and Consistency and Very Effective
column14: My review is for the SPF55 Ultra Sheer Sunscreen, 1 oz. tube. (It seems that reviews for other types are intermingled here.) SPF55 offers protection for up to 80 minutes according to the package directions. I smooth it on my face and neck before I leave the house for my morning 60+ minute walk. Even though it's early in the day, and sometimes a bit overcast, the strong summer sun can still break through. Just one squirt of this lotion covers my entire face and neck and goes on smooth. It has a pleasant scent, unlike the strong chemical smell of other stronger lotions. It's slightly greasy in appearance at first, but absorbs quickly. It does sting if you accidentally rub it into your eye, so it's probably best to wash your hands after application if you're in the habit of touching or rubbing your eyes frequently. I like the 1 oz. tubes since they're the perfect size for my purse and travel kit. I never leave home without it.

column6: OZNaturals Face Peel Contains 50% Glycolic Acid - This micro chemical peel helps dissolve skin, clear blocked pores, Fade the appearance of dark spots & fine lines for a healthy youthful glow!
column14: Ha!! Scary! Applying a 50% acid solution to my face is not something I do a lot lmao. I admit it. I was a little terrified. BUT I read up on glycolic acid peels and they of course are quite common in various strengths (many stronger than this one) and the data shows that acid peels are super effective for collagen production, age or sun spot reduction, and exfoliation. So, I proceeded with caution. The acid solution is a gel. You apply it to one of the included gauze pads and apply a thin layer to your clean skin. It was a bit stingy, but nothing unbearable. They say to leave in on for 1 to 4 minutes. I left it on for two.. Just to make sure I didn't have a bad reaction. To neutralize the acid you MUST rinse your face with a solution of 8oz of water mixed with two tablespoons of baking soda. It bubbled and fizzed on contact and got very warm. I then rinsed very thoroughly with cool water and applied a moisturizer. The scariness was over. The result of my bravery was super soft glowing skin, a BIG reduction in the size of my pores, and what I THINK is a lightening of my sun spots. It will take more applications to know for sure. This is serious skin care and needs to be used with caution. But the final results were so great I will be upping my application time and enjoying my nice glowing face! I am a product tester for Oz Naturals and received this product in exchange for an honest review... And believe me, I would NOT have been happy if this had gone badly. Home run for Oz!

When I want to hop in the shower and get done quickly, having to stop and do anything extra is a bit of a hassle. I have four kids that like to pick the moments when I do anything to try to compete for the kid version of MMA. LOL!

If I remember to, (life is busy) I will update my review to include longer term results. As for current, short term ones, my face feels ok. No irritation from harsh soaps or scrubs. It feels clean but not stripped.

I did receive this item at a discount for an honest and unbiased review. My opinion is my own. I would recommend this to friends with my current experience with the product. :)

This cleanser is awesome-sauce and don't judge the content of my review based on the fact that I use the word, "awesome-sauce," but what better way can I describe my savior from oils? I did a search on Amazon for a oil-free cleanser because I've always had oily skin. Also, my skin isn't a normal oily. It's oily to a point where a little girl once asked me, "Why is your skin so greasy?" :-| True story. That was about twelve years ago, but it sticks out in my mind. Anywho (I digress), I read in some of the reviews that the cleanser was very drying. So since I have abnormally oily skin, I thought to myself, "Self, you should try this out." I have and must say that it has saved me! Skin that was normally oil within an hour of applying makeup, is not dry, but is also not shiny. It now appears that I have a healthy glow, even that my skin is rejuvenated. I started using this along with the [[ASIN:B000052ZB8 Neutrogena Oil-Free Moisture, Combination Skin, 4 Ounce]] and find that the combination together is doing a great job.

One of the reviews did mention breakouts when not using the product and I would have to agree with the same. If I happen to fall asleep with my makeup on (which I do often and likely contributes to my cycle of oily skin), then I do get a breakout here and there, so I definitely recommend consistency with use - morning and evening. All I can say is that this cleanser is awesome for removing makeup as well as calming oily skin. I would recommend. With regards to over-drying, I could see how it might be over-drying for someone with dry or even normal skin, so try at your own risk or maybe even just once a day.

Price-wise, I believe you can find it cheaper in Wal-Mart or Target, but we all know and love the convenience of Amazon prime!

column14:
"Fresh Batch"
Mine was packaged in November of 2014- its 9 months old. Far from "Fresh".
As for the actual powder, it's OK. Smells like it should. Not bad, but the reason I purchased this particular Henna was because of the fresh factor.

I will revise this review after I have actually used it this week- I hope the age doesn't effect it's usability. :/
_______________________________________________________________________________________
*REVISION*
The powder came out well when mixed with warm water- it took a while to get it to the right pudding consistency but once I had it, it stayed nice and smooth- the grassy smell didn't bother me either. The application of it was messy of course- it dripped everywhere, even when my head was covered it dripped down my neck. But, I know it would be messy so nothing was stained or damaged because I was well armed with ugly towels and rubbing alcohol.

Getting it out was very troublesome- but I had added hibiscus powder which I believe made rinsing it out a pain- I don't blame the Cassia itself. I rinsed with some silicone free conditioner to help get it out and after about 20 minutes in the shower it was out for the most part. I shampooed a bit and conditioned like normally- I should have deep conditioned instead because the next day my hair was very dry and straw like. :/ BUT it did make my naturally straight hair more straight so that was a plus

I went ahead and did a deep condition treatment yesterday (after letting my hair get dirty for a couple of days on purpose) with much success, my hair looks pretty darn good- but it's still a bit dry which kind of bums me out
I also used a clarifying shampoo to get rid of all the remnants of the cassia and hibiscus so that helped too.

If I had to do it all over again I'd nix the hibiscus and just use the Cassia itself, then follow up with a really deep conditioner and avocado oil and just not touch my hair for a while. I really do think it helped to smooth my hair out- but I'd advise you to make sure you have a nice rich conditioner on hand to revitalize your locks afterwards. It didn't damage my hair, but it dried it out and the back was nest like before the deep condition treatment. Still a bit dry, but I'm sure it'll go away with time.

Next time I use this (I have some left over) I'll do it the way I described above and add to this review to see if the Cassia still dries out my hair- I don't think I'd use it again if it did, unless I really wanted to straighten it. It gets wavy from time to time which I don't really like so we'll just have to see how the next treatment goes (if and when).

Also regarding the freshness, I apologize for any misinformation I received regarding the freshness of Cassia. I was told that fresh batches are considered at most 12 months old- so that's why I thought that I received a dated one.ut- but I'd advise you to make sure you have a nice rich conditioner on hand to revitalize your locks afterwards. It didn't damage my hair, but it dried it out and the back was nest like before the deep condition treatment. Still a bit dry, but I'm sure it'll go away with time. Next time I use this (I have some left over) I'll do it the way I described above and add to this review to see if the Cassia still dries out my hair- I don't think I'd use it again if it did, unless I really wanted to straighten it. It gets wavy from time to time which I don't really like so we'll just have to see how the next treatment goes (if and when). column13: Highly recommend for older women who want a deep moisturizer without alcohol or astringents
column14: I had used Ponds Cold Cream with the green flower on the label for almost 30 years.  I started using Ponds as a moisturizer before applying makeup, as I had three women, individually, tell me that's what they used, and they all looked very young for their age.  I use regular soap in the shower, then I'd apply Ponds, then blot it off with a towel.  I have had people tell me I look much younger than my age.  However, my new jar of Ponds seems to have had the formula changed, as it now made my psoriasis break out.  I thought I'd try Nourisse.  I couldn't have picked a better choice.  Nourisse is as greasy as Ponds, but an even more luxurious whipped texture.  It GREATLY moisturizes. I still use a towel to blot off the excess before I apply makeup.  Perhaps someone young might find it too greasy (after all, it's supposed to be a night cream), but for my purposes as an older woman, it's great.  It also has a wonderful, light and fresh smell to it.  It's a fairly small jar, but I know it will last a long time, because I only need a small amount to hydrate my whole face.  Even after having it on all day, my face feels sooo soft and moisturized.  I love that it's natural and I'm not getting any toxic ingredients like Ponds must have. The BEST thing is that there is no astringent or alcohol in it.  What sense is applying a moisturizer that will ultimately dry out your face!

column6: Remington MB4040 Lithium Ion Powered Men's Rechargeable Mustache Beard and Stubble Trimmer, Black
column14:
It's an inexpensive trimmer so don't expect a lot, but you get a lot for your money for sure. It does give you the stubble look. Those saying they can't have this happen easily need to watch the instructional video that Remington provides on youtube, it shows how to properly use it. It's not as intuitive as you might think and I suspect many people are using the device wrong. I shave with the stubble blade without the guard and have a perfect stubble look.

As others have said, when you shave with the bare blade only use the stubble blade for that..if you use the larger blade you could cut yourself..the larger blade is intended to be used with the guard for your actual hair. The battery lasts forever and it is light and relatively quiet, easy to clean.

column6: Fengshang White Gold Vintage Crystal Flower Vase Chandelier Earring Simulated Pearl
column13: delicate earrings for a special occasion
column14:
These are really pretty, delicate earrings, but they're definitely for a formal occasion rather than everyday use. The picture is fairly representative, although the pearls in mine were more teardrop shaped (fatter at the bottom and more pointed at the top), which I actually like a little better.

They're quite lightweight and comfortable. I have a metal sensitivity so I did coat the posts with a few coats of clear nail polish and I was able to wear them for several hours with no trouble.

There are a lot of stones in these and they were all securely fastened in place (none were loose). They have some nice sparkle to them. And they come in a cute little gift box. If you are looking for some earrings for a formal occasion, but you don't want to spend a ton of money, these are a good option.

Product provided by the seller for evaluation purposes.

column14:
I just want to thank you for your acts of kindness, your patience and gentle spirit. If only more merchants took pride in their work and in their customer service...boy! what state would this world be? It's nit about the "I" "I" but its all about thw "You!" "You!" That should be every merchants motto and it's pretty obvious that it's yours!!!

I want to write you up the best post that I could ever think to write anyone as AWESOME AS YOU! However, I haven't been feeling my best, lately and as soon as I am, I want to write something really really nice about you and your business/products/customer service...because you are just an AWESOME business woman that OBVIOUSLY LOVES HER WORK AND CARES ABOUT PEOPLE WITH HEALTH ISSUES WHO COME TO YOU FOR HELP IN FINDING WAYS TO LET OTHERS KNOW ABOUT LIFE-ALTERING, SOMETIMES LIFE-THREATENING MAJOR ISSUES THEY MAY HAVE HEALTH-WISE.

Health attendents - total strangers need to know "AT A GLANCE," should we be unable to COMMUNICATE ON OUR OWN BEHALF DUE TO BEING IN DISTRESS and what better way do it than go provide as much information as possible! You obviously care more about us (people in general) than you do about making a quick buck and charging us by the letter... You found such creative ways to get every important thing about my health listed on the braclett that I purchased AND THE NECKLACE THAT YOU GAVE ME FREE...AT NO CHARGE TO ME!!!! YOU ARE SO AWESOME!!!!

Again, I love your product, I love your work, and I love your sweet, sweet, gentle, giving spirit! I pray the Lord blesses you and your business no less than 100-fold for your acts of kindness shown towards me, His child...and others!

Have a blessed last night!

Diane Hines
P.S. I cannot believe that I only meant to write a quick note letting you know you've been on my heart to write-up a post for (something I usually DO NOT do!) and that I had not forgetten you...WHENI LOOKED BACK AND SAW ALL I HAD JUST WRITTEN! WOW! I GOT SO EMOTIONAL THAT IT ALL JUST POURED FROM MY HEART BECAUSE OF MY SINCERE GRATITUDE!

column14: I bought earrings on amazon from a retailer that no longer sells their earrings.  They were very small threaded posts, and I lost one because they are so tiny, you can easily drop them.  These posts were supposed to be a replacement, however the holes are too big.  I will use them for my other earrings, as the white gold is excellent for not reacting and being very comfortable.  Unfortunately, it is hard to buy things online because you never know if they will fit exactly.  I'm off to the jewelry store to find a replacement back, I hope I can find one that fits the tiny posts and doesn't cost a fortune.  I would recommend these replacement backs if you have earrings with a fairly big post.  Good price for white gold.

column14: I purchased a larger 3-tier bracelet holder at my local craft store.  Unfortunately, it did not fit the bill.  I want to keep my bracelets in a dust free cabinet.  But when I got the larger model home it was too big to fit on the shelf of the cabinet.  (I failed to take height into account when I went shopping for that one.)  I gave that holder to my daughter (she has more closet space) and ordered the Songmics 3-tier velvet bracelet holder from Amazon.  This one works well.  It has a shorter profile yet it appears that I will still be able to store the same number of bracelets on it.  It was well packaged; arrived safely and quickly.  The individual "velvet rolls" pull out easily from the stand which gives you greater access to your bracelets or watches.  Highly recommend.

It seems to be a quality setting and it has just the right amount of sparkle. My only complaint is that there are some visible defects in the morganite. column6: Sterling Silver and Cubic Zirconia All-Around Band Ring
column13: Razzled & Dazzled as Well as Frazzled & So Very Confused
column14:
I do wish Amazon would get it together in their descriptions when it comes to CZ jewelry. Case in point: the PRODUCT SPECIFICATIONS of this ring states minimum 5.13 cttw--Almost double the 2.7 carats stated in the TITLE . I don't know which of these is closer to the actual total carat weight. I understand that the carat weight can vary from size 5 to size 9 in a ring that has stones all the way around. However, this ring clearly has significantly larger stones (as shown in my photos) than the other one I ordered at the same time [[ASIN:B009PKAQR8 Platinum Plated Sterling Silver Round Cubic Zirconia All-Around Band Ring, Size 7]] which also contains discrepancies in what its cttw is. Here is what I do know (as of the time I am writing this review):
It is part of the Amazon Collection
Ships from and sold by Amazon.com
It is very sparkly & appears well made
Amazon has great prices

I ordered BOTH rings because I couldn't decide which one would be the right size/look for my taste. In the end, it didn't really matter because I found the ring itself to be uncomfortable. In both sizes. For me, the stones on the sides (where they rub against adjacent fingers) were irritating so I returned the ring even though it was really pretty. If I could find a similar ring with the stones in a BEZEL-style setting rather than prong settings, I will have located my perfect ring! I've included some photos and I hope you will forgive the sickly appearance of my hands. I was trying to capture the clarity and sparkle of the stones as they actually appear so I was using various combinations of incandescent and halogen lighting & flash. It really is difficult to photograph jewelry, particularly while wearing it!

column14: This set is very pretty, not as bold as some jewelry I have.  The crystals that hang from the tassel style earrings and necklace are very well cut, they catch the light beautifully.  I'm not crazy about the little crystals at the top of each tassel, but that's just my opinion.  They are small enough that it doesn't matter much.  The white gold plating is flawless; the earrings have post backs and a 2.5" drop.  The necklace (and earrings) are a snake chain.  The necklace has a small lobster claw clasp, and measures 15" with a 2" extender, so 17" total (not including the Y pendant in the front).  However if you wear it on the extender, it will hang crooked.  The Y drop pendant portion measures 3".  The chain on both the necklace and earrings tend to get little crimped bends in them, that are impossible to smooth out.  It's a small issue, almost unnoticeable when you are wearing the set, but I thought I should mention it.  It comes in a paper gift box and mine included a free scarf gift.  I received it free in exchange for my honest review.

column13: Think twice - you want your pearls to match
column14: The pearls are the same size and shape but do not match as far as color and lustre are concerned.  When I place my pearls on a sheet of white paper (which is the industry standard for determining lustre and color in pearls), one pearl has a white undertone with poor lustre, but the other has a pink undertone with exquisite lustre.  You might think that them being on opposite sides of your head, no one can tell.  And likely, that may be true.  But I notice.  And it is completely unacceptable that a pair of earrings are so mismatched.

column6: Handmade Glow in the Dark Necklace,Romantic Gift,Sunshine Necklace,White Gold Plated,Water Drop Shape
column13: A sweet pendant that I think is more for kids than adults
column14:
I am not sure I understand the reviewer who wrote that this doesn't glow at all. It definitely does, but like all glow in the dark items like this, they first need to be exposed to light before they will glow in total darkness. And this isn't meant to be a "light" but rather simply a glow in the darkness. When it lights up with that gentle green glow it is really fun. I am not sure I go along with the product description that it is either romantic, or a romantic gift but I guess we all have our own ideas of romance. To my mind this necklace which looks equally lovely when it isn't glowing, is more geared towards a younger audience.... girls not yet thinking too much about romance. For me, I loved anything that glowed in the dark prior to the age of about 16. I could see kids loving this and having fun looking at it in their room at night when they are supposed to be sleeping. Personally, having been an insomniac almost since birth, I loved anything I could entertain myself with at night (get your minds out of the gutter, please) when my parents thought I was sleeping. I had a whole arsenal of glow in the dark trinkets that kept me company right along with my stuffed animal collection. But I digress.

I do think this is a very nice pendant. I am not a fan of the chain which competes with it a bit and is altogether a bit too thin. For the current pricetag of around twenty dollars, however, I think this would make a terrific gift for any young girl. It MIGHT be a bit too large for a very small child. The pendant itself is 3/4' long by just over a half inch wide. Some might think that this too much for a petite girl to carry off. Personally I think it would look great.

BOTTOM LINE: For the money I think this is a five star pendant though the chain brings it down a notch. Good news is that you can change it to a different chain. I was sent a complimentary review sample and am favorably impressed. If you are looking for this to be high end jewelry, you would be disappointed but I am not sure where you can get high end jewelry for twenty dollarss to be high end jewelry, you would be disappointed but I am not sure where you can get high end jewelry for twenty dollars

column6: The Sea of Jewels - Sterling Silver 'Baullarum' Earrings
column14:
My ears tend to be very sensitive to cheap earrings. My ear lobe will turn red and itch like crazy within the first 30 minutes of wearing them. I have been wearing these earrings for a few hours now and I am not having any adverse reactions - this makes me SUPER happy.

The earrings look beautiful and are large as other reviewers have said, but they do not weigh my lobes down as a matter of fact I don't even feel them. I also like that that the stem is long. Sometimes they are so short it's hard for the back to stay on. That's a non-issue with these. The backs are fairly snug so you don't have to worry about them slipping off the stem.

I have attached a photo for you to see the size as it fits on an ear lobe, however; please note the photo does not do justice to the clarity and detail of the earring.

My only gripe is the other reviewers got their earrings in a nice box, mine came in a super cheap faux dark blue velvet bag that was inside of a ziplock baggie. That is a serious standard quality issue - I took 1 star off for the quality difference. Presentation is important too.

The Sea Of Jewels provided this sample for testing and review with no guarantee of a favorable review.

I wanted a simple band to wear instead of my diamond wedding ring, but I wasn't willing to spend a lot. This ring is thin so it's comfortable to wear, but the material is hard and durable so I'm confident it won't bend or break. I had read previous reviews so I knew the color would be slightly more gray than the advertised picture. As you can see in my photos, it is more gray than my white gold wedding ring. From a distance the color difference isn't too noticeable, but I probably won't wear them together.

Overall, I'm very satisfied with my purchase and I would definitely buy again if I needed to.

column13: Very stunning vintage style statement necklace
column14:
[[VIDEOID:54f2867fe49314b534da2566c6913312]]This is an impressive statement necklace especially from a distance. I think that up close it is lacking in detail and I think it is because you see so much of the gold triangle shining through but that is also what makes it look more like a vintage piece as this is exactly what they would have looked like back when they were originally made.

This necklace seems very well made especially for the price and would make a great gift. It glitters and shines and catches the light perfectly. The chain is adjustable so there are quite a few different lengths that you can wear this at. When you have it on the tightest hook the chain hangs down your back a good 3 inches and looks very cool from the back.

I look forward to wearing this with a simple black dress and making it the showpiece. However, my daughter has her eyes on it and I actually had her wear it to get a couple of pictures. I have included measurements in the video review in case you are wondering about that.

Also, I need to add that the clasp is easy to use, even my husband can do it with his giant banana hands and he typically can't help me with any of my jewelry.

Overall, this is a very nice vintage look that would set off even the simplest of outfits and make them look even more expensive.

I received this complimentary product for my honest and unbiased review.

column13: i'll start w/ the good 1st then the not so good
column14:
i'll start w/ the good 1st then the not so good;
Super fast shipping ! got it from the east coast to the west coast in 4 days via USPS - WOW !!
The paracord weaving & connections all seem to be sturdy & well made -- BUT .....
Know this before you purchase. ! This bracelet is made LARGE - it is too big for me as an adult female, & certainly way too big for the adolescent girl that I intended it for. (which I seem to have incorrectly figured would be the primary marketing target for the product)
Also note that the 'riveting' of the plate to the bracelet is done BADLY and covers a good portion of the embossing of the first symbol & the last letter - appears to be a big type-O- not very pleasing to the eye, nor would it make a gymnast proud to display her passion in such a shoddy fashion.
For the amount paid I am disappointed, spend your $'s on a better quality product - I am sorry to say that this one is not worth it.

column6: Platinum Plated Sterling Silver Round Cubic Zirconia All-Around Infinity Band Ring
column13: Dazzled and Impressed... but also Dazed and Confused
column14:
I do wish Amazon would get it together in their descriptions when it comes to CZ jewelry. Case in point: the PRODUCT SPECIFICATIONS of this ring states minimum 2.64 cttw--AND 3.07 carats. I don't know which of these is correct, if any. I understand that the carat weight can vary from size 5 to size 9 in a ring that has stones all the way around. However, this ring clearly has significantly smaller stones (as shown in my photos) than the other one I ordered at the same time [[ASIN:B00BG9MODK 18k Yellow Gold-Plated Sterling Silver Round Cut Prong Set Cubic Zirconia All-Around Band Ring (2.7 cttw), Size 7]] whose title states 2.7 cttw! Here is what I do know (as of the time I am writing this review):
It is part of the Amazon Collection
Ships from and sold by Amazon.com
It is very sparkly
Amazon has great prices
I found the ring itself to be uncomfortable. Maybe I have become too accustomed to comfort fit styling. For me, the stones on the sides (where they rub against adjacent fingers) were irritating so I returned the ring even though it was rather pretty. I've included some photos and I hope you will forgive the sickly appearance of my hands. I was trying to capture the clarity and sparkle of the stones as they actually appear so I was using various combinations of incandescent and halogen lighting & flash. It really is difficult to photograph jewelry, particularly while wearing it!

column6: Bling Jewelry Gothic Skeleton Hand One Piece Sterling Silver Ear Cuff
column14:
So I did not purchase this product to use as an ear cuff, so I cannot apply my judgement for that. Rather, I puchased it to use as a temporary lip ring. If that is a customer's intended use, then this item works quite well, in my experience. A few things to note, however:
1. You will have a lisp the first few minutes of wearing it, until you adjust to it being there. It may be advisable to talk to yourself before you go out, in order to learn how to talk around it.
2. While it does not slip off, it can move around a bit, especially if you are talking. I would not recommend eating with it on.
3. I have full lips, so the ring has more to hold on to. While it is adjustable, I can't say if it would work for individuals with thinner lips.

All in all, a good purchase. It's great if you want to have a wild look without the commitment. I most heartily recommend it to any of my alternate brethren out there!

column13: Arrived on different chain,  great locket
column14: Love the locket. That said,  what I ordered is not what I received. Mine did not come on a bamboo chain. It came on a 18 inch snake chain of some sort with a 2 inch extender and the locket cannot come off as the extender (rolo chain) is too thick to slide the locket past. I like the look of the snake chain - I was honestly going to take the locket off the bamboo chain and wear it on a cord anyway, so the mix up was a win for me - but it was annoying that what was pictured and described isn't what was shipped to me. 3 stars for the mixup or the misleading description. 5 star for the locket itself -  several months of use and it still has a very stiff closure so no worries that my charms will be lost and the frame and glass have held up to being dropped a few times. Overall pleased just a tiny bit of buyer beware.

column6: Sterling Silver Genuine Blue Topaz and Created Blue Sapphire Cluster Stud Earrings
column13: Excellent value for some nice colored gemstones
column14:
Bottom line: Amazon Collection's Sterling Silver Genuine Blue Topaz and Created Blue Sapphire Cluster Stud Earrings present a nice set of gemstone earrings at a very reasonable price. Recommended.

Jewelry is always a highly subjective purchase, the tastes and desires of the one receiving the item being the highest concern. If you like what you see, then it is a great item. That being said, folks want to know that they'll get what they think they're getting, and want to make sure that they're not paying for something they aren't getting.

When it comes to the Amazon Collection's Sterling Silver Genuine Blue Topaz and Created Blue Sapphire Cluster Stud Earrings, what you see in the description is pretty much exactly what you're getting. If you like the photos Amazon provided and the description, you'll like these earrings.

Where I found the product to be slightly different than what I might have imagined based on their descriptions and photos, I've noted below where it was better or worse in my humble opinion. When looking to buy colored gemstones, there are some things to consider.

First, set a budget. Looking at the current price of these earrings, this is a good value and within my budget. Actually, looking closely at the stones, it might be somewhat undervalued by Amazon...you're probably getting a better deal than you would at a mall jeweler. They come packaged in an attractive but simple box, suitable for gift giving.

The first thing Amazon notes about gemstones in their description is Color, one of the "4C's" discussed in gemstones (Color, Clarity, Cut and Carat, which Amazon listed as size). Color is the most important thing in colored gemstones like sapphires and topaz, the two stones in these earrings. I found the color of the synthetic sapphires to be superb, far exceeding my expectations from the product description. Color for the topaz was good--not quite as good as I expected from the photos in the description, but very good for the price. More concerning was the subtle difference between the matching color between the paired sets. There was a slight variation in color between the matched pairs that is noticeable when placed side by side in good lighting on a uniform background. This is not going to be something noticed when the jewelry is worn, but certainly something speaking to the quality of production and the overall value of the set. Given the price, it is certainly under acceptable limits and still presents a good value although if looking at a set costing thousands of dollars it would be unacceptable.

Cut is the next thing to look at. The sapphires are essentially a round cut, the darker topaz is an oval and the lighter topaz a pear. Cut is done well with good brightness and sparkle. The darker topaz and sapphires are somewhat better than the lighter topaz in this regard. To my eye, the pear shape cuts were more oval than the photos on Amazon showed, but not to a significant degree in my opinion. I have attached some photos of my set for comparison, although the lighting isn't ideal. Again, for the price we have a good value here.

Clarity is also very important. Fortunately, topaz is a very clean stone in terms of clarity, and synthetic stones such as the sapphires should not have any problems. Looking at the stones with the naked eye at about a foot away, the stones are all very clean and look quite attractive. Under magnification using a loupe and microscope (up to 40x--far exceeding any normal viewing), some imperfections were seen in both the topaz and the sapphires. Topaz had some minimal inclusions with some internal fractures, as well as some minor chipping and pitting at the facet edges. Surprisingly there were also some subtle imperfections in the synthetic sapphires as well. Again, nothing alarming here, and the stones are well beyond eyeclean standards, so at the price again we see agood value.

Size is exactly as advertised, and once again presents a good value.

There was no gemstone certificates with these earrings. Given the price for this set, this is not surprising or even desired, but it is something to consider when purchasing colored gemstone jewelry so it is worth noting.

The stones are set in sterling silver, which should work well for almost anyone and again presents a good value for this set. The backings are a bit flimsy and probably not the best given the size and weight of the earrings, but can easily be replaced if this is a concern or problem.

Overall, the set represents a good value for the price. If you like the color and the style, I recommend the set. If you find this review to not be helpful, please let me know so I can edit it to better assist you.good value.

column13: ... wanted to get a wedding band that was not super expensive but still looked good (and matched
column14:
I wanted to get a wedding band that was not super expensive but still looked good (and matched!) my fiancee's white gold band. This certainly does the trick! The color is very close to white gold (albeit a little bit darker...see the photo below. The ring on my little finger is my fiancee's band). The ring has a little bit of weight, but I like that in a ring. If you would rather have a ring that feels like you aren't wearing one, tungsten carbide is probably not for you.

Unlike a few of the other reviewers, I found that the sizing was true. I had found my size by getting the plastic ring sizer from Blue Nile. If you are interested in getting this ring to size the first time, I would request one of the plastic ring sizers for free from Blue Nile and then order this ring after finding your size. I hope this review was helpful! Feel free to ask any questions.
